title: italian cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add vanilla to milk.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to sugar.

title: creamsicle cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Poke holes in cake with a meat fork.
Pour jello over cake and refrigerate.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Liberally grease and lightly flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Individually prepare cranberries, nuts and orange peel for use. Set aside. Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt (optional) together in a bowl. Cut in shortening. Stir in orange juice, egg and orange peel, mixing just enough to moisten. Fold in cranberries and nuts. Spoon mixture into prepared pan. Bake 60 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on rack for 15 minutes. Remove loaf from pan and cool completely before cutting.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain.
Saute onion, pepper and celery in bacon drippings.
Remove vegetables with slotted spoon.
Add rice to skillet.
Cook until rice starts to brown.
Add onion, pepper and celery to rice.
Add bacon, crumbled; mix well.
Make a hole in mixture.
Put eggs in hole.
Stir with fork until eggs are cooked, then shred egg through mixture.
Serves 4.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend in flour and mix well.
Add oats and nuts.
Drop onto baking sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mom's corn bake
directions: Mix all ingredients except chili and cheese.
Chop chilies and mix with grated cheese.
Put 1/2 of the corn mixture in a 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Put the chili and cheese mixture over corn. Pour the rest of the corn mixture on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 35 minutes or until firm.

title: three fruit drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender. Process until smooth. Yields 4 cups.

title: pecan raisin pie
directions: Melt margarine. Add sugar and eggs, beat. Add rest of ingredients. Bake 45 minutes at 325°. Enjoy with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: school day cookies
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; boil for 1 minute in large saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add the oats, vanilla and other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: mandarin orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and add sherbet.
Stir until sherbet has dissolved.
Let stand until slightly firm.
Add mandarin oranges.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Butter a jelly roll pan or cookie sheet with edges and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Pour batter in and spread thinly. Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Treat as a jelly roll.
Roll up in wax paper until cool.
Unroll and fill with the filling.
Roll up again. Freeze until ready to use.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together for 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Use 2 round pans.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9x5 inch loaf pan. In a large bowl and using a fork, mix the first 5 ingredients. Using a pastry blender, put in the shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Using a fork, stir in bananas and eggs until blended.
Spread batter in a pan and bake for 55 mins. - 1 hr., or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool before cutting.

title: jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple in saucepan till boiling.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Put mixture in serving bowl.
Mix in cottage cheese.
Cook and add cool whip.
Chill in refrigerator until set.

title: chocolate delights
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well and place in a well greased, medium size cookie sheet, spreading thin.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
While cookie is baking, melt chocolate chips.
As soon as dough is baked and removed from oven, spread chocolate on top.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts or white chocolate chips.
Cut into squares after cookie has cooled.

title: favorite icing
directions: Combine milk and flour in saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Cream together sugar, butter, shortening and vanilla.
Add cold mixture and beat for 10 minutes.

title: skillet macaroni and beef
directions: Cook beef in a large skillet until it loses its redness. Remove from skillet and cook onion, macaroni and green pepper in meat until macaroni is yellow.
If meat fat is not sufficient to prevent sticking, add a tablespoon or two of Wesson oil.
Return to skillet along with tomato sauce, water, salt, pepper and sauce. Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until macaroni is cooked to suit taste.

title: pepper steak
directions: Place in frying pan with 2 tablespoons butter and brown for about 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Place in medium-sized casserole with 2 1/2 cups cold water.
Place in oven and bake for about 1 hour at 350°.
Serve over rice or potatoes.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine, egg, vanilla and chopped pecans. Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, margarine, egg, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: all in one dinner
directions: Fry all together until hamburger is done.
Place half of the sliced potatoes in greased casserole.
Cover with 1/2 of hamburger mix.
Layer the hamburger mix and potatoes.
Cover with combined soup and milk.
Top lightly with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: aunt mary lee's broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; toss with next 4 ingredients and chill.

title: flour tortillas
directions: In a bowl, mix the flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix the oil and 1/2 cup of warm water together.
Mix the flour mixture and the water mixture together.
Add a tablespoon of water at a time to the flour mixture until the dough can be gathered into a ball. Let it rest for 15 minutes.
Divide dough into 12 portions; shape into balls.
On a lightly floured surface, roll each ball into a 7-inch round.
Cook in ungreased skillet over medium heat for about 1 1/2 minutes per side, or until lightly browned.
Makes 12 tortillas.

title: queen salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients in order, mixing well with each addition.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: rusty nail caramel sauce
directions: Heat sugar
and
teaspoons
cold water over moderate heat; stir
until dissolved, then swirl pan until golden brown caramel. Set
pan
in sink and stir in cream slowly.
Caramel will seize. Boil over moderate heat until thick.
Remove from heat and
pour in
vanilla,
Drambuie
and
Scotch.
Stir
in butter; let cool 5 minutes.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Serve over your favorite ice cream.

title: froot loops snacks
directions: Melt almond bark in double boiler.
Pour over Froot Loops and pecans and drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: pork oriental
directions: Cut pork in 1-inch squares.
Brown pork in oil, stirring frequently, 15 minutes.
Combine brown gravy mix, water, honey, soy sauce, ginger and garlic salt.
Add to skillet.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.
Add carrots.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add onion and pepper.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream together shortening, brown sugar, molasses and eggs until fluffy.
Sift together all remaining ingredients and add to shortening mixture.
Once blended, form into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: cream of lima soup
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan combine broth, beans, the 1/3 cup green onion, margarine or butter, curry powder, tarragon and pepper. Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Cool slightly.
Pour mixture into a blender container.
Cover and carefully blend until smooth.
Return to saucepan.
Stir cream and heat through. Sprinkle each serving with green onion tops.
Makes 4 to 6 side dish servings.
I use powdered milk instead of cream.
Very good with salad or as a first course.

title: diet fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.

title: lefse(norwegian dish)
directions: Boil potatoes, mash very fine and add cream, butter and salt. Beat until light and cool.
Add flour.
Take piece of dough and roll as for pie crust, rolling as thin as possible.
Bake on top of grill (one at a time), until light brown, turning frequently, to prevent scorching.
Use very hot griddle or in 12-inch skillet (475°).

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar and oil.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually beat in egg mixture.
Stir in poppy seed and almond extract.
Divide batter into two well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Add vanilla; stir cereal until evenly coated.
Put in bag or bowl with tight lid.
Add 10x sugar.
Shake until well coated.
Sweet and crunchy!

title: spanish wane rice
directions: Rinse the starch off of the white rice and place it in a microwave-safe dish. Add the remaining ingredients and stir. Microwave for 15 minutes, then stir. Continue to microwave for 35 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter and pour in a Pyrex dish.
Pour graham cracker crumbs over melted butter.
Generously sprinkle coconut, chocolate chips and pecans over crumbs.
Pour condensed milk on top. Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes or until top browns.
After cooling, cut into small squares.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Add pumpkin, eggs, shortening, milk, vanilla and chocolate chips. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pecan tarts
directions: In medium sized bowl, combine cream cheese, 1 stick margarine and flour.
Mix until crumbly.
Form dough into ball.
Cover and chill 1 hour.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Mix jello per directions (cooled, but not jelled).
Place Twinkies in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour jello over Twinkies and let set.
Mix pudding by directions.
Pour over jello.
Let set. Cover with Cool Whip.
Top with cherries and nuts.

title: barbecue chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil in skillet.
Stir in barbecue sauce, water and rice.
Cover.
Cook over medium heat, about 20 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Stir in corn.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer at least 5 minutes.

title: cold macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and cool; combine onion, green pepper, Cheddar cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise, sugar, salt and pepper.
Combine well.
Chill.
You may add chopped, boiled eggs, if desired.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Scrape and cook carrots whole.
When softened, cut into desired shapes.
Mix all other ingredients except bread crumbs. Add to carrots, mixing well.
Top with crumbs.
Some cheese may be reserved to mix with crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and crumbs are lightly browned.

title: cheese baked carrots
directions: Slice and cook carrots.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion and saute.
Add flour, salt, mustard, celery salt, pepper and milk. Cook until mixture comes to a boil.

title: sausage crescent nuggets
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium-sized skillet, lightly brown sausage and drain.
While sausage is still hot, add cream cheese and stir until cheese is melted and creamy.
Cool completely.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix together water, sugar, salt and yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Add eggs and soft shortening.
Mix first with a spoon, then with hands.
Add lukewarm mashed potatoes.
Add flour; work and knead well.
Let rise to double in bulk.
Work down and shape in rolls.
Let rise and bake or keep in refrigerator for several days before baking rolls.
Makes good "loaf bread".
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Dip in butter and fold over before baking.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook broccoli to crisp tender.
Combine with rice and 1/2 the cheese.
Saute celery and onion in butter.
Combine with broccoli mixture.
Add milk and soup.
Pour into casserole dish.
Place balance of cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: potato skins
directions: Cut potatoes in half, scoop out some of the potato.
Deep fry until brown.
Place potatoes on baking sheet, top with cheese. Broil until cheese is melted.
Garnish with green onions and bacon bits.
Serve with sour cream on the side.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown meat in large pan.
Add onions, celery and garlic until done.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Water may be added if needed; heat.

title: old-time ginger and molasses cake
directions: Mix boiling water and shortening.
Add sugar, molasses and egg.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
May top with whipped cream.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix and frost layers and top.
Chill before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: garden macaroni salad
directions: Gradually add mayonnaise to cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Stir in relish and mustard.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.

title: rigatoni
directions: Fry and drain hamburger.
Boil rigatoni, drain and mix all ingredients.
Top with shredded cheese.
Place in microwave or oven at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: colleen's hot sauce
directions: Melt butter and add catsup over low heat until blended.
Add brown sugar, stirring until blended.
Add garlic pepper and garlic powder.
Stir.
Blend in oregano and add hot sauce to taste. Simmer briefly.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix and flour; dissolve jello in hot water and let cool.
Add jello and oil to flour mixture.
Add eggs (1 at a time); mix well after each egg.
Add strawberries and juice.
Mix well.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: In dish mix together cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning mix. Shred lettuce, tomatoes and onions.
Sprinkle over mixture.
Top off with Velveeta Mexican cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in covered dish or pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove and brush with coating (melted butter, salt, pepper, oregano, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt).
Place back in oven, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Remove and turn pork chops over.
Brush with the remaining coating.
Bake for 5 minutes or until done to desired crispness.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In large frypan, saute butter, onion and celery.
Blend in flour, stirring well.
Add milk and half and half slowly; keep stirring until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat; cover and let set.
In a 4-quart (or larger) saucepan, cook broccoli in 4 cups water for 6 minutes.
Add chicken bouillon; cook and gradually add the milk-onion-celery mixture.
Simmer on low heat.
Add cheese and ham until cheese is completely melted.
Serves 8.

title: rollini di vitella, polla(veal or chicken rollettes)
directions: Slice veal or chicken very thin.
Cut in 4 to 5-inch squares. Mix garlic, parsley, basil, salt, cheese and ham.
Place heaping teaspoon of mixture and slice of onion on each square.
Roll and tie with a string or toothpicks very carefully.

title: rabbit salami
directions: Chop celery and onion.
Put cleaned rabbit in baking pan with chopped vegetables and bay leaf.
Roast at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove rabbit and add butter and flour to drippings.
Cook until brown.
Add water, salt, olives and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir and replace meat.
Bake another 45 minutes at 350°.
Garnish with parsley.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain and rinse first 4 ingredients. Add other ingredients and mix well. Put into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Sprinkle with topping.

title: easy au gratin potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Pour into a well-greased casserole or baking dish (9 x 13-inch) or smaller. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This can be topped with extra cheese and browned the last 5 minutes.
tags: cream of your favorite kind soup

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Put fruit in buttered dish. Put bread fingers on top of fruit. Melt margarine. Add sugar, flour and egg. Pour mixture over bread and fruit. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: irresistible clam dip
directions: Before mixing ingredients, lightly rub bowl with garlic. Combine remaining ingredients in bowl and chill for 3 hours or more.
Good served with corn chips.
The flavor is at its best when made a day ahead.

title: golden punch
directions: Put sugar and cold water in large vessel and bring to a boil. Use
another
vessel
with
close	fitting
lid.
Pour boiling water over tea leaves and steep for 4 minutes.
Strain and cool (do
not
put
tea	leaves in aluminum or tin).
Add juices and salt
and pour over ice in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale and any slices of fruit.
Serves 50.

title: poached eggs
directions: Heat milk slowly in a large skillet.
Add salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon butter.
Add eggs when milk is steaming (don't break yolks).
Spoon milk over eggs.
About now, put toast in toaster. Turn eggs, if necessary.
Stir milk, it will start to look like gravy.
Butter toast in plate.
Place 1 egg on each piece of toast.
Spoon gravy over top.
Add salt and pepper to taste!

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots in water with 1 teaspoon of sugar until almost tender.
Drain.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Make into balls size of walnut.
Place in oblong baking dish or pan 2 inches deep.
Cover with sauce and bake 45 minutes.
Turn balls and bake 45 minutes longer in 350° oven.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Moisten bread crumbs with milk.
Combine with ground beef, salt and pepper.
Shape mixture into balls.
Place in baking dish.

title: caramel apple oat squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine flour, oats, sugar, soda and salt.
Cut in margarine or oleo until crumbly, reserving 1 1/2 cups of crumb mixture.
Press remainder on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Add nuts to reserved crumb mixture.
In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt caramels with condensed milk, stirring until smooth.
Spoon apple filling over prepared crust.
Top with caramel mixture then reserved crumb mixture.
Bake 20 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Serve warm with ice cream if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Frozen chopped broccoli can also be used.

title: cinnamon zucchini brownies
directions: Mix oil or butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat thoroughly. Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add zucchini and nuts.
Blend well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: hobo stew(good for crowd)
directions: Saut meat, onion and celery.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer on low heat about 2 hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth. Add peanut butter and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour mixture into pie crusts.
Freeze overnight.
For variety use chocolate pie crusts, put chocolate syrup over top and serve, spoon fruit pie filling on top and serve, or line pie crust with banana slices before filling.

title: baked fish(serves 1)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine seasonings with chicken soup dissolved in water.
Coat fish in this mixture, then in bread crumbs.
Place in baking dish and bake for 30 minutes.

title: chili-cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat in fondue pot.
Keep and serve warm.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cinnamon scents(nonedible)
directions: Combine applesauce, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir until well blended; work mix with your hands until it has a smooth clay like consistency.
Generously flour pastry board and rolling pin with cinnamon.
Roll out about 1/8-inch thick.
Use your favorite cookie cutter and form shapes.
With a skewer, mark details on cutout shapes.
Make holes where ribbon or string will be threaded through.
Place on cookie sheet.
Place in 120° oven.
After 1 1/2 hours, turn off heat.
Leave in oven 5 to 6 hours or overnight. Store in airtight container.
Can be placed in dresser drawers or hung in rooms for the fragrance.

title: no-bake chocolate cake
directions: Melt chips in double boiler over warm water.
Add peanut butter.
Mix together well.
Add raisins and remove from water. Heat and add the cornflakes.
Mix until covered well.
Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper or cookie sheets.
Chill until firm in refrigerator.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix juices from pineapple and oranges with pudding mix.
Cook until slightly thick.
Cool.
Refrigerate overnight, after pineapple, oranges and peaches have been added.
Add strawberries, bananas, cherries and grapes before serving.

title: cinnamon rolls (bisquick)
directions: Mix ingredients until dough forms.
Beat 30 seconds.
If too sticky, gradually mix in enough Bisquick (up to 1/4 cup) to make dough easy to handle.
Turn onto surface dusted with Bisquick. Roll in Bisquick to coat.
Shape into ball and knead 10 times. Roll to 1/4-inch thick rectangle.
Spread with 3 tablespoons melted butter.
Sprinkle with mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Roll like jelly roll and cut off 1-inch slices.
Bake on greased pan for 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese and coconut pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine, Crisco and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.

title: pineapple do-nothing cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. (Do not use mixer.)

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown meat in large skillet and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and spices to taste.
Cook noodles.
After noodles are ready, layer noodles, sauce and cheese in 3-quart glass casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until cheese is brown.

title: surprise bundles
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar in small bowl.
Roll each biscuit around each Kiss.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture to coat. Place on cookie sheet; bake at 350° for about 10 minutes, or until biscuits are done.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Mix together rhubarb and jello.
Spread over first layer.
Mix together butter, sugar and flour.
Crumble over top of rhubarb mixture and pat lightly.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: scalloped scallops
directions: Saute scallops in butter for 5 minutes.
Add flour, cream and milk; cook until thick.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put in buttered casserole.
Cover with 1/2 cup bread crumbs; bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sandy's white chili
directions: Cook beans in chicken broth until done.
If necessary add more broth to beans.
Add garlic, onions, chillies, cumin, oregano and cloves.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add chicken and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve topped with grated cheese, salsa and sour cream.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Combine cocoa with sugar, salt and syrup.
Stir in milk. Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Cook to 232° or until a small amount of mixture forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water, stirring several times during the cooking process.
Remove from heat; drop in butter.
Cool to lukewarm (110°).
Add vanilla and beat until mixture thickens and loses its shiny appearance.

title: gazpacho soup
directions: Chop the first eight ingredients very fine.
Mix together. Then add remaining ingredients.
Chill well before serving.
May add additional tomato juice to thin if necessary.
Serves 10.

title: red raspberry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir until well blended. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 50 minutes at 325°. Serve with whipped cream.

title: apricot almond bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop apricots finely.
Add water, butter, sugar and salt and mix.
In separate bowl, sift together the pastry flour and baking soda.
Add to apricot mixture, then add whole wheat flour, almonds, egg and orange extract.
Stir well and put into buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf tin.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: hacienda dip
directions: Mix cheese, salsa and salt until well blended, spread cheese mixture in microwavable pie plate or bowl.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring every 2 minutes. Makes 2 cups.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all but cheese; fold in cheese.
Bake at 400° until golden brown in 13 x 9-inch pan, about 45 minutes.

title: magic fruitcake
directions: Put mincemeat and water in a medium pan and bring to a boil. Let boil for 1 minute stirring occasionally; cool.
Combine eggs, condensed milk, mince meat, fruit and nuts.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 inch tube pan, 2 loaf pans, or 4 small loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours until center springs back.
Reduce time to 1-1/2 hours for loaf pans, and to 1 hour for small loaf pans.
Brush with Karo syrup for glaze.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook pudding and mix with half of Cool Whip.
Chill until set in crust.
Remaining Cool Whip can be used on top if desired.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Beat eggs and milk until well mixed.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in well-greased 2-quart casserole and set in pan of hot water.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until set.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream
the
first 3 ingredients until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time.
Mix several more minutes.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture alternately with milk. Add flavorings last.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not open
door for first hour.
After removing from oven, let stand for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: creole hamburgers
directions: For sauce, cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender. Add soup, water and thyme.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes. Stir often.
Serve over sizzling hamburgers.

title: pancake and waffle mix
directions: Mix together thoroughly. This may be used immediately or stored away in a cool place for later use. When using, take equal amounts of mixture and milk (sour milk is best). For pancakes, use 1 egg to 1 or 2 cups mixture.
For waffles, use 1 egg to each cup of mixture.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Prepare jello as directed on package.
Chill 1 hour stirring 2 times.
Mix jello and other liquids in large bowl.
Freeze.
Three hours before serving, put frozen mixture in punch bowl to thaw.
At serving time, add strawberries and ginger ale.

title: baked apples
directions: Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.
Delicious breakfast treat served with hot biscuits.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix separately the melted oleo, eggs, sugar and vanilla. Add dry ingredients separately.
Mix well. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, corn syrup, flour, salt and vanilla.
Beat until well combined.
Stir in butter and pecans, mixing well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 60 minutes or until filling is set.

title: fruit pizza
directions: *Whichever ones are in season, strawberries, grapes, bananas, kiwi and peaches are good.

title: layered salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together in large salad bowl.
Top with spoonfuls of mayonnaise and cover with grated Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until golden brown and bubbly all over.

title: cheezie potatoes and broccoli
directions: Add water, salt, margarine and broccoli to a pot that holds at least 4 quarts.
Place on burner and bring to a boil.
Add milk and remove from heat immediately.
Add potato flakes and stir with a fork.
Place in a large casserole dish; cover with cheese. Place in a 400° oven until cheese is melted and lightly browned.

title: bread
directions: Knead; turn in greased bowl and let rise 1 hour.
Punch down; let
rise
minutes.
Divide
in fourths; shape into loaves and
let
rise.
Bake 30 minutes at 425°.
Butter tops just before removing from oven.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix the pineapple, pudding, marshmallows and pecan pieces together.
Then add Cool Whip and stir well.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: skyline chili dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Pour thawed chili over cream cheese.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 30 minutes.
Place Cheddar cheese over chili until melts. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cucumber medley
directions: Mix together cucumbers and onions.
Blend together rest of ingredients.
Toss lightly with cucumbers.
Chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot pickle cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage into quarters and pack into jar.
Add salt, pepper and
garlic
to
jar.
Boil vinegar and water together. Add vinegar and water to jar.
Process in a hot water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes 1 quart.

title: firehouse onions
directions: Thinly slice the onions and place them in a saucepan.
Cover with water and add butter or margarine.
Simmer until onions are soft.
Just before serving, add the ketchup and mix well.
Heat a few minutes and serve.

title: chocolate-banana lunch box cake
directions: Do not beat; stir until mixed.
Wrap individual pieces in plastic; store in freezer.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Scoop out 3 cups watermelon balls and all the cantaloupe and honeydew balls you can get.
Combine melon balls and grapes in large mixing bowl.
Add the frozen juices and mix well.
Slice and add bananas just before serving.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise and remove yolks.
Mash yolks with a fork.
Add mayonnaise, mustard and vinegar.
Mix well. Season with salt and pepper.
Stuff egg whites with yolk mixture. Garnish with paprika.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 dried beef.
Form ball and roll in rest of beef.

title: tortilla black bean casserole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper, canned tomatoes, picante sauce, garlic and cumin.
Add beans and heat.
Put 1/3 of mixture in 9 x 11-inch pan.
Top with half tortillas and half cheese.
Spread next 1/3 mixture and top with remaining tortillas and cheese.
Spread final mixture on top and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with lettuce, sliced tomatoes and sour cream and serve.

title: fruit nut cake
directions: Heat milk, cocoa and egg in double boiler, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in shortening until melted.
Add all mixed dry ingredients to cocoa mixture until smooth.
Mixture will be thick.
Spread in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.
Top with ice cream.

title: caramel-filled chocolate cookies
directions: Wash oranges, lemons or grapefruit.
Remove peel in 2 sections.
Cut each section into 1/4-inch strips.
Cover with cold water.
Heat to boiling.
Boil 10 minutes.
Drain.
Repeat 3 times.
Drain.
Cover with boiling water and simmer until tender. Drain.
Divide peel into 3 portions.
Prepare a heavy syrup, using 2 cups sugar and 1 cup water.
Color 1 portion of syrup red, 1 portion green and leave 1 portion clear.
Add 1/3 of peel to each portion of syrup.
There should be sufficient syrup to cover each portion of peel.
Cook slowly until tender.
Allow to stand in syrup overnight.
Drain thoroughly.
Roll in granulated sugar. Place on cake rack.
Dry in very slow oven (250°) until surface is firm.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: "A woman can throw out more with a spoon tha a man can bring in with a shovel."

title: audrey's pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup pineapple juice.
Punch holes in cake after cutting cake lengthwise in 3 sections. Pour juice over cake.
Spread each layer with mixture.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Dump chopped pineapple.
Dump cherry pie filling.
Dump box of vanilla cake mix.
Cover with layer of finely chopped walnuts.
Dot with butter pats.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour, or until toothpick can clearly be removed at center of cake.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.
Flavors of cake mix and pie filling can be alternated.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Add sliced strawberries and walnut halves to top.

title: jelly roll
directions: Add sugar to eggs gradually.
Add water and vanilla all at once.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add all at once.
Bake on a 10 x 15-inch pan for 14 minutes at 375°.
Grease pan; flour it.
After it is baked, roll on damp cloth.
Roll in damp cloth until cool.

title: neapolitan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of three 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans and three wire racks.
Line pans with waxed paper; grease wax paper.

title: simple angel biscuits
directions: Mix together.
Drop in greased muffin tins or roll out on floured cloth and cut.
Bake at 400° till golden.
Makes 12-15 biscuits.

title: baked sliced potatoes
directions: Cut unpared potatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Place overlapping slices in buttered oven-to-table 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix butter and oil.
Brush slices with mixture.
Pour remaining over potatoes.
Sprinkle with garlic, salt and thyme.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are done and browned at the edges.
Serve immediately.

title: graham cracker pralines
directions: Slightly grease cookie sheet.
Melt butter and oleo.
Add sugar; boil 2 minutes.
Pour immediately over graham crackers. Top with almonds; bake for 12 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan at once.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish, add broccoli, diced chicken and water chestnuts.
Mix together the mayonnaise, lemon juice, soup and pour over the mixture.
Cover with cheese and bread crumbs. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon together.
Blend all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Boil chicken until done.
Take chicken off bone.
Put 5 tablespoons grease in a skillet and fry green pepper and onions.
Take 1 1/2 cups of broth from the chicken and mix with mushroom soup.
Add pepper, onions and and pimentos into soup mixture.
Grate cheese.
Place a layer of noodles, then a layer of chicken, layer of cheese, layer of soup mixture and repeat.
Grate cheese over last layer and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: *To de-fat the chicken broth, place in the refrigerator until surface fat congeals, remove congealed fat.

title: easy baked corn
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in greased dish at 375° for 40 minutes.
(Don't make any substitutions.)

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix enough flour with can of cream of chicken soup until stiff enough to roll out.
Take small portion of dough, roll out and cut into strips.
Put into simmering chicken broth.
Cook
until dumplings are done.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Let cool to touch.
Peel and cut potatoes lengthwise into 1/4-inch slices.
Set aside.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Thoroughly mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Mix dry ingredients together; then add to shortening.
Mix alternately with milk. Fill greased muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, 20 to 24 minutes.
Immediately roll in melted butter and shake in a mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Serve hot.

title: fruit cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder at least twice.
Cut up fruit and nuts.
Use 1 cup of the flour to roll the fruit and nuts in.
Beat eggs separately.
Cream butter and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Add flavoring.
Fold in remaining eggs.
Add flavoring; fold in nuts and fruit.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: brandon's chili
directions: Brown meat with onion and drain.
In large pan add meat, juice, beans, Chili-O and tomatoes.
Let simmer 45 minutes.

title: chimichangas
directions: Shred roast beef, add onion and hot pepper to taste.
Simmer until tender.
Roll meat mixture in tortillas, then deep fry until crispy.
Serve with Enchilada sauce, salsa and cheese.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Stir pie filling and crushed pineapple together in baking dish. Sprinkle the cake mix on top. Add melted butter, coconut and chopped nuts. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm or cold with scoop of vanilla ice cream.
So simple and tastes great!

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, eggs, pickles and salt.
Moisten with mayonnaise.

title: amber pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg yolks, vinegar and raisins.
Put in an unbaked pie shell and cook.
When done, put meringue on top and brown.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish at 350°. Add sugar, baking powder, flour, salt and milk. Pour over melted margarine. Don't stir. Sweeten any fruit and pour over batter. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Serve with cream (optional).

title: honey-moist cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, stir together flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients just until moistened.
Pour into greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or just until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: divinity
directions: Beat Marshmallow Creme, water and vanilla at high speed until peaks form.
Fold in sugar and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: creme drop fudge
directions: Butter bowl.
Melt creme drops and peanut butter.
Pour into buttered bowl.
Chill.

title: hail to the chief
directions: In bowl of warm water, thaw pea pouch for 20 minutes.
In large skillet, cook sausage until browned; drain.
Stir in onion and garlic; cook until golden, about 3 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, chicken, celery, olives, Worcestershire sauce and hot pepper sauce. Bring mixture to a boil; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in rice and thawed peas.
Cover and continue cooking 5 minutes or until rice and peas are thoroughly heated.
Makes 4 servings.
tags: frozen early peas with butter sauce

title: hot fudge for sundaes
directions: Melt chocolate squares and 1/2 cup butter or margarine in top of double boiler.
Add salt.
Then add sugar, 1/2 cup at a time. Stir well after each addition.
Then add evaporated milk, small amount at a time.
Continue cooking until thickened.
Serve hot over ice cream.

title: seasoned onion rice
directions: Coat a medium saucepan with cooking spray; add onion and saute 5 minutes.
Add chicken broth, water, Worcestershire sauce, bouillon cube and pepper; bring to a boil.
Coat a 1 1/2-quart casserole with vegetable cooking spray; add rice mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
6 servings (about 136 calories per serving).

title: italian bread sticks
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix in Bisquick.
Beat vigorously.
Turn dough onto surface well dusted with Bisquick. Knead until smooth, about 20 times.
Divide dough into 16 equal parts.
Roll each piece between hands into pencil-like strips, 8-inches long.
Spread part of butter in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Put strips of dough in pan.
Brush tops with rest of butter. Sprinkle with caraway seed, poppy seed, celery seed, sesame seed or garlic salt.
Cover with damp cloth and let rise in warm place about 1 hour.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Pour dry pudding mix over undrained pineapple and mix.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Slowly fold in whipped topping. Refrigerate 3-4 hours.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
After it melts, add the sour cream, tomatoes and green chilies.
Heat before serving or keep warm in a mini crock-pot.

title: potato supreme
directions: Boil whole peeled potatoes for 15 minutes. Cool. Coarsely grate potatoes.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Put in long baking dish (mix together).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
May be made several days in advance.
Very good.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add bananas and mix until smooth. Combine next 5 ingredients and add to creamed mixture, stirring just enough to moisten.
Stir in pecans and raisins and pour in greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from loaf pan.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook ground beef; drain off grease.
Mix chopped onion, bell pepper, cream of mushroom and beefy mushroom soups together.
Pour into square pan; grate cheese over top.
Cover with Tater Tots. Cook in oven at 400° until potatoes brown.

title: misua at itlog(noodles and egg soup)
directions: In medium saucepan, saute garlic and onion in hot oil until lightly brown.
Add chicken stock and bring to a boil.
Season with salt, pepper and patis.
Lower heat to simmer.
Stir in misua and break eggs into the simmering stock.
Cook until eggs are set (about 2 minutes).
Serve immediately; garnish with green onions.

title: bacon sweet smoky links
directions: Wrap each link with about 1/3 piece of bacon.
Secure with toothpick.
Place all in large glass casserole dish, single layer if possible.
Pour enough brown sugar over to completely cover the sausages.
Bake covered at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until the sugar has melted.

title: easy lasagne(microwave)
directions: In large glass bowl, crumble ground beef.
Heat at High 3 to 6 minutes or until the beef is no longer pink.
Stir once; drain. Stir in spaghetti sauce and water.
Combine Ricotta cheese, egg and pepper.
In an oblong dish, spoon 1/2 cup sauce, alternate layers of noodles, egg mixture, Mozzarella cheese and sauce.
Heat covered with plastic wrap at High 8 minutes and at Medium-low 30 minutes or until noodles are fork tender.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and layer potatoes with thin strips of bell peppers and pimiento.
Melt butter and add flour, milk and cheeses.
Pour sauce over potatoes and cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until done.
Good with ham or steaks.

title: pot pie
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, combine soups, milk, thyme and pepper; stir in vegetables and meat. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: easy peach pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into baking dish with 3/4 cup melted butter.
Place fruit around in mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: busy mother's bread
directions: Use large mixing bowl.
Add all ingredients, making sure milk is lukewarm and not hot enough to kill yeast. Beat well as flour added a little at a time.
Add flour until dough can be kneaded by hand on a table.
Knead 5 minutes and shape into 2 to 3 loaves. Place in greased loaf pans.
Let rise until almost doubled in bulk.
Brush with butter.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 5 to 10 minutes, then lower to 350° until done.
Turn out to cool.

title: date nut torte
directions: Cream all together.
Spread in a greased pan, 10 x 14-inches. Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Then spread with topping.

title: chicken with mushrooms and onions
directions: Melt butter in medium skillet over medium high heat, add oil. Add onions, saute 5 minutes.
Add garlic powder, stir in well, add chicken.
Saute until chicken is opaque, 5 to 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms and white cooking wine, mix well.
Simmer over low heat 10 minutes.
If it looks too dry add more white cooking wine. Serve over white rice.
Serves 2 to 3. To serve 4 people, add two more cutlets.

title: chocolate torte
directions: In a double boiler add all ingredients, except the eggs. Separate the eggs, adding the yolks to mixture.
Beat the egg whites and fold in.
Bake 3/4 of the mixture in a spring-form pan at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Put shortening, sugar and salt in boiling water.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs, yeast, water and flour.
Mix well.
Cover with damp cloth in a warm place for 1 hour.
Punch down and roll out.
Put in greased pan for 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: apple crisp
directions: Toss together and pour into a greased 8-inch square baking dish.

title: toffee-pecan roulage
directions: Coat 2 (15 x 10 x 1-inch) jellyroll pans with cooking spray; line with wax paper and coat with cooking spray. Set aside. Beat eggs in a large bowl at medium-high speed with an electric mixer 5 minutes. Add water, beating at low speed to blend. Gradually add cake mix, beating at low speed until moistened. Beat at medium-high speed 2 minutes.
Fold in brickle chips and finely chopped pecans. Divide batter in half and spread evenly into prepared pans.
(Layers will be thin.) Bake each cake at 350° on the middle rack in separate ovens for 13 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched in the center.

title: butter chews
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in flour.
Pat into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry, and set aside.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in brown sugar, nuts and coconut. Fold in egg whites and put over first mixture.
Return to oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and dust with powdered sugar and cut into squares.

title: mr. l's peanut soup
directions: Chop the nuts very fine.
Place the nuts and the other ingredients in a large saucepan and heat, stirring for 20 minutes. Serve hot.
Soup is rich.
Make the portions small.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shake dressing over mixture and store in refrigerator overnight.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: In saucepan, heat gelatin, jello and pineapple until gelatin is melted. Take off stove and add buttermilk, Cool Whip and orange juice.
Pour into bowl and let stay in refrigerator until set. This makes a big salad.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.
A small amount of broth may be needed if you use plain deboned chicken.

title: frozen fruit ring
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Freeze in Bundt pan or muffin pans for individual servings.
Let set awhile before serving.

title: asparagus cheese pie
directions: Combine Parmesan cheese and crumbs.
Pat into a greased 10-inch pie pan or 2-quart baking dish.
Refrigerate for 15 to 30 minutes. In a bowl, combine the cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese and eggs. Stir in asparagus, basil, garlic powder and parsley flakes. Refrigerate for 15 to 30 minutes.
Pour egg mixture over crumb crust.
Smooth top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until knife inserted near the center comes out clean.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together first 5 ingredients.
Mix in one cup whole pecans.
Pour into 9-inch pastry shell and bake approximately 45 minutes to one hour at 350°.

title: three cheese macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
Add butter and stir in flour. Add onions and peppers. Beat eggs with milk real good. Add salt and pepper. Stir over heat until thickened.
Add cheese. Stir real good until well mixed, then add macaroni and mushrooms, drained.
Put in a casserole dish and bake 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: santee catfish stew
directions: Brown salt pork.
Add 2 cups water.
Boil fish and onions in water for 30 minutes.
Remove bones from fish and return to water. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Put milk in mixing bowl and slowly pour lemon juice into milk while stirring.
Whip the cream and fold 2/3 of it into the lemon mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Spread remainder of whipped cream on top.
Sprinkle generously with fresh grated lemon rind.
Place in freezer.
Serve partially frozen.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Top with cherry tomato.
Serves 4.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Make white sauce.
Add 1/2 cup Cheez Whiz. Simmer 5 minutes. Take your 4 cups cold cooked potatoes (1/4-inch thick or cubes) and place in casserole.
Pour over the white sauce and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes or until slightly brown on top.

title: piccalilli
directions: Drain vegetables of any extra liquid.
In a large kettle, add vegetables and 1/2 of vinegar.
Boil for 1/2 hour, stirring often. Drain and discard liquid, add remaining vinegar, sugar and spices.
Simmer for 3 minutes.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: williamsburg souffle
directions: Remove crust from bread; cut or break into bite-sized pieces and arrange in well-buttered 9 x 13-inch (or larger) Pyrex baking dish.
Heat 4 tablespoons butter in a skillet and saute sliced mushrooms with finely chopped onion for 5 minutes.
Spoon evenly over bread cubes.
Distribute ham over mushrooms.
Dust the grated cheese with flour and sprinkle over ham.
Beat eggs and add mustard, milk and garlic salt.
Pour over mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes (until puffed and brown).
May be assembled and refrigerated overnight before cooking.

title: easy potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Stir well.
Bake in a greased 2-quart shallow dish at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: so easy strawberry pie
directions: Crush 1 pint strawberries and place in a saucepan.
Add sugar and cornstarch.
Stir and bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute.
While mixture cools, slice remaining pint of berries and place in pie shell.
Pour cooked berries on top and refrigerate.
Good served with a dollop of Cool Whip.

title: smokey sensations
directions: Spread rolls to cover bottom of 9 x 11-inch greased pan. Sprinkle cheese and bacon over dough. Combine eggs, milk and onion. Pour over dough. Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes or until egg mixture is firm. Cut into squares. Serve warm.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with assorted fresh vegetables.

title: cheese cake
directions: Blend all ingredients, except crust.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with chilled pie filling, if desired.

title: white chili
directions: Sort and wash beans; place in a Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2-inches above beans; let soak 8 hours.
Drain beans and return to Dutch oven.
Add broth and next 4 ingredients. Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken and next 5 ingredients; cover and cook 30 minutes.
Spoon into serving bowls; top each with cheese (6 servings).

title: crinkle top cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Add molasses, salt, soda and spices.
Add presifted flour, 1/2 cup at a time.
Roll dough into small balls.
Dip in sugar and bake at 350°
for approximately 10 minutes.

title: spud nuts
directions: Mix sugar and shortening with potatoes and warm milk.
Then mix all ingredients except flour.
Add flour; let rise until double in size.
Roll out and cut.
Let rise 25 minutes.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix well.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: heavenly spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions; drain and cool. Saute ground beef until brown. Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper to beef. Remove from heat. Combine cream cheese, sour cream, onions and green pepper in a bowl. Butter a 2 qt. casserole dish. Spread 1/2 of spaghetti in bottom of dish. Cover with cream cheese mixture. Top with remaining spaghetti. Spread tomato-meat mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: "no-bake" cookie crumble cheesecake
directions: In blender, sprinkle Knox gelatine over cold milk.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Add hot milk and process at low until dissolved, about 2 minutes.
Add cream cheese, sugar and vanilla and process until blended.
Arrange chocolate in bottom of crust.
Pour in gelatine mixture.
Sprinkle with crushed cookies.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Makes 10 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream the softened cheese.
Add next 4 ingredients and mix well.
Fold in shrimp.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: baked beans
directions: Slice bacon into 1/2-inch strips.
Fry bacon, onion and garlic for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain beans.
Combine beans, onion mixture and remaining ingredients in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: cheddar cabbage wedges
directions: Cut the cabbage into 8 wedges, leaving a portion of the core on each wedge, leaving
a portion of the core on each wedge. Steam wedges in boiling salted water in large kettle for 10-15 minutes or until crisp tender.
Drain and remove core, place wedges in a greased 3 qt. baking dish.
In a medium saucepan, saute green pepper and onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook until bubbly, gradually add milk and cook and stir until thickened.
Pour over cabbage, bake uncovered at 375° for 15 minutes.
In a small bowl, combine cheese, mayonnaise and chili sauce, spoon over wedges and return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except pecans.
Fold pecans in last.
Mix about 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rancher's stew
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add all other ingredients; bring to boil and turn heat down to simmer and cook for 1 hour.
Great served with cornbread.

title: tofu fruit ambrosia
directions: Whip all ingredients in blender.
Use a variety of fruit in season, strawberries, blueberries, peaches, bananas, oranges, apples, pears and pineapple.
Keep tofu creams refrigerated before serving.
Prepare fruit by cutting in bite size pieces, pour on the cream of your choice, garnish with nuts, coconut and minced fruit. Change fruits with the seasons to enjoy all year round.
Serves 6 or more (depending on amount of fruit used).

title: apple enchiladas
directions: Spoon fruit filling evenly down center of each tortilla; sprinkle evenly with cinnamon. Roll up and place, seam side down, in a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.

title: frosty coffee float
directions: Dissolve instant coffee and water in a tall glass.
Add milk, sugar and almond extract.
Stir well and top with a generous scoop of ice cream.
Serves 1.

title: no bake peanut oat cookies
directions: In medium saucepan, mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and butter. Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and oats.
Drop by teaspoon onto foil lined cookie sheet.
Let stand until firm and cold.
Store airtight.

title: "creamsicle" jello
directions: Mix orange juice, water, sugar and tapioca.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Put mixture on stove and add dry vanilla pudding.
Cook until thick.
Add orange Jell-O (dry) and mix until blended.
Let stand until cool.
Fold mixture into Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until hardened.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine in heavy saucepan; add sugar, cocoa and flour. Stir well.
Add eggs.
Stir mixture.
Do not beat.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: roast venison
directions: Season roast with salt, pepper and flour.
Brown on all sides in hot skillet.
Place in crock-pot, add remaining ingredients. Cover and cook 4 to 5 hours on High.
Great for Sunday lunch!
It will be ready when you come in from worship.
Add rice and serve the tomatoes and onions over the rice.
Delicious!

title: grandma's glop
directions: Mix flour, nuts and margarine together and spread in 9x13 pan.
Bake at 375 for 20 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cut up and cook meat with 3 quarts of water and salt for 1 hour.
Add onions, potatoes, carrots, and celery and cook 20 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
Makes 7 quarts.

title: deviled beef patties
directions: Mix well.
Shape into 4 patties.
Broil 3 inches from heat for 5 minutes.
Turn and broil 4 minutes longer or until done.
Serve on toasted hamburger buns.

title: gingered tofu
directions: Drain tofu, rinse, dry on a towel and cut into 1/2 to 1 inch cubes.
Heat oil in wok or skillet until quite hot.
Add tofu.
Fry until lightly golden.
Lower heat.
Add ginger, garlic to taste and a little tamari if desired.
Kids like it like this or set this aside and add it to stir-fried veggies.

title: peanut butter dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter. Beat at low speed with electric mixer until smooth. Store in refrigerator in airtight container.
Serve at room temperature with fresh fruit. Makes 1 3/4 cups dip.

title: oriental cole slaw
directions: Mix top 4 together. Crumble 2 pkg. ramen noodles uncooked. Dressing; oil, sugar, vinegar, and the two beef seasoning packets. Mix in noodles & dressing just before serving.

title: hopping john
directions: Soak peas 1 hour.
Fry salt pork.
Add vegetables and after frying for a few minutes, add them to the peas; together with the seasoning.
Let steam at least 20 minutes until the rice is cooked and water is absorbed.

title: chewy chocolate chip cookies
directions: In large bowl, combine butter, sugars, vanilla and egg; mix well.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix well.	Add chocolate chips. Drop
onto	greased
cookie sheet.	Bake at 350° until golden brown (8 to 10 minutes).

title: pistachio cake
directions: Beat together yellow cake mix, instant pudding, eggs, oil and sour cream; beat well.
Mix sugar, nuts and cinnamon separately. Put half of first mixture in a greased tube pan, then half of sugar mixture.
Add remaining yellow cake mixture and sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple and add jello to melt.
Cool.
When this starts to thicken, stir in buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts.
Chill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and place into sprayed casserole dish.
Spread soup (no water added) over squash.
Salt and pepper to taste. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with corn flakes.
Cook for additional 10 minutes or until corn flakes are golden brown. Should be tender and crisp.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Sift all ingredients together and mix well. Use 6 tablespoons per cup of boiling water.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Mix well the first 6 ingredients.
Form into balls. Refrigerate while melting morsels and wax in microwave, stirring after each minute cooked.
Continue until completely smooth, then dip balls in chocolate and drain on wax paper.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: cabbage slaw(serves 2)
directions: In a medium bowl, shred cabbage and mix with all other ingredients.

title: french toast
directions: Beat all together.
Dip sliced bread in mixture.
Put in frying pan (sprayed with vegetable oil).
Brown, turn and brown on medium-low heat.
This does 8 to 10 slices of bread.
Serve hot with butter and syrup.

title: joyous sunday casserole
directions: Saut sausage, onion and green pepper in skillet. Pour off drippings. Add flour and salt, blending well. Gradually add milk. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Stir in macaroni and 1 cup cheese. Spoon mixture into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes whole with skins on until tender.
Remove skins as soon as possible and cube.
While still warm, beat the oil and vinegar together; pour over potatoes.
Stir gently.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate an hour or so longer to let flavors combine.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in container with lid. Use 2 to 3 teaspoons per mug of hot water or to your taste.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Microwave oleo until melted.
Add marshmallows.
Coat with oleo.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Add cereal; mix well.
Press into greased square baking pan; cool.
Cut into squares.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and chill.

title: broiled peaches
directions: Broil peach halves slowly until golden brown, about 5 minutes. Fill centers with jam and top with Cool Whip.

title: pasta with shrimp
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients until bubbly; stir in shrimp.
Cook until shrimp turn pink.
Serve over cooked pasta (goes well with angel hair pasta).

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix and dissolve water and soda; set aside.
Mix dry ingredients; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs. Add flour mixture and milk alternately.
Add soda water.
Batter may be thin.
Grease cookie sheet, drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.
Test by touch.
Cool.

title: low-fat chicken and pasta casserole
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in 1 tablespoon margarine in nonstick skillet for 5 minutes.
Place chicken in saucepan. Cover with 3 1/2 cups water.
Bring to boil and simmer for 30 minutes.
Let cool and shred chicken.
Save broth.

title: enhanced spaghetti sauce
directions: In large pot, heat spaghetti sauce.
In skillet, brown hamburger and sausage with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Drain and add to sauce.
In same skillet, saute mushrooms, onion and bell pepper in olive oil; stir in ripe olives and sprinkle with oregano; add to sauce.
Stir in can of tomato paste.
Cook on low heat until hot throughout (or let simmer all day for even more flavor).
Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water, adding 1 teaspoon oil to prevent sticking.
Drain.
Serve sauce ladled over cooked spaghetti.

title: sugar and spice cookies
directions: Mix flour and cinnamon.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill. Roll into 1-inch balls and dip in sugar.

title: frozen punch
directions: In large pot, bring sugar and water to a boil.
When dissolved, remove from heat.
Add Jell-O, stirring constantly. (Flavor doesn't matter.
It is just for color.)
Add frozen lemonade and frozen orange juice.
Mix well.
Add can of pineapple juice and almond extract.
Put into 2 (1 gallon) freezer bags and freeze flat.

title: veggi pasta salad
directions: Throw hot pasta on top of thawed defrosted veggies. Toss with salad dressing.

title: fried ice cream
directions: Mix first four ingredients and store overnight.
Take balls of ice cream, roll in crushed cornflakes.
Freeze overnight.
Dip in batter (no bare spots in batter covered balls).
Fry until golden brown.

title: bread pudding with lemon cream sauce
directions: Combine milk and eggs.
Pour over bread cubes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture in an 8-inch baking dish. Place in a shallow pan on oven rack.
Pour hot water around it one-inch deep.

Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 30 minutes (or until a knife, inserted halfway between center and outside edge, comes out clean, and should spring back when lightly pressed). Serve with Lemon Cream Sauce.
Serves 8.

title: ground beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet; drain.
Combine beef, green beans, soup, water, salt and pepper.
Combine mashed potatoes and 1/2 can onions.
Spoon potato mixture in ring around edge of casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mississippi mud trifle
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Cool.
Cut into layers to make 4 rounds.
Prepare pudding as directed.
Put 1 cake layer into dish. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon Kahlua; add a layer of pudding, layer of crushed candy and layer of Cool Whip.
Repeat 3 times, ending with Cool Whip.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and serve.

title: beef, bean and barley stew
directions: Place the quartered potatoes in an even layer in the bottom of a 5 to 5 1/2-quart slow-cooker pot. On top of the potatoes, first evenly layer the garlic, then the chopped onion, beef cubes, barley and cannellini beans. Stir together the beef broth, water, ketchup, paprika, salt and black pepper in a small bowl until the mixture is well blended and smooth. Pour ketchup mixture over the beef mixture in the pot. Cover the slow-cooker pot. Cook on high for 6 hours or on low for 9 to 10 hours until the meat, potatoes and barley are tender and the stew liquid is nicely thickened.
tags: cubes of beef chuck stew meat

title: irish soda bread
directions: In a glass bowl, combine milk and vinegar.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine well the other remaining ingredients.
Stir in milk mixture all at once.
Mix thoroughly but gently.
Don't

title: thai-fried rice
directions: Heat oil in wok or large frypan and fry onion and garlic until golden.
Add the pork and stir-fry until just cooked through.
Make a hole in center or pork and pour in seasoned eggs; scramble.
Toss in rice and stir.
Sprinkle the fish, chili and soy sauces over mixture.
Then add the green pepper, tomato, scallions and shrimp, stirring until mixed.

title: venison jerky
directions: Mix liquid smoke, onion, garlic powder, salt and pepper in large enough bowl to soak meat in overnight.
Place in dehydrator or oven at 150° for 10 to 12 hours, or until desired dryness.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain.
Combine all ingredients in kettle; cook until zucchini is soft.
Place in blender container; process until smooth.
Reheat.
May be frozen.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for Dream Whip.
Set aside.
Mix 1 package of Dream Whip according to directions on package.
Fold into mixture.
Put all into graham cracker pie shell.
Mix another package of Dream Whip.
Put on top of pie. Sprinkle with nuts and coconut.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package but add bananas, soda and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: crescents(cookies)
directions: Mix all together and roll in crescent shape (small).
Bake in slow oven (275°) for about 40 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.

title: sour cream softies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, salt, soda and baking powder; mix with first mixture.
Stir in sour cream a little at a time.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix flour, meal, sugar and eggs.
Stir until creamy.
Drain pineapple juice.
Add pineapple and butter to mixture.
Bake at 300° for about 40 minutes.

title: manicotti with cheese
directions: Cook manicotti according to package directions.
Drain.
Cool in a single layer on wax paper or aluminum foil to prevent manicotti from sticking together.

title: minted fruit salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients, except fruit.
Place fruit in large shallow dish, pour mixture over fruit.
Cover. Chill 3 hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: Trim and peel carrots.
Cut into 4 or 5 pieces.
Peel and cube potatoes.
Heat butter and saute onion briefly.
Add potatoes and carrots to chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Then add thyme and bay leaf.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Discard bay leaf.
Put carrots and potatoes with a little liquid in food processor or blender and puree.
Continue to do this until all the potatoes and carrots are pureed.
Put back in pot and bring pureed vegetables to a boil.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Heat it through. Garnish with fresh dill.

title: orange dessert sauce
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar, mixing until well blended. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve over pound cake or sponge cake slices.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.
This can be used for Passover also.

title: mocha-banana shake
directions: Peel banana.
Break into pieces and put into a blender.
Add milk, 2 scoops ice cream and fudge topping.
Blend at medium speed until smooth.
Pour into cup.
Add last scoop of ice cream.

title: toni's brownies
directions: Grease & flour 9 X 13 pan.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy lemon poppy seed muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Fill greased muffin cups good half full.
Bake 15 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen muffins.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion. Add taco seasoning and beans. Mix.
Pour into casserole dish. Spread cheese over mixture. Mix corn bread as directed on package. Spread over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour until corn bread is brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix white sugar, egg yolks, flour and milk. Let boil. Put 1 cup sugar in iron skillet and let dissolve until brown. Add to other mixture. Cook until thick. Pour into a pastry shell, bake until done. Makes 2 pies.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Allow cheese and sausage to come to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sausage nibblers
directions: Mix and knead ingredients until well blended.
Roll into small balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes in a 325° to 350° oven.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and enjoy.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant in salted water, drain.
Saute onions in butter.
Add eggplant, egg, and cheese. Cook a little more, until cheese is melted.
Add a little bread crumbs, then add seasoned bread crumbs on top, then dot with butter.
Bake at 350° in a pan for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole ii
directions: In a bowl combine all ingredients well; add salt and pepper to taste.
Transfer to 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: fantasy squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan in oven until melted.
Sprinkle vanilla wafer crumbs evenly over margarine.
Sprinkle coconut and candies over crumbs.
Pour milk over candies.
Mix remaining ingredients except 1 cup candies in medium bowl.
Stir in candies.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 1-inch apart onto candies in pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool squares completely before cutting.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Makes 48.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger.
Add sauces, onions, beans, half of the corn chips (lightly crushed) and half of the Cheddar cheese.
Pour into a large casserole and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pea soup
directions: Boil pork chop in seasoned water for 20 minutes.
When ready to serve, beat 1 egg with green onion.
Add to soup and serve.

title: quick country corn cakes
directions: Blend corn and egg.
Add pancake mix.
Fry in 1/2-inch hot shortening until golden brown. Turn and brown other side.

title: chinese spareribs
directions: In a saucepan, combine stock and catsup.
Heat slowly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Marinate ribs for 3 hours or longer in sauce.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place ribs on rack in a roasting pan.
Roast for 1 hour, basting frequently with sauce.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soups and water together.
Add Cheez Whiz and mix well. Add onion, rice and broccoli.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hot cereal mix
directions: Put all ingredients into a storage container with a lid (Tupperware is nice).
Shake well.
Store in a kitchen cupboard.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together.
Add zucchini, eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Combine next 5 ingredients in a small bowl, blending well.
Mix with rest of mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Contains 221 calories and 11.9 fat.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Heat soup until hot and add all ingredients.
Pour over carrots.
Refrigerate for at least 24 hours.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch with sugar; add water and jello.
Cook until thick.
Pour over strawberries in a baked crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chunky corn chowder
directions: Cook potatoes in small amount of water.
Saute onion and pepper in 1/2 stick margarine.
Add creamed corn, Niblets Mexicorn and mushroom soup.
Mix all ingredients and heat well.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion and pepper; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Place cheese on top.
Cover with aluminum foil. Bake for 35 minutes at 325°.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes.

title: prune bread
directions: Mix all together; put in greased bread pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: crab meat spread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and spread in a 1/8-inch thick circle on platter.
Leave room around circle for crackers.

title: easy meatballs and sauce
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, salt, pepper, oats, milk and eggs. Shape in small balls.
Place in cake pan.
Punch holes in balls. Mix ketchup, brown sugar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Place cucumbers, onions and bell peppers in dishpan and cover with ice.
Heat sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Let cool. Pour over iced cucumbers.
Mix together.
Put in freezer bags and freeze.
Serve half frozen.

title: pineapple sauce cake or applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix soda with fruit.
Sift dry ingredients 3 times.
Add each alternately, beating after each.

title: chicken thighs with tarragon sauce
directions: In a heavy saucepan, place the chicken thighs, one layer thick.
In a heavy saucepan, melt the butter.
Add the onions and cook until translucent.
Add the flour, stirring until very thick. Gradually add the cream and stock, stirring to maintain a thick sauce consistency.
Add the next five ingredients.

title: seasoned shrimp with noodles
directions: Peel and rinse shrimp.
Chop green onions to 1/4-inch each. In a skillet, heat oil on high.
Add garlic and ginger; fry until brown.
Add shrimp; fry until they begin to turn pink.
Add chili powder, coriander and sesame oil.
Add mushrooms, green onions and salt to taste.
Mix with cooked noodles until spices are blended. Serve with lemon wedges.

title: pork chops with quick tomato sauce(makes 4 to 6)
directions: Dredge breaded pork chops with seasoned flour.
Heat oil; add chops and brown.
Remove; add mushrooms.
Cook until tender.
Pour chicken broth, tomato paste, onion, green pepper and garlic in blender or food processor until well blended (no lumps).
Pour half of mixture in bottom of casserole dish; add chops and mushrooms, then add remainder of tomato mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes; uncover and bake 20 minutes.

title: bud's chili
directions: Melt oil in large skillet and brown onion, green pepper and beef.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir and cook over low heat 1 1/2 hours.
(Serves 4 to 6.)

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding and undrained pineapple.
Add other ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: shrimp elegant
directions: Clean and peel shrimp.
Heat safflower oil until hot.
Add shrimp and cook 1 minute on each side; remove.
Add to skillet the shallots and tarragon; saute a few seconds.
Add water and boil down.
Add heavy cream and reduce heat.
Add butter and melt. Add mustard.
(Do not allow to boil after mustard is added.)
Remove from heat. Add salt and pepper.
To serve, pour a little sauce onto each plate, then arrange shrimp in a nice design on top of each plate of sauce.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Sprinkle sugar on vegetables and let stand. Bring to boil the remaining ingredients; pour over vegetables and let stand 1 1/2 hours. Put into containers and freeze.

title: savory chipper loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Blend together.
Shape into loaf and bake in shallow pan, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hearty stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In 9-inch baking dish, arrange peppers; set aside. In large bowl, combine meat sauce, 1/2 cup cheese and uncooked rice. Evenly stuff peppers with sauce mixture. Pour water in dish, then cover with aluminum foil. Bake 50 minutes or until peppers are tender. Remove foil and top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese. Bake 5 minutes or until cheese is melted. Makes 4 servings. Prep time: 15 minutes.

title: sauce for fish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fish in baking dish.
Spread sauce over fish and bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chow mein
directions: Boil chicken.
Cool and pick off bones.
Cut up celery and onions.
Steam in separate pans until tender.
(Drain off water.) Drain bean sprouts.
Add celery, onions, bean sprouts and chicken. Mix all together.
Heat; do not cook.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook rice.
Serve over rice or chow mein noodles.

title: blueberry banana cream cheese pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
In crusts, layer each with sliced bananas.
Pour 1/2 of creamed mixture in each crust.
Top with blueberry pie filling (1/2 can on each).
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry refresher
directions: Mix in blender, then add three qt. Ginger Ale.
Makes one gallon.

title: tropical pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray loaf pan and set aside. In a 2-quart bowl, combine cake mix, milk, banana and eggs; mix well. Stir in coconut. Pour into loaf pan. Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until done. Cool in pan on wire rack for 15 minutes. Loosen edges with knife and remove from pan. Cool completely. Cut cake into 12 slices. Top with kiwifruit, ice cream and preserves.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Pour boiling water over oatmeal. Cool until warm.
Add butter, molasses and yeast mix.
Blend in eggs.
Gradually mix in flour, adding enough to make a smooth dough.
Knead for 10 minutes on floured board.
Place in greased bowl; cover and let rise until double in size.
Punch down.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Place into greased loaf pans.
Paint top with melted butter and sprinkle with oatmeal.
Cover and let rise to double.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Serves 20 slices.

title: meat loaf
directions: Lightly mix the first seven ingredients and form in loaf pan. Start baking at 350°.

title: crescent chicken
directions: Cook chicken; cut into bite size pieces.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture onto 2 crescent rolls (rectangular shaped).
Pinch up all 4 corners.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: caramel corn
directions: Place corn puffs into a greased roaster pan. Set aside.
In a saucepan, add margarine, brown sugar and Karo syrup.
Boil for 5 minutes at medium heat.
Remove from heat and add salt, vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over corn puffs.
Bake in a 250° oven for 1/2 hour, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: In a large skillet, cook the bacon until crisp; drain (reserve 3 teaspoons drippings).
Crumble bacon in a large bowl; toss bacon with potatoes and onion.
Set aside.
Combine flour, sugar, water, vinegar, salt and pepper; stir into skillet.
Cook until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in cream; pour over potato mixture.
Toss gently to coat.
Serve warm.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients. Chill dough about 1 hour and keep chilled while making.
Use cookie press.
Bake in 350° oven until firm on top, about 10 or 12 minutes.

title: meal in a pan
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and heat. Serve immediately.
