title: low-fat taco dip
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Soften cream cheese and spread into pan.
Spread can of chili beans over cream cheese. Add chili peppers over beans.
Layer black olives, then green onions, then cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate satin glaze
directions: Combine sugar and water in a small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Immediately add mini chocolate chips, stirring until melted.
Continue stirring until glaze is desired consistency.
Makes about 1/2 cup of glaze.

title: van's mexican casserole
directions: In saucepan, melt cheese along with Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
To beef, add cheese mixture, bean and soup.
Stir.
In baking dish, cover bottom with chips.
Pour mixture over chips.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with sour cream, grated cheese, lettuce, black olives and green onions, if you like.

title: spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and garlic salt in
iron frying pan. Put into crock-pot, the hamburger combination plus the remaining ingredients.
Put in crock-pot in the morning.
Later in the day, cook spaghetti and add to pot with as much grated cheese as you like.
Cook on low until supper time.
Feel free to add more salt or pepper to taste.
Serve with hot rolls, tossed salad and iced tea.

title: sour cream pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper; dredge with flour. Brown in margarine.
Insert a clove in each pork chop and place in baking dish.
In same pan where pork chops were browned, put sugar, water, sour cream, bay leaf and vinegar.
Bring to boil; pour over chops.
Tightly cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: sherry d's spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and while still warm, add 1/2 bottle of dressing.
Add Good Seasons; chop up vegetables and stir into spaghetti.
Add remaining bottle of dressing.
Toss; sprinkle in Parmesan cheese.

title: baked hot dogs
directions: Take a bun and split open. Spread with margarine. Then spread with mustard and add slice of cheese. Place hot dog on bun and add 1 teaspoon relish. Wrap each bun in aluminum foil and bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Melt butter in glass pie plate in 350° oven.
Add crushed crackers and mix well.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour sauteed onions over cracker crumbs. Beat eggs and add milk; pour over onions.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes or until done.

title: onion beef(makes 4 or 5 servings)
directions: *Thaw beef partially, it will be easier to slice that way.

title: dirt cups
directions: You will also need 8 to 10 (7 ounce) paper or plastic cups.

title: chili con carne
directions: Saute chopped onion in bacon drippings or butter.
Then add ground beef and saute until well done.
Add tomato soup, kidney beans, chili powder and salt.
Cover and cook slowly for 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: disgustingly delicious brownies
directions: Smear the inside of 8 x 9-inch baking pan with shortening. Add melted butter.
Mix cocoa and sugar together, then stir in melted butter.
Add eggs and vanilla and stir again.
Now add flour and salt and mix until smooth.
Spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Let cool before cutting.
(That's the hard part.)

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook and drain the spaghetti. Cook the chicken breast and tear apart. Put the spaghetti and chicken in a large baking dish. Add the soups and rotel. Put the velveeta in a microwave safe bowl and melt the cheese. Mix with the other ingredients and cook until hot and bubbly. This is delicious served with a salad and five cheese garlic bread.

title: sugar-free cinnamon buns
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Sprinkle nuts and raisins on bottom of pan.
Put cinnamon in bag with rolls and shake to cover each roll; arrange over nuts and raisins.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over dough.
Drizzle syrup and margarine over all. Cover with damp towel.
Let set 5 to 6 hours.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Invert pan onto serving plate.

title: roast leg of lamb
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Make incisions in the meat with a sharp knife and fill with garlic pieces.
Make incisions about every 3 inches or so all over the meat.
Rub meat with lemon juice; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Wrap in foil; place in oven roaster.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes per pound.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Empty potato slices and packet of seasoned sauce mix into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Heat tomatoes, water and oregano to boiling; stir into potatoes.
Arrange pepperoni on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes. Yields four servings.

title: powdered hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large container.
Store in airtight container.
Use 1/3 cup powder to 1 cup water.

title: cheese ball
directions: In large bowl of mixer, combine cheeses, Worcestershire sauce, cayenne pepper and salt.
Cream until well blended and smooth. Spoon into a piece of wax paper or plastic wrap and refrigerate. In about 15 minutes, mold into a ball while in paper or plastic wrap.
Chill.
To serve, roll in chopped parsley or chopped nuts. Serve with apple wedges and crackers.

title: cathren's cucumbers
directions: Slice all vegetables very thin.
Sprinkle 1 big tablespoon of salt over vegetables.
Set aside 1 or 2 hours.
Drain off water. Mix 3/4 cup of sugar, vinegar and celery seed and pour over vegetables; refrigerate before eating.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until boiling.
Drain.
Add both eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Mix ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender and remove skin and bone.
Chop chicken.
Set aside.
Chop onions and cook slowly in oil or oleo. Do not brown!
When onion is tender, add celery soup and let come to a boil.
Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain.
Use baking dish and add layer of macaroni, a layer of cheese, then a layer of chicken.
Then pour the onion and celery soup mixture over this and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in an oven for about 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Mix flour, eggs, milk, sugar and vanilla.
Bring to a boil and cook until thickens.
(Stir at all times.)
Remove from heat and add butter and pineapple.
Pour over graham crackers.

title: fall cake
directions: Peel and dice apples enough for 4 cups.
Mix with sugar; let stand 1 hour.
Add eggs beaten in salad oil and vanilla.
Add flour sifted with salt and baking soda.
Add walnuts. Mix well, but do not beat hard.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 325° for 45 minutes in Bundt pan.

title: artichoke spinach salad
directions: For dressing, whisk olive oil with vinegar, lemon juice, mustard, sugar, dill and pepper.
In a large bowl, combine spinach, cabbage, artichoke hearts, ham and cheese.
Pour dressing over salad.
Toss gently.
Yields 4 servings.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Saute bacon drippings, sugar, salt and vinegar.
Dice onions and radishes.
Pour over leaf lettuce (garden lettuce).

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and butter and cream until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour to creamed mixture.
Add milk and beat well.
Stir in flavorings.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion in Dutch oven on stove.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients except Fritos.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over Fritos.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Mix
together and put in buttered dish.
Set in refrigerator overnight.	Next
day,
add 1/2 cup milk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Place all ingredients except sausage and rice in saucepan. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to a simmer, cover and cook for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add sausage to red beans the last 30 minutes of cooking time. Serve over rice.

title: apple torte
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, oil and vanilla.
Slice 6 apples thin and fold into batter.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet-n-sour salad
directions: Mix together in a bowl.
Pour 1 cup sugar on top.
Do not stir.
Refrigerate.
Stir sugar into salad before serving.
Drain if you like.

title: mexican breakfast
directions: Peel and
dice potatoes.
Fry separately.
Fry sausage, onion and green
pepper.	Add
eggs
and cheese.	Add potatoes and diced tortillas.
Make sure tomatoes are heated thoroughly.
Put 1 large spoonful in each tortilla.
Wrap and serve.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown ground beef with garlic and green pepper.
Strain fat off.
Add spices.
Add beans and water; stir well.
Add tomato paste.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve on hot dogs.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Blend shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt into the first mixture.
Mix well, then shape into small walnut size balls.
Roll balls in the cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in food processor or blender; pulse the motor to make a homogeneous sauce which is not as fine as a puree. Yields 2 1/2 cups for 8 servings of pasta.

title: marie's lemon pie
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Add the hot water.
Cook until clear, stirring to prevent sticking.
Add the egg yolks, juice from the lemon and margarine.
Cook until done.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: pumpkin roll cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts and bake in jelly roll pan at 375° for 15 minutes.
Roll cake up in towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Let cool and add filling.

title: beef fiesta
directions: Brown meat over high heat in skillet, leaving meat in coarse chunks.
Add onion and reduce heat and cook until onion is tender, but not browned.
Add seasonings, tomatoes, corn and bouillon.
Bring to a boil.
Add green peppers and boil again. Stir in rice and remove from heat.
Cover.
Let stand 5 minutes. Fluff with fork.
Serves 6.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream together first three ingredients, then add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into loaf pan (greased).
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: salad dressing *
directions: Whisk together mustard, vinegar, cumin, Tabasco, salt and pepper.
Slowly add the oil while whisking vigorously.
Serves 4.

title: emerald dressing(for seafood or green salad)
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend on high for 2 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Speed up the preparation time by cooking the potatoes in your microwave oven.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken for 20 minutes, cool and debone; cook spaghetti in chicken broth and then drain.
In a large pan add cubed Velveeta cheese, water chestnuts, mushrooms, cream of mushroom soup, broccoli and condensed milk.
After all is mixed together, add spaghetti and chicken to mixture and mix well.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fried cheese meltaways
directions: Heat 2-inches of oil in deep-fat fryer or saucepan to 375°. Beat biscuit mix, milk and egg with hand beater until smooth. Coat cheese cubes lightly with baking mix.
Insert a round wooden pick in each cheese cube.
Dip into batter, covering cheese completely.
Fry several cubes at a time, turning carefully, until golden brown, 1 to 2 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Makes about 45 appetizers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine; add broccoli and heat until thawed. Cook rice according to package directions.
Combine all ingredients in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
May sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sour green beans
directions: Put cans of beans, including juice, in saucepan and warm.
Fry bacon in a skillet until crisp.
Pour vinegar and sugar in skillet and heat until clear and sugar is dissolved.
Pour all in the saucepan; keep warm until ready to serve.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil and egg whites.
Add buttermilk and vanilla, mixing well.
Sift flour, soda and salt; add to the above.
Fold in rhubarb and nuts.
Bake in 2 loaf pans that have been sprayed with Pam, lightly floured.
Mix 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle over bread mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour (until done).

title: seafood pasta
directions: Whip butter or soft margarine until fluffy.
Season with garlic, lemon juice, dill and pepper.
Heat sherry in skillet; cook scallops in it, then add lobster meat until heated.
Add cream and heat until sauce thickens.
Add butter and heat until frothy. Serve over angel hair pasta or mix pasta and sauce in large serving dish.

title: pull apart bread
directions: Dissolve yeast with water. Add eggs, sugar and then flour, a little at a time. Let rise 2 hours. Then roll, cut out in 2-inch diameter circles and dip pieces in melted oleo and put in Bundt pan. Let rise. Bake at 300° for 1/2 hour or until done. Turn out and break the pieces off.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour slowly.
Mix until smooth.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on cookie sheet.
Press with glass coated with sugar.
Bake at 300° to 325° until brown around edges.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Heat 6 cups water in a large pan.
When water comes to a rolling boil, put peppers in 2 at a time.
Boil for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: elegant carrots
directions: Pare 6 carrots into julienne strips or thinly sliced crinkle slices.
Boil 1/2 cup water and 1 teaspoon chicken bouillon or 1 cube.
Add carrots; cover and cook for 2 to 3 minutes or until cooked to your liking.
Transfer into casserole dish.

title: banana salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and instant pudding mix until well blended by hand.
Add sliced bananas and walnuts and mix well.
Sprinkle extra walnuts on top of salad.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in butter. Put everything in kettle, add milk to desired thickness. Add mushrooms and onions, cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until hot.

title: blueberry salad
directions: 1st Layer:
Six ounce package of
raspberry jello, 2 cups boiling water and 2 cups cold water.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: so our time together

title: baked "fries"
directions: Lightly spray a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking sheet with nonstick coating. Cut potatoes lengthwise into thin wedges. Place in a plastic bag. Spray wedges with nonstick coating. Combine cheese, paprika and pepper. Add to bag; close bag and shake to coat potatoes with seasonings. Arrange potatoes in a single layer on baking sheet. Bake in 425° oven for 30 minutes or until crisp and fork-tender, turning once. Season with salt. Makes 4 servings. Contains 155 cal., 3 g total fat (1 g saturated fat).

title: low-fat orange creamsicle pie
directions: In large bowl, with electric mixer on medium speed, blend yogurt and orange juice concentrate.
Spread into prepared crust. Freeze until firm.
Before serving, garnish.
Makes 8 servings.

title: microwave peanut patties
directions: Cook sugar, water, Karo and peanuts in a microwave bowl.
Cook 4 minutes on High, stir cook 8 more minutes on High, remove from microwave.
Add salt, butter, vanilla and 3 or 4 drops food color. Stir until mixture looks glazy, about 3 minutes.
Drop by spoon on buttered sheet of foil quickly, before mixture becomes too hard.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Combine all.
Layer over unbaked cake mixture.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: bacon-cheddar potato topping
directions: In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, cheese and bacon.
Serve over baked potatoes.

title: baked hawaiian beans
directions: Brown bacon first; drain.
Combine all above ingredients. Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: taco stew
directions: Brown beef, drain and rinse with hot water to remove excess fat.
Combine all ingredients except tortilla chips and cheese, in a Dutch oven.
Simmer on low.
To serve, crumble tortilla chips in a serving bowl and cover with a generous helping of stew. Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: rhubarb roll
directions: Pour boiling water over rhubarb.
Let stand 5 minutes; drain well.
Combine the sugar with the water.
Boil 5 minutes.
Prepare biscuit mix. Roll dough 1/2-inch thick.
Spread with softened butter. Sprinkle with the 1/2 cup sugar, then sprinkle with rhubarb. Sprinkle red hot cinnamons on top.
Roll as for jelly roll. Cut in 1-inch slices.
Place slices in an 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Pour boiling syrup over rolls. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Absolutely delicious!

title: brownies
directions: Melt together over hot water the chocolate and shortening. Beat in sugar and eggs.
Sift together and beat in flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in nuts.
Spread in well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until top has dull color.
A slight imprint will be left when top is touched lightly with finger.
Cool slightly, then cut into squares.
Makes 16 (2-inch) squares.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In double boiler heat 1/4 stick butter and 3/4 cup sugar. Turn heat on high so that the water in the bottom boiler comes to a boil.
In blender, blend 1/2 cup milk, egg and salt.
Mix well. Add cornstarch.
Microwave 2 cups milk to boiling stage.
Add blender mixture and hot milk to mixture in pan.
Stir constantly until thick.
Add shredded coconut and extract.
Stir and pour into baked 10-inch pie shell.

title: peppy pizza pasta
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain.
In bowl, combine all ingredients except cheese.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: diabetic bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, mix cereal, flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Add eggs, buttermilk and Butter Buds and mix well.
Spray muffin tins with nonstick coating agent.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full and bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: frozen pudding sandwiches
directions: Add milk to peanut butter and beat until smooth. Add pudding mix and beat slowly until well blended.
Let stand 15 minutes. Spread filling 1/2-inch thick on 12 of the graham crackers. Top with remaining 12 graham crackers and wrap in Saran Wrap.
Freeze until firm (about 3 hours).

title: chess cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Melt oleo and both sugars; cream together.
Add egg yellows, vanilla and dry ingredients and mix well.
Fold in egg whites, beaten stiff.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Chop beef finely; place in bottom of casserole dish.
Wrap each chicken piece with half of bacon slice.
Place each piece on its own bed of chipped beef.

title: golden cream soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine potatoes, water, celery, carrots, onion, parsley, bouillon cube and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
You may need to add more water so the vegetables won't stick to the bottom of the pan.
Gradually add milk to the flour, mixing until well blended.
Add milk mixture to vegetables; cook until thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: joggin' in a jug
directions: Mix all and serve 1 to 2 ounces daily.

title: party green beans
directions: Cook and drain beans.
Make white sauce by melting margarine, adding flour, salt, pepper and sugar and forming a paste.
Stir in sour cream and grated onion.

Add green beans to white sauce. Place half of beans in greased 2-quart casserole; layer half of Swiss and Cheddar cheese and place remaining beans on top of cheese, then layer other half of cheeses on top of beans. Sprinkle crushed cornflakes on top of cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix sour cream, cheese, onion, soup and 1/2 stick butter (melted).
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle corn flake crumbs over top and drizzle with remaining 1/2 stick of melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Cut up vegetables.
Add to kraut.
Bring to a boil the sugar, vinegar, oil, water and celery seed.
Pour over vegetables. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Keeps well for a week.

title: apple pie in paper bag
directions: Pare, core and slice apples (about 7 cups) into a bowl.
Make filling with sugar, flour, nutmeg and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Toss to coat well.
Spoon into pastry shell.
Drizzle with lemon juice.

title: breakfast french toast
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add sugar and cinnamon; stir.
Put bread over this.
Beat eggs; add milk.
Stir.
Pour over bread; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Turn bread over; bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tennessee river mud pie
directions: Put a can of Eagle Brand or Carnation condensed milk in deep saucepan filled
with
water (be sure can is covered with water all the time).
Bring water to a boil, then simmer for 2 1/2 hours.
Be sure
to
watch and be sure water covers it all the time.
Take out
of water and let cool, then open can.
It will be caramelized.
Spoon
into
baked
plain pie shell or a graham cracker
crust.
Let
cool
completely, then cover with Cool Whip or
whipped
cream.
Refrigerate.
(Very
rich
and delicious.)

title: orange-zucchini squares(diabetic)
directions: When using frozen zucchini, drain juice.

title: tampa's slaw
directions: Mix onions, slaw, noodles, sunflower seeds and almonds in bowl.
In smaller bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over slaw mixture just before serving to keep noodles crunchy.

title: creamed lobster
directions: *You may use imitation crab meat or shrimp, if desired.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and season to taste.
Add tomato paste and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
In 9 x 13 pan, alternate layers of sauce, noodles and cheese, beginning and ending with sauce. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly before serving.

title: alabama chicken spaghetti
directions: Place han in a large pot; cover with cold water.
Add a little salt and cook until tender, covered; reserve the broth.

title: special tea
directions: Combine
water,
sugar,
cloves and cinnamon in 2 quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add orange juice and tea.
Remove from heat.
Steep
for 3 to 5 minutes.
Strain into tea pot to serve.

title: tuna salad sandwich filling
directions: Mix all ingredients; refrigerate until serving time.
Makes 1 1/4 cups filling (3 or 4 sandwiches).

title: banana punch(u. s. a.)
directions: Put ingredients through a blender and freeze.
When gushy or slushy, add 2 or 3 quarts ginger ale.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients, and pour in a large baking dish. Mix crushed cornflakes with softened butter and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45
minutes.

title: texas shrimp dip
directions: Combine 1 cup cooked and chopped shrimp, 1 package softened cream cheese, 1/4 cup each chopped onion, stuffed olives, mayonnaise, 1/4 teaspoon each salt and white pepper.
Garnish with cooked shrimp.
Recipe makes about 2 cups dip.

title: broccoli strata
directions: Combine eggs and milk in a large bowl.
Stir in stuffing mix, 1 1/2 cups of the cheese, broccoli, lemon rind and nutmeg.
Pour into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is set.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add Salad Supreme seasoning to taste.
Make the night before serving.

title: creamy chicken breasts
directions: Saute breasts in margarine plus Italian salad dressing.
Place in casserole and top with condensed mushroom soup and undiluted cream cheese and chives.
Mix cream cheese and soup together. Bake at 350° until done.
With bones, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine according to directions on box.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Pour into large bowl.
Add vegetables as desired. Mix in dressing and spice.
Let stand in refrigerator for several hours (overnight is better).

title: chicken with lemon and olives
directions: Heat oil in a frying pan over medium heat.
Brown chicken on both sides; remove.
Add garlic and chopped green onions; saute. Add water.
Return chicken to pan; salt and pepper to taste. Cover and cook over low heat for 20 to 25 minutes until chicken is no longer pink.
Remove chicken again.
Boil pan juices 2 to 3 minutes until slightly thickened.
Stir in lemon juice and olives. Pour over the chicken.
Serves 4.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pineapple into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour pie filling over pineapple.
Crumble cake mix over this.
Cut butter into pats and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pie crust (2 pies)
directions: Sift together salt and flour; cut in shortening.
Stir in water, a little at a time, until flour is moistened.
Dough is soft.
Do not knead, squeeze into balls.
Handles better if chilled.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Bring last 4 ingredients to a boil and pour over remaining ingredients.
Let stand 1 1/2 hours.
Package and freeze.

title: gorgonzola-sauced pasta
directions: Melt butter; add Blue cheese.
Stir in light cream, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Toss cheese with pasta until coated.
Serve immediately.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Heat to scalding the milk.
Pour over the bread crumbs.
Cool and add the melted butter, sugar, eggs, salt and raisins.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until silver knife inserted in pudding comes out clean. Serve warm with or without sauce or cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter pancakes
directions: Mix all together and cook.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all and pour in a 2-quart baking dish.

title: cranberry crumble coffee cake
directions: Sprinkle almonds over bottom of greased 9-inch spring form pan; set aside.
Cream sugar, butter and vanilla; beat on medium speed for 1-2 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine dry ingredients and add to batter, alternately with sour cream.
Mix well.
Spread 3 cups over almonds,
spoon cranberry sauce over batter and top with remaining batter.
For topping, combine flour, sugar, almonds and vanilla. Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over batter and bake at 350 degrees for 70-75 minutes or until wooden pick inserted near middle comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack for 15 minutes; remove sides of pan.
Serve warm.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; stir well.
Store mix in an airtight container at room temperature.

title: banana bread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine and blend sugar and margarine.
Then add 1 egg at a time and blend.
In a separate bowl, blend dry ingredients.
Now blend all ingredients in one bowl and add bananas.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured bread pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until fork or toothpick comes out clean or until center springs back.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick butter and 2 cups cracker crumbs.
Beat egg and rest of butter and powdered sugar for 2 to 4 minutes with mixer. Spread over crumbs and put 1 layer of bananas, then pineapple, Cool Whip, nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: aspirin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Turn down television.
Measure flour. Answer telephone.
Separate eggs.
Go look for Christie!
Cream butter and sugar.
Get Christie's hand out of flour.
Answer doorbell.
Add eggs and flour.
Hunt Grandpa's cap.
Grease pan. Salesman at door.
Return; pan filled with salt.
Spank Christie. Call bakery.
Take aspirins.

title: chili mac
directions: Cook beef, pepper and onion until brown.
Mix salt, pepper, chili powder, sugar, vinegar and water.
Stir into meat mixture, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add macaroni; mix well, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: clam patties
directions: Use canned or fresh clams.
Chop, but do not make small pieces. Beat eggs and milk for 1 minute.
Add garlic, oregano, parsley, salt, pepper and cheese to egg mixture and set aside.
Next put oil in frying pan and heat.
Mix flour and bread crumbs in bowl.
Place clams in and coat with crumb mixture.
Spoon this into the egg mixture and place in oil by spoonfuls (large tablespoon).
Fry on each side about 1 minute.
Clam patties should be golden brown on both sides.
Serve on crusty roll or bread.

title: rice and vegetables casserole
directions: Brown rice lightly in heated shortening or pan drippings, stirring frequently, to brown evenly.
Arrange carrots and celery in bottom of a 2-quart casserole.
Cover with rice, then beans and finally onions.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour water over rice and vegetables and cover.
Bake in moderate oven about 1 hour or until rice and vegetables are tender.
Makes 6 servings.
You may also add tuna or chicken to this dish if you wish a meat.

title: purple plum crunch
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, sugar and egg.
Put plums in bottom of ungreased 2-quart baking dish and crumble flour mixture on top. Mix brown sugar, 3 tablespoons flour and cinnamon and sprinkle all over.
Melt margarine and pour over all.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
You may also use larger red plums, bing cherries, peaches or apples in place of plums.

title: angel's delight
directions: Grease and flour muffin pans.
Put a little flour over nuts and dates.
Stir all together (except whipped cream).
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.
Remove from pan immediately.
Cool; break up in pieces. Mix in 1 pint whipped cream.
Put in sherbet dish and place a cherry on top.

title: "good for you"
directions: Blend all ingredients together, sprinkle more cinnamon on top of another blop of Cool Whip.
This makes for a good muscle tone builder with fiber "shake."
My Mother and I developed this milk shake for me when I was about 8 years old so I could gain a little weight and get extra fiber in my diet because I don't eat green vegetables.

title: stir-fry chicken and broccoli
directions: In a large frying pan or wok, heat oil over medium high heat. Add the chicken cubes and stir-fry 3 minutes, until chicken becomes opaque.
Remove with slotted spoon and set aside.
Add broccoli, fry for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add mushrooms, scallions, soy sauce, ginger and sesame oil.
Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add cornstarch, dissolved in water, and chicken.
Cook until heated through and sauce has thickened.
Serve over rice or angel hair pasta.
Serves 4.
Preparation time 20 minutes.
Cooking time 20 minutes.

title: sam's stuff (mush)
directions: Mix together cornmeal and cold water.
Add cornmeal mixture to salt and boiling water.
Stir in slowly over low heat.
Cook and stir.
Lower heat to very low; cover and cook about 15 minutes.

title: carol's marinade for tri-tips roast
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Pour over tri-tip roast or London broil.
Let sit in refrigerator for 2 to 3 days, then cook.

title: vegetable ball
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Make ball and roll in sunflower seeds or chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Dredge chicken in flour, then dip in egg whites until coated. Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Roll chicken in bread mixture until completely covered. Saute onions and garlic in oil until tender. Add chicken and cook 5 minutes on each side. Transfer to baking pan and top with spaghetti sauce and 1 slice of Mozzarella cheese per chicken. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until well done.

title: ranch stew
directions: Brown beef and onion until lightly brown. Drain corn, beans and tomatoes and add the liquid to the meat. Cook until liquid is reduced in half. Add corn, beans, tomatoes, chili powder and salt. Mix and heat thoroughly. Stir occasionally. Makes 6 servings.

title: corn and sausage dish
directions: Beat 4	eggs
well.
Blend
corn into eggs. Add crumbs. Break sausage
into chunks and add. Add seasoning (optional). Pour into oiled
casserole.
Top with catsup.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let set for 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, soda, salt and fruit cocktail. Beat eggs and add to mixture; beat with mixture.
Bake in layers or tube pan.

title: broccoli with bacon
directions: Remove broccoli leaves and cut off tough ends of stalks; discard.
Wash broccoli and cut into spears.
Cook in a small amount of boiling water 6 to 8 minutes or just until tender; drain.
Place in a serving dish; keep warm.
Cook bacon in a skillet until crisp.
Add green onions.
Cook until tender. Remove from skillet.
Add chopped walnuts.
Stir together and pour over broccoli.

title: green tomato pie
directions: In bowl, combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Add tomatoes and vinegar; toss to mix.
Line pie plate with bottom crust.
Add filling and dot with butter.
Top with lattice crust. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until tomatoes are tender.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and beat by hand. Sift flour, cocoa and salt; add to creamed mixture. Mix well. Add vanilla. Pour into a greased and floured oblong pan. Bake at 300° for 35 minutes. Remove from oven and pour desired amount of marshmallows over top; return to oven for 10 minutes at 350°. Cool cake 1 hour before icing.

title: dietetic cake
directions: Combine raisins, water and 1 packet sweetener in small saucepan.
Simmer over medium heat until all water is absorbed. In blender, combine oil, apple, applesauce, raisins, prunes, eggs, cinnamon, allspice, vanilla and 8 packets sweetener.
Blend well. In small bowl, combine baking soda, salt and flour.
Add flour mixture to batter.
Mix well.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan coated with vegetable spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake is light brown.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
After in pan, sprinkle with brown sugar and top with a few walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Wash and quarter
tomatoes and unpeeled apples.
Remove cores. Cut off and
discard
ends
of lemons, then quarter or slice and remove seeds.
Chop tomatoes, apples and lemons.
In a 6 to 8 quart
kettle,
combine
tomatoes,
apples,
lemons, butter, raisins and sugar.
Bring
to a boil over medium heat, stirring. Add salt
and
spices.
Simmer gently uncovered for about 1 hour or
until
thick
and
liquid
is absorbed.
Stir often.
Reduce heat,
if necessary, to prevent sticking.
Boil in hot water bath for 15 minutes.

title: sherry's rolls(easy no knead dough)
directions: Mix together ingredients in large bowl, cover with plastic wrap.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Dough should have risen by morning.
Take plastic wrap off and spoon dough into muffin pans, spray with Pam (dough will be sticky).
Let rise 3 hours in muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Best never fail recipe you'll ever find!

title: potato buns
directions: Soften yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Measure sugar, shortening, salt and instant potatoes into a large bowl.
Add hot milk; stir to melt shortening.
Beat in eggs and 1 cup flour.
Mix in yeast and enough flour to make a soft dough.
Shape into ball and sit in warm place for 1 hour.
Knead on floured board and roll about 3/8-inch and make into desired shapes.
Let rise again to desired heights.
Bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: hot sweet mustard sauce
directions: Mix mustard with a little water; allow to stand.
Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt with remainder of water until smooth. Add vinegar.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Bring to low boil; remove from heat.
Cool.
Add mustard; mix well.

title: creamy taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion over medium heat until browned; drain well.
Add the other ingredients.
Mix well.
Add sour cream and diced Velveeta cheese. Put this all in a crock-pot and simmer for a couple of hours or longer.
Stir occasionally so the cheese and sour cream are melted.
Serve hot over Fritos.

title: "leftover roast" casserole
directions: Make the enchilada sauce but make only half its recipe.
In a mixing bowl, mix 1 1/2 cups of sour cream with the grated cheese that's already been grated into the mixing bowl.
Add chopped green chilies and chopped onion.
(This mixture will be about the consistency of a pudding.) Grease and "flour" the bottom of a baking dish.
Spread noncrushed Doritos just as they came from the sack on the bottom of baking dish.
Then place your chopped leftover roast scattered on the Doritos.
Spread the "mixture" you've already made on top of this.
Now another layer of noncrushed Doritos.
Lastly, pour enchilada sauce over all of the above layers.
Bake approximately 25 minutes at 325°.
(This is easier than it looks; a tasty way to use leftover roast.)

title: chocolate sauerkraut cake
directions: *Chop well with a sharp knife.

title: gumbo
directions: Saute chopped onions, pepper and garlic (optional). In stew pot, heat diced tomatoes over medium heat. Add vegetables. Brown kielbasa or Italian sausage cut into 1-inch cubes, then add to the stew. Deglaze saute pan with red wine and add to stew pot. Add marinated, browned beef tips with sauce (reference other recipe). Cook rice per package directions. Add to gumbo. Simmer over low heat for 1 hour. Add salt and pepper to taste. If desired, add hot sauce. If necessary, thicken with cornstarch.

title: pineapple sponge pie
directions: Cream butter and add beaten egg yolks.
Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Add dry ingredients to egg/sugar mixture.
Add pineapple and milk and blend thoroughly.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour mixture in an unbaked crust and bake at 425° for 8 minutes, then reduce temperature to 325° and continue to bake 30 to 35 minutes longer.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Scrub zucchini; remove ends and cook, covered in a small amount of salted water, until tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain, reserving water and chop.
Heat 2 tablespoons butter in a pan and fry onion until yellow.
Blend one cup of reserved water with flour until smooth and add to onion.
Bring mixture to a boil, stirring; add zucchini, milk and salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes and add cream and bread, which have been toasted in butter.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Stir spaghetti with 2 tablespoons margarine, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Put in pie plate.
Spread cottage cheese.
Then add meat, sauce, peppers, onion and mushrooms.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: sauce for broccoli
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat until butter melts.
Pour over cooked broccoli just before serving.

title: lime salad
directions: Sprinkle the dry jello into the other ingredients and beat together.
I usually add pecans also.

title: thanksgiving treats
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix together coconut, sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract; mix well.
Stir in nuts; mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake 20 minutes or until edge of cookies are golden brown.
Remove from baking sheet immediately.
Let cool and serve. Makes about 30 cookies.
So pretty and so easy!

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Take softened cream cheese and green onions and stir well. Spread on each slice of ham and roll up.
Slice in fourths. Chill and serve.

title: apple crisp
directions: Cut margarine into dry ingredients and mix well.
Mixture is crumbly.
Pat 1/2 crumb mixture into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cut up 8 apples, which have been peeled and cored. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and a little cinnamon.
Pat remainder of crumbs on top.
Pat real good.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Layer ingredients in order given in small baking dish.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 250°
for 4 hours.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Put in pot, sugar, cocoa and salt.
Mix well, then add milk. Cook over mid-heat until boils.
Turn down to low heat but try to keep it at a boil (low boil).
Cook for 45 minutes.
Be careful, it will burn, then add butter and vanilla.
Cook remaining 15 or 20 minutes until fudge starts to form on side of pan.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch pan or cake pan.
Let cool in refrigerator.
Cut before it sets.

title: chocolate box cake with cream
directions: Line 9 x 9-inch square pan with foil; press out wrinkles so chocolate box will come off foil easily.
In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt semi-sweet chocolate squares with shortening until melted and smooth, stirring frequently.
Pour melted chocolate into foil lined pan, swirl around covering sides and bottom of pan, keeping edges as even as possible.
Refrigerate 1 minute, then swirl chocolate mixture around inside of pan a second time to reinforce sides of chocolate box.
Refrigerate while making filling.

title: flautas de pollo(chicken flautas)
directions: Wash chicken thoroughly; boil in water until tender.
Remove from broth; cool and shred.
Once you have shredded the chicken, sprinkle some salt and pepper to taste.
Dip tortillas in hot oil to soften, individually.
Place on a platter.
Place some shredded chicken on each tortilla.
Roll tightly and place on cookie sheet.

title: coriander-pepper chops
directions: Combine all ingredients except pork chops.
Place chops in a shallow dish and pour marinade over chops.
Marinate 30 minutes.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound chicken to make 1/4-inch cutlets.
Sprinkle with salt. Place 1 ham slice and cheese slice on cutlet.
Tuck in sides of each; roll up as for jello roll.
Skewer or tie securely.
Coat rolls with 1/4 cup flour; brown in margarine and put in an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.

title: basil salad dressing
directions: Mix garlic, salt, pepper, vinegar and sugar.
Whisk in olive oil and sweet basil.

title: cherry flavored nectar syrup
directions: Boil sugar and water for 20 minutes.
Cool; add rest of ingredients and stir well.
To make an old-fashioned soda, pour 2 tablespoons of syrup in a tall glass, add 2 scoops of ice cream and fill glass with soda water.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve over tortilla chips.

title: avocado-corn salsa
directions: Gently stir together all ingredients in a medium bowl; adjust flavors to taste.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: party chicken
directions: Line a shallow casserole with dried beef.
Lay chicken on top. Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Lay bacon on top. Bake, uncovered, 3 hours at 275°.

title: rhubarb meringue pie dessert
directions: Return to 350° oven and bake for 15 minutes.

title: texas chili with beans
directions: Cook pinto beans.
Sort, wash and cover with water.
Bring to boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Let sit for one hour.
Drain, put in fresh water and cook.
Bring to boil and then simmer 2 hours until beans are done.
Pressure cook beans for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook onions and broccoli until tender; drain.
Add soup; mix well.
Pour into shallow dish; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: jean's pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta al dente.
Grate pickles and carrots.
Cut cauliflower in small sections.
Slice remaining vegetables. Marinate pasta overnight in salad dressing.
Mix with rest of ingredients and mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add tomatoes, diced, just before serving to keep firm.
Serve chilled. Serves 10.

title: homemade peach ice cream
directions: Mix sugar with eggs.
Add milk and vanilla extract.
Stir good and add blended peaches, (blend peaches in blender to small pieces so it will freeze better) and Eagle Brand milk.
Pour into freezer. Add lots of ice and salt.
Takes longer with fruit in ice cream.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine in saucepan sugar, milk and corn syrup and cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking without stirring until
small amount forms a soft ball in cold water (232° on candy thermometer).	Remove from stove; add	peanut butter,
salt and vanilla.
Beat immediately with wooden
spoon until creamy.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: punch
directions: Boil sugar and water.
Cool.
Add orange juice, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Freeze at least 24 hours.
Thaw for 2 hours before serving.
Then chop and add 7-Up.
It's yellow in color but can be changed with food coloring.
Makes 5 quarts.
(Serves 20 people.)

title: creamed corn fritters
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, baking powder, sugar, salt, creamed corn and egg.
Mix well.

title: waffles
directions: Blend butter and sugar together.
Beat eggs and add vanilla, salt and flour.
Form into walnut size balls and put on waffle iron.
Cook until steaming stops and waffles are golden brown.

title: aggie's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix as given.
Drop on cookie sheet by teaspoon.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Best to let stand overnight.
Brush on chicken while cooking slowly over coals.
Turn often to keep from burning.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Whip sugar and cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip.
Stir to blend. Add pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into crust. Chill.

title: classic beef barley soup
directions: Brown meat with onion, celery, carrots and clove of garlic. Add rest of ingredients and simmer.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter and stuffing mix.
Mix melted butter with stuffing mix and use half to line bottom of long casserole dish. Pour squash mixture in dish and top with other half of stuffing mix.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: orange dessert
directions: Make pudding using eggs.
While hot, add dry Jell-O.
Add drained fruit.
Pour over broken cake.
Frost with Cool Whip. Chill thoroughly.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Put milk in double boiler; add chocolate and heat until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add salt, vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, then add remaining ingredients. Dough may seem thin.
Put in refrigerator for a short while and it will thicken.
Bake in greased muffin pans at 350° until golden brown.
(Do not substitute oil for shortening.)

title: vi's easy coconut pie
directions: Whirl eggs in blender.
Mix flour, baking powder and sugar. Add to eggs with all remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Pour into two 9-inch pie pans.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes. Yield:
2 pies.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Beat eggs.
Add flour and sugar and beat until foamy and somewhat thickened.
Fold in pineapple.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish sprayed with vegetable spray.
Top with buttered bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease two 8 x 4-inch loaf pans. Thoroughly mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Divide mixture in half and pour into loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool thoroughly on racks before slicing.

title: squash pickles *
directions: Lay squash out and sprinkle with salt.
Cover with cold water and set overnight.
Drain and combine remaining ingredients.
Boil 3 to 4 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: mom's custard pie
directions: Heat milk and oleo.
Beat eggs (save two of the whites).
Mix milk, egg yolks, sugar, flour, vanilla, food coloring and salt; beat egg whites to soft peaks and fold in last.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, then 20 minutes at 350° in unbaked 9-inch pastry shell.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Layer fruit.
Mix sugar and flour and put over fruit.
Then cover with cheese, Ritz crackers and butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix together; put 1 pint Hellmann's mayonnaise on top.
Store overnight, then mix together before serving.

title: kim's english muffins
directions: Spread mix on each muffin half.
Cut into 1/4 pieces.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: blue ribbon cheesecake
directions: Mix ingredients and pat into greased (or Pam) 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 300°.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix together flour, soda and salt. Combine butter, egg, sugar and flavoring. Add sour cream and half of flour. Blend. Add remaining flour. Roll to 1/4-inch thickness on lightly floured surface. Cut. Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and press mixture into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Mix last 3 ingredients well. Spread over cake mixture.

title: nana's desert
directions: Mix all together in bowl and chill for 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in loaf or tube pan for 1 hour at 325°.
Mix together 1 cup powdered sugar and juice of one lemon; pour over hot cake.

title: buttercream easter eggs
directions: Cream 1/2 pound butter and cream cheese.
Gradually blend in sugar.
Shape into eggs.
Cool for 1 hour.
Melt chocolate, remaining 1 tablespoon butter, wax and vanilla over hot water. Dip eggs in mixture and allow to cool on waxed paper.
Makes 50 eggs.
Use a double boiler pan.

title: corn pudding
directions: Heat butter and sugar in a medium size saucepan until butter melts.
Stir in flour and blend well. Remove from heat. Gradually stir in cream. Add eggs and baking powder; mix well. Fold in onion, bell pepper, black pepper and corn.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart casserole. Bake 40 minutes at 350° or until a knife inserted into center comes out clean.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cracklin' corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal and flour.
Add milk.
Stir in cracklings.
Pour into greased iron skillet. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: spud soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery, carrots and onion in water until tender. Add other ingredients and cook over medium heat until blended.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix the above ingredients together.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes or until brown on top.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Drizzle lemon juice over apples and toss well.
Add celery and nuts.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise.
Fold into the apple mixture.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together and set aside.
Add beaten egg.
Add cherries and nuts.
Stir in the dry ingredients until blended.
Do not add liquid.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
When cool, serve with whipped cream.

title: almond rusks(almond biscotti)
directions: Preheat the oven to 325° and grease one large cookie sheet. Combine the eggs and sugar and beat them together until thick and pale yellow, then beat in the vanilla and almond extracts.
Stir together 1 cup of the flour with the baking powder and salt; add to the first mixture along with the butter and beat until the dough is smooth.
Beat in the remaining 2/3 cup flour, then stir in the almonds.
Divide the dough in half and on a lightly floured surface, shape each piece into a loaf about 10 inches long, 1 1/2 inches wide and 1 inch high.
Using spatulas and your hands, carefully lift onto the prepared cookie sheet.
Push the loaves back into shape if necessary.
Bake for about 25 minutes or until the dough has puffed, the tops have cracked and are golden brown. Remove from the oven and let cool for about 5 minutes.
Transfer to a cutting board and with a thin, sharp knife, cut each loaf into about 15 (3/4-inch thick) slices.
Place the slices, standing upright, on the baking sheet and return to the oven.
Bake again for 15 minutes.
Remove from the oven (they will be soft, but will crisp as they cool) and transfer to a rack to cool completely.

title: steaming hot holiday punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a very large pan, except the cinnamon sticks.
Bring to a boil and turn to simmer for a few minutes.
You can put the ingredients in a crock-pot after it has boiled and keep warm over low heat.
Cinnamon sticks should be put in mugs with individual servings and used as stirrers.

title: chicken milano
directions: Prepare rice or orzo as label directs.
Meanwhile, remove the skin and bones from the chicken breasts.
Cut breast meat into 1 1/2-inch chunks.
In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot butter, cook onion and garlic until onion is tender, stirring occasionally. Add chicken chunks.
Cook until chicken is lightly browned on all sides, stirring frequently. Stir in undiluted tomato soup and remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. To serve, spoon chicken mixture over rice in deep platter.
Makes 4 servings.
Contains 460 calories per serving.

title: caribbean chicken
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: "sinker" dumplings
directions: Rinse grated potatoes in cold water; drain well.
Combine potatoes, eggs, salt, crumbs and enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Using a wet spoon, drop tablespoons of dough into the boiling, salted water.
Cook until the dumplings float to the top. Serve with roast pork.
Use pork drippings and browned, minced/chopped onions over the top of the dumplings.

title: lemonade bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 cup lemonade, in a large mixing bowl.
Blend well and beat for 3 minutes on medium speed. Use 9 x 5-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Loosen bread from edges of pan.
Pour 1/3 cup concentrated lemonade over bread.
Cool.
Remove from pan.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together sugar and softened margarine.
Add eggs, corn syrup, oats and coconut.
Mix well. Put in unbaked pie shell and bake for 45 minutes.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes and enough water to cover in 4-quart saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium; cook 25 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.
Mash potatoes, gradually stirring in salad dressing, cream cheese, onion powder, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper until light and fluffy.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover tightly; freeze.

title: myrtle's pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine filling ingredients into pie shells.
Place in oven for 45 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes and cook until tender.
Drain water; add butter and salt.
Add eggs, pimentos, onions, pickles, mustard and mayonnaise as needed to mix.

title: abigail's open house fruit punch
directions: Mix up some of the punch ahead of time, with the exception of the ginger ale.
Pour a small amount in a ring mold and arrange red or green maraschino cherries or fruit which will match your color scheme in an interesting design.
Freeze this until solid, then fill the mold the rest of the way with additional punch and freeze.

title: chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons butter until smooth.
Add next six ingredients; mix well.
Separate crescent rolls into four; close perforations. Spoon 1/2 cup mixture into center of rectangle.
Pull four corners of dough to top and seal tightly.
Brush top with cup of remaining butter; dip in crumbs.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt into mixing bowl. Add corn meal.
Cut in shortening with fork or pastry cutter until mixture is fine textured.
Combine eggs and milk and add to dry ingredients.
Stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Do not beat.
Pour into well-greased pan and bake in oven at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: florida trifle
directions: Cook cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut in cubes when cool.
Mix both packages of pudding with milk and let thicken.
In a large glass or trifle bowl, layer 1/2 cake cubes, 1/2 pudding, 1/2 whipped topping, oranges, pineapple and coconut.
Repeat layers, ending with coconut.
Chill several hours.

title: cooked icing
directions: Combine milk and cake flour.
Cook on medium heat until thick. Set aside to cool.
After completely cooled, add to pudding mixture the confectioners sugar and shortening.
Whip until creamy.

title: poke cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes, then poke with fork at 1/2-inch intervals. Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water and stir.
Pour over cake in pan.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Top with thawed Cool Whip. Keep refrigerated.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine and freeze in ice cream freezer.
Yield:
4 quarts.

title: custard pie
directions: Bake pastry shell in a 450° oven for 5 minutes.

title: broccoli sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Pour over steamed broccoli and serve.

title: crab, shrimp and artichoke au gratin
directions: Combine shrimp, artichokes, crab and cheese.
Saute garlic, scallions and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter.
Drain and combine with seafood mixture.
Melt remaining butter; stir in flour and when smooth, add milk.
Stir constantly over medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in wine.
Add seafood mixture to the white sauce and pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with more cheese and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Blend in mixture.
Put in small bowl lined with plastic wrap. Chill.
Unmold and garnish.
Can serve with water biscuits.

title: spaghetti
directions: Fry beef, onion and garlic until done.
(Add green peppers and mushrooms, if desired.)
Add seasonings to taste.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Simmer.
Boil spaghetti noodles and mix.

title: granola
directions: Mix liquids together and add to dry ingredients to moisten. More liquid may be needed.
Spread and bake on cookie sheets at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.
Cool completely and store in tightly sealed container.

title: surprise tea cakes
directions: In mixing bowl, soften butter.
Add vanilla, egg and powdered sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour and nuts. Shape dough (about size of walnut) around each chocolate kiss. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in a 325° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
They should not be browned, but make sure they are cooked through and not doughy.
Roll warm cookies in powdered sugar.
They can be frozen for later use.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Soak
gelatine in 1/2 cup shrimp liquid.
(Drain liquid from rest
of
canned shrimp and cover shrimp with cold water until ready to add.) Heat undiluted soup to boil;
add cheese and
mix until
well
blended.
Add	gelatine
and cool.
Add mayonnaise, vegetables, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice. Stir
to	mix well.
Drain
shrimp
well, then add to mixture gently.
Pour into chilled mold and refrigerate.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugars, beaten eggs, nutmeg, cinnamon and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour and soda which have been sifted together.
Mix well.
Last, add rolled oats and nuts.
Drop by spoonful on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and apples together.
Combine oil and eggs.
Add to apple mixture.
Combine flour, nutmeg, cinnamon, salt and soda; mix well.
Then add to apple mixture.
Then add pecans or walnuts. Bake in greased and floured Bundt cake pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pecan pralines
directions: In a 2-quart heavy saucepan combine sugars and cream.

Bring to boiling over medium heat, stirring occasionally with wooden spoon. Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, to 228° on candy thermometer or until syrup spins 2-inch thread when dropped from spoon.
Add pecans and butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently to 236° on candy thermometer or until a little in cold water forms soft ball.
Remove pan to wire rack.
Let cool 10 minutes to 200° on thermometer.
Stir abut 1 minute or until slightly thick but still glossy.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 3 inches apart onto sheet of foil (pralines will spread into large patties).
If mixture becomes too stiff, stir in 1 to 2 drops cold water.

title: hawaiian fudge
directions: Cook until soft ball stage.
Cool.
Beat until creamy.
Add nuts. Tint light green.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cut in squares.

title: easy tea doughnuts
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar, melted butter, vanilla and milk.
Beat 1 minute.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add to egg mixture. Beat until well blended.
Drop by small teaspoonfuls into preheated shortening.
Fry until golden brown, turning to brown evenly.
Drain.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Boil stalk of celery, onion and salt with chicken.
Drain and pull chicken apart.
Set aside.
Mix 2 cans of cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder in bowl.
Place chicken over broccoli in layers.
Pour mixture over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese and then add crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grilled chicken breast with black bean ranchero sauce(serves 4)
directions: Soak beans for at least two hours, preferably overnight.
Cook beans in 3 cups of water, bay leaves and thyme.
Simmer beans until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Drain liquid from beans and remove bay leaves. Char the tomatoes over an open flame until black on one side.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients into a mixing bowl.
Use an electric mixer.
Beat mixture until very smooth.
Pour into a round cake pan.
Place in cold oven.
Turn heat to 325°.
Bake about 2 hours or until done.
Use thin knife to test if cake is done.
I hope you enjoy it.

title: 6 week muffins
directions: Before you start, dissolve the baking soda in the boiling water; let cool.
In a large bowl, mix the cooled soda water and all remaining ingredients in the order given.
Add any other desired goodies, such as blueberries, raisins and bananas.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in greased or papered tins.
(Batter will stay good for up to 6 weeks.)

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients. Leave 1/2 cup of cheese for top.
Pour into quart casserole and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 30 minutes in 400° oven.

title: cinnamon graham muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine egg, buttermilk, cooking oil and vanilla.
Stir in cracker crumbs and raisins.
Set aside.
Stir together remaining ingredients and add to egg mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Fill greased or lined muffin pans 2/3 full. Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Makes 10 to 12 muffins.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix boiling water, butter or margarine and oats and let set 20 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: mounds bars
directions: Mix graham crackers, butter and sugar.
Press in 8 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix Eagle Brand milk and coconut.
Spread over graham cracker crust while still hot. Return to oven for 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter and wax if you wish.
Add nuts if desired.
Cut and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: *I use 1/2 cup white and 1/2 cup dark syrup.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt oleo in large saucepan.
Mix all soups and milk into oleo.
Spread rice on bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 of soup mixture over rice.
Mix soup and rice.
Place chicken breasts on top of rice.
Pour remaining soup mixture over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.

title: noonday sweet onion and sausage stuffing
directions: Split onions (and make a nest for sausage mixture) and place in a greased dish.
Cook chopped onions and sausage in frying pan until brown; drain.
Add water and soup to pan and cook until soup is smooth.
Add stuffing and mix well.
Put mixture inside 6 split and nested onions.
Onions should not be touching.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika in last 5 minutes time.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on back of box.
(Bake in two 9-inch round cake pans.)
When cooled, slice each layer in half so to have 4 layers.

title: easy cucumber pickles
directions: Using 6 pre-sterilized jars, place 1 sprig dill, 2 cloves garlic and 1 pepper in each jar.
Fill with sliced cucumbers. Combine 2 quarts water, salt and vinegar in pan.
Bring to a boil. Pour over cucumbers and seal.
Let stand 3 weeks before using.

title: clara's taco salad
directions: Put all items into individual bowls.
Allow each person to build their own taco salad with the items above to their personal liking.
The salad dressing is the best!

title: holiday scent
directions: Put ingredients in a large saucepan and bring to a rolling boil; simmer 30 minutes.
Refrigerate in a non-aluminum container. When you want a festive holiday smell in your rooms, simmer without a cover on the stove.

title: glazed pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice. Combine pudding mix and pineapple juice; set aside. Arrange pineapple slices on bottom of a 13
x 9-inch greased pan. Place cherry half in center of each. Pour pudding mixture over pineapple; sprinkle with brown sugar.

title: fluffy icing
directions: Cook the milk and cornstarch.
Let cool.
Beat the sugar, butter, Crisco and vanilla.
Add cooled milk and cornstarch. Beat 10 minutes.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Mix
in
a baking dish flour, sugar and milk.
Add margarine.
Bring peaches to a hard boil in saucepan,
then
pour over the mixture in the baking dish. Bake 40 minutes in 375° oven.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Brown bacon, onion and bread cubes.
Add flour and stir until brown.
Add partially drained tomatoes.
Simmer.
Delicious served over mashed potatoes.

title: fig preserves
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 5 tablespoons of hot water.
Combine and cook until thick.
Makes 1 1/2 pints.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix well.
Pour in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: italian pork chops
directions: Take pork chops and dip in eggs, then bread crumbs.
Brown pork chops on both sides.
Then add 1 to 1 1/2 cups of water to the skillet.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, turning once.
Drain water, then cover the pork chops with spaghetti sauce and simmer, covered, for another 15 to 20 minutes.
The last 5 minutes, cover the entire thing with the cheese.
Allow to melt and serve.
Serves 4.

title: easy turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Saut mushrooms in 1 Tbsp. butter.
Remove from pan.
Saut onions in remaining butter, whisk in flour.
Cook 3 minutes, pour in broth add milk and spices and bring to boil and cook 2-3 minutes.
Add turkey and cook another 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms and heat through.
Toss with cooked and drained pasta. Top with parmesan cheese and serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Add pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients (sifted or mixed).
Pour into well greased pans.
(Soup or fruit cans can be used.)
Regular loaf pans (if small pans are used, makes 4 loaves).
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes in 350° oven.

title: maple heights baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef until browned, stirring to crumble; drain. Combine ground beef and next 10 ingredients. Spoon mixture into lightly greased 2-quart baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Fold in dry corn muffin mix.
Add melted butter.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: pumpkin or squash pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, salt, eggs, sugars, flour & spices together, then stir in the milk.
Pour into pie shells and sprinkle with a little more cinnamon.
Bake 425° for 15 minutes, then 350° until done (when knife inserted in center comes out clean).

title: crab dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, salt, onion, milk and horseradish.
Mix with mixer until smooth.
Stir in crab meat and almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: paradise bars
directions: Mix together.
Press into greased 8 x 10-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into squares. One-half cup of dates and/or cherries may be added.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together. (Do not salt.) Put into baking dish, and bake covered at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: pineapple pecan cheese ball
directions: Mix pineapple, cheese, peppers, onions and salt.
Add 1/2 cup pecans; mix well.
Shape and roll ball in remainder of pecans. Chill well before serving with crackers of your choice.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown the hamburger and bacon in a large skillet.
Drain and put in casserole. Add all remaining ingredients. Stir and bake for 1 hour.

title: drop cheese biscuits
directions: Mix with fork until blended.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and brush with garlic butter (1/8 teaspoon garlic spread and 1/2 stick butter or margarine).

title: corned beef sandwich filling
directions: Mix ingredients together (or grind together in food grinder). Mix with enough mayonnaise for good spreading consistency.

title: old homesteader soup
directions: Brown ground beef in oil and drain.
Add chopped green pepper, onion and chili powder; continue cooking until vegetables are tender.
Add the remaining ingredients; simmer 30 minutes to blend flavors.
May add more chili powder if hotter soup is desired.

title: moma's cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray. Cream together the margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla. Stir in coconut, oatmeal, cereal and pecans. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes for chewy, 12 to 15 minutes for crunchy. (We prefer chewy.)

title: sugar-free apple tarts
directions: Cook apples in water until tender and most of the water cooks out; let cool.

title: teddy bear bread
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk mixture and 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough more flour to make a stiff dough.
On floured board knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Grease top.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.

title: german sugar cookies
directions: Combine the sugar, butter or margarine, milk, eggs, baking soda (in boiling water) and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Mix on medium speed until well blended.
Slowly add baking powder and flour to mixture.
Mix well.
Add coconut and mix well again.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix baking powder, salt and flour.
Add half to sugar mixture with milk, then remainder of flour.
Add flavor.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tangy mustard appetizers
directions: Gradually add water to mustard in small bowl; stir until well blended.
This makes 1/4 cup.
This is very hot, so use sparingly.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove broth and dice chicken.
Reserve broth for spaghetti.
Saute onion and pepper in butter approximately 4 minutes.
Cook spaghetti in broth, adding water if necessary. When spaghetti is done, do not drain but add chunks of Velveeta and stir until melted.
Mix with chicken and other ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Heat until warm and bubbly.

title: strawberry cool
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water together; add strawberries and marshmallows.
Pour half of mixture into dish.
Chill slightly. Top with a little sour cream.
Pour remaining Jell-O mix over this. Chill.
Mix sour cream, Cool Whip and pecans, spread over top.

title: cherry pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Mix baking powder and flour.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk and cherry juice.
Add cherries, flavorings and nuts. Pour batter into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in 325° oven.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan. Frost.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Wrap around cherries. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Melt wax and chocolate bits over medium heat until melted.
Dip cherries in chocolate.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate until served.
May be served on lettuce or any type plate or platter.
Can also be put on roll or bread.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Combine in casserole dish:
zucchini, string beans and tomato sauce.
Add meat.
Heat in oven at 350° for 1/2 hour.
If you wish, put Mozzarella on top.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Layer potatoes in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, brushing each layer with margarine mixture.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Heat butter and oil in large kettle and saute chopped onion, jalapeno, garlic, carrots, celery, and chicken.
Simmer 5 minutes. Combine with cumin, chili powder, salt, lemon pepper, pepper sauce, and flour.
Add tomatoes and chicken stock and simmer one hour.
tags: bottled liquid hot red pepper sauce

title: pepper steak
directions: In a skillet melt butter. Add all the vegetables and salt and simmer for 5 to 7 minutes. When your steaks are done, pour vegetables over the steaks and let cook on low heat for 10 to 12 minutes. Serve with rice or baked potatoes.

title: broccoli cheese scalloped potatoes
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot oleo, cook onion until tender. Add remaining ingredients, except parsley.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until hot. Garnish with parsley.

title: sidewalk chalk(craft idea)
directions: *Okay to use wet poster paint, just decrease amount of water.

title: hawaiian ham
directions: Combine brown sugar, cornstarch, salt, vinegar, pineapple juice
and soy sauce in a saucepan.
Cook until mixture is clear and slightly thickened, stirring constantly.
Place ham in	a casserole;	add onion slices, green peppers and pineapple.	Pour sauce over and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate deluxe zucchini cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Beat eggs in large bowl until frothy; gradually beat in sugar and oil.
Add chocolate, vanilla and almond extract.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Squeeze excess moisture from zucchini; fold zucchini, nuts and dates into batter.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes (cake will appear moist).
Let stand inverted on wire rack 20 minutes; remove pan.
Cool cake completely.
Frost with butter frosting or a chocolate glaze, if you wish.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: walnut spice kisses
directions: Beat egg white with salt until stiff.
Gradually beat in sugar mixed with spices.
Fold in chopped walnuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto a well-greased cookie sheet.
Top with golden Diamond walnut halves.
Bake at 250° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Dot top with margarine.
Sprinkle 1 cup of corn flakes (crunched up) on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 adults.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, milk, pumpkin and spices in large bowl or electric mixer on low speed for 1 minute.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell.
Chill.
Serve garnished with prepared whipped topping.

title: overnight lettuce salad
directions: Cook and drain peas; cool.
Break up (don't cut) lettuce in salad bowl.
Chop green onions and dice celery.
Sprinkle this over lettuce.
Sprinkle peas on lettuce, next.
Spread mayonnaise over peas.
Sprinkle mayonnaise with Parmesan cheese.
Crumble bacon on top*.
Cover well and refrigerate overnight.

title: salmon cheddar pie
directions: Make regular pie crust to fit a 10-inch pie tin and bake it. Beat eggs.
Add milk, butter, parsley, onion, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Fold in cheese and salmon. Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown in 375° oven.

title: sparkling tea punch
directions: Freeze 1 quart ginger ale for cubes.
Boil sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Combine with juices and tea.
Chill.
Before serving, add chilled raspberry soda.
Float ginger ale cubes and mint leaves.
Serves 40 punch size cups.

title: yogurt pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each addition.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing until just blended.
Add orange rind, vanilla and yogurt.
Mix well.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Cool 15 minutes and remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack.

title: christmas wreath cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Put round drinking glass in center of platter.
Drop tablespoons of mixture around glass to form wreath.
Smooth with spatula.
Remove glass. Garnish with chopped parsley and green pimiento.
Make a bow from red pimiento.
I use canned ones.
Serve with crackers or Triscuits.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Saute garlic in butter and oil.
Cut sausage into bite size pieces and saute until brown.
Add vegetables and lightly toss. Cook until tender.
Add the cream, chopped basil and the halved tomatoes; cook until the tomatoes are heated through.
Serve over hot pasta.
Garnish with chopped parsley, basil and Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: french tuna salad
directions: Make layers, using a large, round, flat plate.
Layer coarsely grated egg whites, coarsely grated cheese, chopped and drained tuna, 1/2 cup mayonnaise, minced onion and coarsely grated egg yolks.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together. Add the oil, food coloring, buttermilk, vinegar and eggs.
Mix.
Bake in 3 layer pans that have been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Squeeze the orange. Add boiling water to make 1 cup.
Cut up orange rind fine, then add orange juice and boiled water.
Add vanilla, oil and slightly beaten eggs. Add the flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Blend well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Grease pans (1 large loaf pan or 2 small).
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: aunt donna's cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate for a few hours before serving.

title: golden peach dumplings
directions: Mix flour with salt.
