Cut in shortening until particles are size of small peas.
Add cheese; mix lightly with fork.
Add water to make stiff dough.

title: mexican dish
directions: Break up tortillas in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Brown hamburger; drain. Add onion and 2 cans of kidney beans; mix, and pour over tortillas. Stir together Ro-Tel, hot taco sauce and cream of chicken soup; pour over mixture. Top with the cheeses. Put in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips together and stir until creamy. Pour over cereal and mix until well coated. Pour into paper or plastic sack with powdered sugar and shake. Use enough powdered sugar to coat cereal.

title: best-ever banana pudding
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a heavy saucepan. Whisk together milks and egg yolks; stir into dry ingredients. Cook over medium heat, whisking constantly, until smooth and thickened. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.

title: flour tortilla fingers
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with olives, chilies and nuts. Spread mixture thinly on a flour tortilla; lay another tortilla on top and spread another layer on that.
(I usually use 5 layers.) Press edges together firmly.
Chill.
Can be cut into fingers or squares.
Put damp paper towel over all to keep edges from curling or drying out.

title: apple butterscotch bread
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add butterscotch morsels, raisins and nuts; mix well.
Combine egg and milk in a separate bowl; 1 into mixture.
Add applesauce and beat mixture vigorously by hand for 30 seconds.
Pour into a large greased loaf pan (about 9 1/4 x 5 1/4 x 2 1/2-inch) and bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool completely before slicing. Serve it for breakfast, dessert, snack or anytime!

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet on medium heat. Add chicken, onion and pepper. Cook and stir until chicken is cooked thoroughly.
Add corn, broth and salsa.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes. Fluff with a fork. Sprinkle with cheese.
Let stand, covered, 2 minutes or until cheese melts. Makes 4 servings.

title: crunch drop cookies
directions: Beat oleo, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Beat in flour, soda and salt.
Stir in oatmeal and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: corvette dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat, rinse meat and add chopped onion and small amount of water.
Saute.
Add taco seasoning.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes (mashed) and cheese.
Additional cheese may be needed to thicken.
Taste to see how hot, and if you are crazy, add peppers.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars, oil, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Sift remaining ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet and flatten with a spoon. Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: no sugar sweet potatoes
directions: Drain sweet potatoes and place in casserole dish.
Add melted oleo and apple juice concentrate.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh tomato sauce
directions: Dice tomatoes and fresh garlic, if used.
In a frying pan, heat oil on medium heat. Add garlic and saute for 1 minute.
Add tomatoes and saute until tomatoes are soft and tender.
Add spices and water.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over pasta or on top of meatballs.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook ground beef with chopped onion.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper in a casserole dish.
Put layer of rice, layer of sauce and layer of cheese.
Continue; make sure cheese is last layer.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 or more.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, oatmeal and salt and pepper.
Make meatballs the size of golf balls.
Brown in oil.
Place in a baking dish. Make gravy in skillet used to brown meat.
Cover meatballs with gravy.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Then boil, without stirring, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over popcorn, mixing well.
Turn into 2 large shallow baking or roasting pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes. Cool completely.
Store in tightly covered containers.

title: herbed potatoes(microwave)
directions: Slice potatoes about 1/4 inch thick.
Arrange potato and onion slices in microwave-safe dish, placing smaller pieces in the center.
Combine water, butter and herb.
Pour over potatoes and onions.
Cover and cook on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir before serving.

title: rich corn bread
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add milk gradually, eggs well beaten and butter.
Bake in a buttered, shallow pan, in a hot oven, 400°.

title: crunchy potato chip salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine mayonnaise and vinegar.
Stir in cabbage, tuna, carrots, green pepper and onion.
Cover and chill. Just before serving, add potato chips; toss lightly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lentil soup
directions: Add lentils and all other ingredients to 1/2 gallon water in large soup pot.
Bring to boil.
When onion and carrots are very soft, lower heat and cook over low boil until lentils are tender. Stir constantly.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and sugar mixed together.
Mix and add eggs one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add milk and pineapple and mix well.
Add vanilla and coconut and mix.
Makes four 9-inch pies in shallow pie dishes and two deep dish pies. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until pie is golden brown.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, butter and sugar, add eggs; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients, add to creamed mixture; add nuts. Drop from teaspoon, about 2 inches apart, onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: hush puppies
directions: Add well beaten egg and milk to corn meal.
Add hot melted shortening and minced onions just before frying.
Fry tablespoon of batter in deep fat.
Excellent when served with fish.
Frying in grease used for frying fish adds an extra delicious flavor to hush puppies.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together biscuit mix, cheese and pepper. Stir in beaten eggs just until mixture is moistened.
Fold in zucchini.
In a 10-inch skillet, melt butter.
Using 2 tablespoons mixture for each round, cook 4 rounds at a time for 2 to 3 minutes on each side, or until golden brown.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate over hot water in double boiler. Stir in milk and sugar alternately.
Add salt.
Use low heat and cook at least 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook over water to reheat any remaining sauce.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Dice scallions.
Cut dried beef into small shreds.
Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 2 balls.
Roll balls into crushed walnuts.
Freeze.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.
Do not open while cooking.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: In large bowl, place Ricotta, cream cheese and sour cream. Beat until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch spring-form pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven; let cake set 1 hour and don't open oven door.
Remove cake from oven; let cool in pan for 45 minutes.
Remove pan sides.
Refrigerate. Serve with cherry pie filling or sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: christmas punch
directions: Place the spices in a bag of fine cheesecloth.	Peel & cut into thin slices the lemons and oranges, mixing with the apple cider and pineapple juice.
To this add the bag of spices and bring to a very low simmering boil.
Stir as it simmers for approximately 15 minutes, then add salt and stir vigorously.
Just prior to serving, add as much rum as preferred.

title: easy fettucini(very delicious and easy!!)
directions: While your pasta is cooking, saute the shallots in butter for about 2 to 3 minutes.
Now stir in the chicken broth.
Boil gently for about 3 minutes.
Remove from the heat and stir in the heavy cream.
By this time the pasta should be ready to be drained.
The last step is to add the drained pasta, sour cream, cheese and chives.
Toss and heat through but don't boil.
Go get a nice glass of wine and mangia!!

title: sticky buns
directions: Spray tube pan with Pam.
Sprinkle nuts and raisins in pan. Put in roll dough.
Sprinkle dry pudding on top.
Sprinkle sugar on.
Melt butter and pour on top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Let rise overnight.
(Cover with towel.)
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool 5 minutes, then flip onto plate.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Use deep round dish.
Cut pound cake and layer cake and strawberries; beginning with cake and ending with strawberries. Top with:
egg yolks beaten with confectioners sugar.
Beat this until mixture is pale yellow.
Add the whipped cream or Cool Whip. Mix well.
Refrigerate.
Is better when sets several hours to allow cake to absorb juice from berries.

title: bottletown inn squash
directions: Peel, cook and mash squash.
Saute onion.
Add cracker crumbs, cream and salt to taste.
Mix in squash.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables.
Drain off water.
In large mixing bowl, add cooked vegetables and mayonnaise, onion and grated cheese.
Spread in greased baking dish.
Add crushed Ritz crackers over top of casserole.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, salt, eggs and flavors.
Make a paste of cocoa and food coloring.
Add to first mixture.
Alternately add flour and buttermilk.
Mix soda and vinegar in a small bowl; add to batter.
Blend.
Bake in three 8 or 9-inch pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350° or until tests done.
Let cool completely.
Cover with frosting.

title: dirt cups(children's recipe)
directions: You will also need 8 to 10 (7 ounce) paper cups.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: aunt betty's breakfast biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch or equivalent pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: pudding cheese pie
directions: Combine pie filling, sugar and milk.
Microwave at High 4 minutes; stir well.
Cook
2 minutes longer; stir again and cook 2 more minutes until mixture comes to a boil.
Add cream cheese, blending until smooth.
Pour into pie shell; chill at least 3 hours.

title: christmas crunch
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients and spread mixture out on waxed paper. Melt almond bark in microwave and pour over mixture. Let cool and crumble up. Store in covered container.

title: honey curry chicken
directions: Combine first five ingredients; stir well.
Dip chicken into honey sauce; coat well.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Reserve remaining sauce.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, basting occasionally with remaining sauce.

title: jalapeno corn casserole
directions: Cook rice as usual.
Saute onion, pepper and celery in butter until tender.
Stir into rice and corn the cheese and chopped jalapeno peppers.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix together in large covered jar.
Wash and cut cukes into strips and put into jar mixture.
Ready to eat instantly but the longer they are in the jar, the more dill they become.
As you take some out, add more cukes.

title: peanut butter snack spread
directions: Combine dry milk, water and vanilla, stirring to moisten.
Add honey and peanut butter.
Spread between graham crackers or regular crackers.
The spread can also be formed into balls, chilled and eaten as candy.
Keeps well in refrigerator, but difficult to spread when cold.

title: tuna tomato combo
directions: Saute Onions in Butter; add Flour, then everything else except Tuna. Cook; stir constantly, until thick. Stir in Tuna. Dump this mixture over bed of Rice.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Soften the butter or margarine.
In a mixing bowl, cream together the butter (margarine) and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Stir together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and beat until blended.
Divide dough in half.
Cover and chill about 1 hour.
On a ligthly floured surface, roll each half of dough to 1/8 inch thickness for thin crisp cookies or 1/4 inch thickness for thick cookies.
Cut into desired shapes with cookie cutters.
Place cookies on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake thin cookies in 375° oven for 7 to 8 minutes. Bake thick cookies for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet; cool on wire rack.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen thin cookies or about 2 1/2 dozen thick cookies.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in double boiler over water.
Mix the next 4 ingredients together and roll into small balls.
Take toothpick and dip balls in chocolate mixture.
Makes large amount.

title: rice breakfast
directions: Heat leftover rice in microwave oven.
Top with warm milk, cinnamon and sugar.

title: greek feta cheese triangles
directions: Thaw puff pastry for 20 minutes.
In a bowl, mix cheese, eggs and parsley until well blended.
Unfold 1 puff pastry sheet and, on a lightly floured surface, roll to a 9 x 12-inch rectangle.
Cut into 3-inch squares.
Put 1 tablespoon cheese filling in the center of each square.
Moisten edges with water and fold pastry in half forming a triangle.
Press edges together firmly with tines of a fork to seal.
Chill.
Repeat with remaining pastry sheet and cheese mixture.
Place triangles on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake in a preheated 425° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until puffed and golden brown.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Makes 24.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.

title: green angel salad
directions: Mix the lime jello and water.
Set to firm, then whip. Add the marshmallows, cottage cheese, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan or in a mold.

title: zucchini imperial
directions: Boil zucchini in 2 cups of water.
Cook until just tender and drain.
Beat eggs; stir in mayonnaise, onion, green pepper, cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Add zucchini.
Put in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Dot with 1 tablespoon butter and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients at medium speed until well mixed, occasionally scraping the sides. Drop by teaspoonfuls 1-inch apart onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Immediately remove to wire racks to cool.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: butterscotch-walnut bread
directions: Mix vanilla, sugar, egg and butter.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk; beat for 4 minutes.
Add nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup.

Roll mixture into small patties and then roll in flour. Brown on all sides in a skillet with small amount of oil. Place patties in a casserole dish and pour mushroom soup over patties. Cover with aluminum foil. Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: homemade cabbage rolls
directions: You will also need 1 box round toothpicks.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix brown sugar to cream cheese until creamy.
Slice apples and dip in mixture.
Can double recipe if needed.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Slice bananas and dip in lemon juice.
In a large bowl combine sweetened condensed milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat well. Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into 2 1/2-quart glass serving bowl.
Top with 1/3 each of wafers, bananas and pudding.
Repeat layers twice, ending with pudding.
Chill.
Garnish as desired.

title: nutty yam bake
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until tender, drain off liquid.
Beat with electric mixer, adding all listed ingredients.
Pour into greased 1 1/2 quart casserole.

title: everyman's pate
directions: In a small skillet, cook bacon until it begins to brown. Transfer to the bowl of a processor.
Add onion to the bacon fat and cook until limp.
Add onion to the bowl.
Add chicken livers to the fat, cooking until no longer pink.
Add them to the bowl. Cook sausage in the same pan until browned and add to the bowl. Add brandy, cream, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Process until smooth. Pour into a well buttered mold and refrigerate until firm. Unmold and serve with rounds of dark bread.

title: hot tuna sandwich
directions: Place mixture in hamburger rolls and wrap in foil. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: dijon green peppercorn dip
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container. Blend just until smooth.
Serve with chicken chunks or raw vegetables.

title: poor boy cookies
directions: Simmer dates,
Crisco,
water and apples for 15 minutes and let cool.
Mix remaining ingredients and then add to other mixture.
Pour
on
greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15
minutes.
When
cool
ice
with
a thin powdered sugar icing. Cut in squares and these can be frozen.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Mix sugar, water, syrup and salt together and boil for 1 minute.
Add pecans and cook to 305° on candy thermometer.
Add soda, stir and turn out onto buttered pans.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine flour and sugar and add to melted margarine.
Blend in beaten eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fat-free potato burritos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread one cup of the sauce over the bottom of a casserole dish.
Spread a line of potatoes down the center of each tortilla.
Sprinkle on some scallion, corn and green chilies.
Roll up and place, seam side down, in the casserole.
Repeat until all of the ingredients are used.
Pour the remaining sauce over the tortillas.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes, or until sauce is bubbly.

title: garlic grits casserole
directions: Melt cheese and margarine together.
Add to beaten eggs and milk.
Stir into grits.
Pour into greased casserole.
Crumble crushed corn flakes on top before baking.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes or until set.

title: easy minestrone soup
directions: In small microwave-safe bowl, put 1 tablespoon olive oil, chopped onion and garlic.
Microwave for 1 minute with bowl covered.
Transfer to 4-quart pan and add all remaining ingredients.
Cook on medium heat until vegetables are done. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on hot soup.

title: turkey mushroom casserole
directions: Cook onions in oleo.
Blend in flour.
Add broth and liquid from peas.
Cook until thickened.
Add turkey, peas, soup and seasoning.
Turn into greased casserole and top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: In a small bowl, combine egg, milk and pepper.
In another bowl, stir together cracker crumbs, Parmesan cheese and dried parsley flakes.
Dip eggplant slices in the milk mixture to coat, then dip both sides in the cracker mixture.
Spray a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish with nonstick spray coating.
Arrange eggplant in dish.
In a bowl, stir together tomato sauce, oregano and garlic; pour over eggplant.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 40 minutes, or until eggplant is tender.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 10 minutes more.
Can serve over spaghetti.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage and place in large baking dish.
Saute onion, bell pepper and ground chuck.
Drain off fat and place on top of cabbage.
Pour can of tomato soup on top.
Rinse can with small amount of water; pour on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° until cabbage is tender, but not mushy (approximately 30 minutes).

title: eggplant salad (salata melitzanas)(greek)
directions: Bake eggplant in
a 350° oven for 1 hour or until soft. Remove skin and chop flesh.
In a bowl, combine eggplant, onion, salt, pepper, olive oil and vinegar.
Garnish with chopped parsley, tomato wedges and olives.
Oven temperature: 350°. Preparation time:
1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cooking time:
1 hour.

title: pork chops - rice
directions: Cook rice with 2 cups water about 10 minutes. Spread in bottom of baking dish. Salt, pepper and flour chops; brown slightly on top of stove.
Place chops on top of rice.
Mix both cans of soup with 1/2 can
of water and pour over all.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
If it seems too dry, add a little more water on top. (Recipe may also be used with chicken.)

title: pecan crisps
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually and cream thoroughly.
Blend in 1 egg yolk and milk.
Add sifted flour to mixture.

title: baked squash
directions: Put squash, green chilies, tomatoes and onion in a large roaster pan.
Put cheese on top and bake for 1 1/2 hours or until soft at 325°.

title: cinnamon stick cucumbers
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers and cut out seed.
Mix lime in 8 1/2 quarts water.
Pour over cucumbers and let set for 24 hours.
Wash off lime water.
In pan, combine 1 cup cider vinegar, food coloring, alum and enough water to cover cucumbers.
Simmer for 2 hours on stove.
Drain and make syrup with vinegar, 2 cups water, sugar, stick cinnamon and cinnamon candy.
Bring to boil and let set for 24 hours.
Put drained cucumbers in jars.
Cover with hot syrup, putting 1 cinnamon stick in each pint jar.
Seal.

title: punch with mint
directions: Stir together orange juice, cranberry juice and sugar.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Float mint leaves for garnish.

title: new england boiled beef dinner
directions: Cover corned beef with water and simmer until tender, about 3 1/2 hours.
Remove meat to a hot platter; keep hot in a low oven. Boil onions, turnip, carrots and potatoes in the broth for 30 minutes or until done.
Add cabbage during last 15 minutes of cooking.
Arrange vegetables around the corned beef on platter or to allow room for carving, serve separately.
(If corned beef has not been kept hot, return it to the pot for a few minutes.) Serves 6.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Beat 4 egg whites stiff.
Sprinkle in sugar, baking powder and vanilla flavoring.
Add crushed vanilla wafers and chopped nuts. Pour in buttered 8 to 9-inch pie pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: parsleyed new potatoes
directions: Prepare and cook new potatoes. Just before serving, toss with butter and sprinkle with parsley.

title: crab and rice primavera
directions: Bring vegetables and water to a boil in a medium saucepan stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat cover and simmer for 8 minutes. Add milk, meat, margarine, garlic powder, and basil.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice and cheese, remove from heat, cover let and stand for 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork.

title: pat's chicken
directions: Line baking pan with corned beef slices (1 per breast). Wrap bacon strips (uncooked) around each chicken breast (wrap as many strips around each breast as you want, usually 2 will be fine). Mix sour cream with soup. Pour mixture over chicken breasts in pan. Bake at 250° for approximately 3 hours. Serve with mashed potatoes!!

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a buttered 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, salt and water.
Rub together the flour, sugar and butter.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve warm with cream.

title: wacky cake
directions: In a 8 x 12-inch pan, sift flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Punch 1 large, 1 medium and 1 small hole in mixture.
In large hole, pour melted butter or oil.
In medium hole, pour vinegar.
In small hole, pour vanilla.
Cover all with cold water and gently stir with a fork.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Frost in pan.

title: cherry-almond pie
directions: Mix ingredients and let stand 15 minutes.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Add top crust.
Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil butter, cocoa, milk and sugar for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter and stir, then add rolled oats.
Spoon on wax paper and let cool.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix together apples, bananas, grapes (use Fruit-Fresh liberally), celery, raisins and cherries.
Mix mayonnaise, honey and sour cream; pour over fruit mixture and mix well.
Last, add nuts and marshmallows.
Keep refrigerated.

title: red velvet cake(low-fat recipe)
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese at medium speed until creamy. Gradually add sugar, beating well. Gradually add egg substitute, beating well. Stir in food coloring.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients.
Add to butter mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix until just blended after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into three 9-inch cake pans coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Cool in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes. Remove from pans.
Cool completely on wire racks. Spread Boiled Frosting between layers, on sides and top of cake.

title: floating island punch
directions: Bring water to a boil. Add the sugar and boil until it becomes a syrup. Let cool.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil lasagna in 4 quarts rapidly boiling water to which salt and
olive oil have been added to prevent sticking.
Stir gently for
minutes.
Drain
and
cool.
Saute
beef
and sausage. Drain.
To the spaghetti sauce add the garlic powder and oregano (some
sauces
can omit this).
In a well-greased baking dish, spread a layer of the sauce, lasagna and cheese. Alternate until all are used.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cut in squares.

title: corn casserole
directions: Pour all ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove all skin and bones.
Cover bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan with chicken pieces.
Spread with cream of chicken soup then spread with cream of mushroom soup. Spread bread crumbs.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use 1 1/2-quart, 3-inch deep baking dish.
Melt 1 stick butter in microwave baking dish; add 1 cup sugar, flour and milk.
Whisk, not too well.
Pour in a couple cups of fruit in middle.
(I recommend peaches or blueberries.) Bake 1 hour; serve warm.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat the cream cheese until smooth. Add eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla and sugar and beat again. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300°.

title: swiss cheese bake
directions: Grease 9 x 13 inch pan.
Single layer chicken.
Top each piece with a slice of cheese.
Spoon soup over the chicken.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Bake uncovered 45 to 55 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: pear salad
directions: Pour off enough pear juice to make 1 cup.
Bring to a boil and add gelatin.
Cool.
Blend pears and cream cheese in blender.
Add cooled gelatin and Cool Whip.
Add nuts.

title: quick barbecue
directions: Simmer all ingredients, except ham, for about 1 hour.
Add ham and stir until thoroughly heated.
Serve over small dinner rolls for sandwiches.

title: carrots with onions
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in 1/2 cup water.
Cut carrots in 1-inch strips and cook in bouillon for 10 minutes.
Melt butter and cook onions in a large pan for 10 minutes.
Mix flour and 3/4 cup water until smooth.
Add to onion mixture.
Add carrots, salt and sugar to taste; simmer for 10 minutes.
A nice change from plain carrots!

title: dutch doughnuts(oliebollen)
directions: First, blend the yeast with a little lukewarm milk.
Sift the flour and salt.
Add milk; mix to a batter with yeast and egg. Add currants, raisins and peeled, minced apple.
Leave batter in a warm place to rise to double its size.
Heat the fat to 375° (190°C).
Put two metal spoons into the batter.
Shape balls with the two spoons and drop them into the fat.
Fry them for 8 minutes until brown.
The doughnuts should be soft and should not be grease-soaked inside.
If they are fried too slowly, the crust becomes hard and tough and the doughnuts become greasy.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve them piled on a dish and cover thickly with sifted confectioners sugar.
Eat them hot, if possible. Makes 20.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together flour, soda, cinnamon, sugar and salt. Add oil, eggs, apples and nuts. Bake in 325° oven. I use a Bundt pan for 1 hour. Makes a large cake.

title: toasted coconut pie
directions: Thoroughly combine first 5 ingredients; stir in coconut.
Pour filling into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool before serving.

title: wheat germ cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine dry cake mix, egg, brown sugar, oil, butter, wheat germ and water in a bowl.
Mix with a spoon (dough will be stiff).
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes for chewy cookies; 12 minutes for crispy.
Cool 1 minute, then remove to rack.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: "healthier" cookie bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer, adding chips last. Spread onto jelly roll pan about 1/2 inch thick (may make more than one pan). Bake at 350° for 15-20 minutes until golden brown.

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Put flour, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Add eggs.
Mix lightly until stiff enough to roll.
Cut in strips and place in boiling chicken broth.
Cook 10 minutes, covered, then 10 minutes uncovered.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk and broth.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in chicken, vegetables and parsley. Heat until bubbly.
Pour into oblong casserole or 6 or 8 individual casseroles.
Top with canned biscuits, cut into fourths (better with a recipe of real biscuits, cut in tiny rounds). Serves 6 or 8 generously.

title: citrus shake
directions: Place ingredients in blender.
Process until smooth and frothy.
Serve immediately in large glass.
Makes 1 serving.

title: deer roast
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place roast on piece of aluminum foil. Sprinkle dry soup mix over meat.
Bring edges of foil together and seal tightly.
Place in shallow pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: jalapeno dip
directions: Brown meat with bell pepper and onions.
Drain, then put in cut up cheese along with rest of ingredients.
Heat until melted or cook slowly in crock-pot, but keep warm!

title: quick macaroni salad
directions: Mix macaroni, diced Spam, pickles and 4 eggs together.
Pour pickle juice into the mayonnaise to your taste, then over all of the ingredients. Garnish with the remaining 2 eggs.

title: chery's cauliflower sauce
directions: Cook cauliflower in 3/4 cup water for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broken glass salad
directions: Separately mix packages of Jell-O with 1 1/2 cups hot water each.
Pour into 3 separate shallow pans.
When set, cut into small cubes.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Add hot water and pineapple juice.
Cool.
Fold this mixture into colored cubes and Cool Whip.
Set until firm.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° until done.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening.
Beat in sugar and eggs.
Sift together and stir in dry ingredients.
Mix in walnuts.
Spread in well-greased baking pan.
Bake until top has dull crust in a 350° oven.

title: paper bag apple pie
directions: Place apples in large bowl.
Combine nutmeg, sugar and flour; sprinkle over apples.
Toss to coat apples well.
Spoon into unbaked pastry shell.
Add lemon juice.
Combine butter, sugar and flour.
Sprinkle over apples.
Slice pie into heavy brown paper bag large enough to cover pie loosely.
Fold open end over twice and fasten with paper clips.
Place on large cookie sheet for easier handling.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and slice tomatoes.
Sprinkle with sugar and let set for 15 minutes.
Combine flour and cornmeal.
Dredge tomato slices in mixture.
Melt butter in large frying pan.
Fry tomato slices until brown on both sides.
Keep warm while making gravy.

title: cranberry salad(super easy and excellent for holiday meals.)
directions: Mix gelatins together; add boiling water. Add cranberry sauce and stir until dissolved. Add pineapple with juice, pecans and celery. Pour in mold and refrigerate. Supposed to serve 12 but it's so good, it seldom does!!!

title: cheese and broccoli potato topper
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, combine soup, sour cream and mustard; add broccoli.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Serve over baked potato/oven baked potato (400° for 1 hour).
Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes.

title: kahlua
directions: Put all ingredients in a one gallon jug.
Shake well until dissolved.
Shake daily for several days.
Store in a dark cool place.

title: crunchy celery casserole
directions: Heat butter, water and bouillon in saucepan.
Add celery and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in salt, sugar and flour, then tomato sauce, water and thyme.
Cook until hot.

title: chocolate chiffon cake
directions: Mix water and cocoa.
Let cool.
Mix flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Make a well.
Add oil, egg yolks and vanilla.
Add cocoa. Mix well.

title: golden fish casserole
directions: Saute pepper and onions in butter.
Blend in the flour and salt.
Remove from heat.
Stir in gradually 2 cups milk.
Return to heat and boil.
Stir in carefully the salmon and juice.
Pour mixture into well-greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli vinaigrette
directions: Mix all ingredients and use to marinate broccoli for several hours or overnight, in refrigerator.
Serve cold as an appetizer.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add unbeaten egg; beat thoroughly.
Mix cocoa and Coca-Cola; bring to a boil.
Add to creamed mixture; beat well.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Add flour and buttermilk mixture to the creamed mixture.
Stir in marshmallows.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add corn, both packages of taco seasoning and 3/4 cup water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Layer tortilla chips in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Then layer meat mixture and cubed Velveeta.
Repeat chips, meat mixture and cheese.
Crush remaining chips and sprinkle over top.
Spread picante sauce evenly over all and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: no-fail fudge
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a 4-quart pan.
Stir over medium heat until blended.
Bring to a boil over medium high heat and continue boiling for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate, vanilla and nuts until chocolate is melted. Pour into two 9 x 9-inch pans and cool.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Core and clean insides of green pepper.
Parboil in water about 4 minutes, until semi-cooked.
Brown ground beef with onion and pepper.
Cook cabbage 5 to 7 minutes, until semi-cooked.
Mix tomato sauce, ketchup, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce; this will make the sauce and topping.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Crust:
Combine graham crackers, 1/4 cup sugar and melted oleo.
Filling: Mix until fluffy the cream cheese, powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Add to cheese the milk and Cool Whip.
Mix and spread over crust.

title: party punch
directions: Partially defrost the lemonade. Pour the lemonade into the punch bowl. Add the chilled Hawaiian Punch| and 7-Up| and mix well. Float fresh lemon and orange slices on top as a garnish. Prep time: 5 minutes.

title: french fried zucchini squash
directions: Peel squash and cut in 4-inch long strips.
Beat egg and add salt, pepper and buttermilk.
Dip squash in this mixture, then coat with flour.
Fry in hot cooking oil until golden brown. Drain on paper towel.
Serve while warm.

title: spaghetti with mushroom sauce
directions: In a frying pan, put oil.
Add the onion, cut up in small pieces.
Saute until browned.
Add mushrooms, parsley, hot pepper and salt.
Let them simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Let it simmer for 15 to 20 minutes more.
At the same time, cook the spaghetti for 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain.
Pour in platter.
Pour the mushroom sauce over, mix and serve.
Serves four to six.

title: low-fat salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Add milk to thin and cottage cheese to thicken.

title: pepper steak
directions: Slice steak diagonally across the grain into 1/8-inch thick pieces.

In small bowl, combine broth, soy sauce and Sweet One. In large skillet, over medium-high heat, heat 1 tablespoon oil. Add half the beef; stir-fry 2 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove beef from skillet; repeat process with remaining oil and beef.
Remove beef from skillet.

title: pie crust - 101(makes 2)
directions: Cut butter into dry ingredients until feels like corn meal. Add 1/4 to 1/2 ice water to mixture until a ball forms. Divide into 2 halves; chill. Roll out into 2 crusts.

title: mother's applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and applesauce.
(Mother cooked tart apples like Granny Smiths.)
Sift flour and spices.
Add to sugar mixture and stir well (save about 1/2 cup to dredge raisins and nuts).
Add raisins to mixture.
Add cherries and 1/4 cup cherry juice to batter.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325°
for 75 minutes.

title: party puffs
directions: Heat water and butter to boiling in medium size saucepan; add flour and salt all at once.
Stir hard with a wooden spoon about 2 minutes or until batter forms a thick smooth ball that follows spoon around pan; remove from heat.

Cool slightly; add eggs, one at a time, beating in each well until mixture is shiny and thick. Shape tiny mound with 2 teaspoons, 1 inch apart, on ungreased cookie sheets (about 1 teaspoon of batter is enough for each). Bake in hot oven (400°) for 25 to 30 minutes or until shells are puffed, crisp and lightly golden.
Remove at once from cookie sheets; cool completely on wire racks.

title: cocoa syrup
directions: Boil 3 minutes.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Pour at once into jar.
Makes 2 cups.

title: crock-pot style macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook in crock-pot on high 3 to 4 hours.
Thirty minutes before you're ready to eat, add cheese, cooked macaroni, milk and butter.
Enjoy!
Tastes great as a meal alone or as a side dish to ham steaks.

title: date nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt together.
Cream butter and honey together.
Add vanilla and beaten eggs to the butter and honey mixture.
Alternately add the flour mixture and the milk to the butter mixture.
Fold in the dates, nuts and orange rind.
Pour into an oiled loaf pan and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: nut roll
directions: Crumble vanilla wafers fine.
Add Eagle Brand milk and margarine.
Mix well.
Add pecans and raisins.
Mix well.
Divide dough.
Roll in 2 rolls.
Chill.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on cake box.
Add frozen coconut and mix well.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: grace marmalade pudding
directions: Butter a 2-quart pie dish; cover the bottom of the dish with a layer of marmalade.
Heat together the butter, milk and 2 teaspoons of sugar.
Add the breadcrumbs; leave to stand for 10 minutes.
Beat together 1 whole egg and 2 egg yolks; stir well into the breadcrumb mixture.
Pour 1/2 of the breadcrumb mixture into the dish.
Add another layer of Grace Seville orange marmalade.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until mixture is set. Whip egg whites stiffly; fold in the last quantity of sugar.
Bake in a very cool oven (290°) for approximately 20 to 30 minutes, until the meringue is brown and crisp.
Serves 6.

title: coconut treasure cake
directions: Beat egg yolks with butter until creamy.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Gradually add flour alternately with milk.
Add coconut. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg whites into mixture.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.
Let cool 15 minutes in pan.

title: chicken-stove top casserole
directions: Heat chicken in 1 quart of water to boiling.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer until chicken is done (about 45 minutes). Remove chicken from pan.
Let cool, then remove bones and skin. Cut chicken into small pieces.

title: rhubarb pineapple pie
directions: Combine tapioca, sugar, salt, rhubarb, pineapple and water. Let stand about 15 minutes.
Roll pastry 1/8-inch thick and line a 9-inch pan.
Trim pastry one-inch larger than pan.
Fold edge to form a standing rim.
Flute.
Fill with fruit mixture.
Combine brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and butter.
Mix with pastry blender, fork or fingers until crumbly.
Sprinkle over fruit mixture. Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: italian cheese and crackers
directions: Empty dry Italian salad dressing mix onto small saucer. Roll cream cheese in
mix
to
completely
coat cheese.	Serve cheese with crackers.
Great for snacks or parties.

title: chocolate-peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, milk, cocoa, margarine and salt in saucepan.
Bring to rolling boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and oats.
Mix well, then drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: Break cake up into 1-inch pieces and put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix pudding and milk.
Add ice cream and mix well.
Dribble over cake pieces.
Dissolve jello in the boiling water and add frozen strawberries.
Pour over cake/pudding mixture.
Chill 4 hours.

title: broiled shrimp with garlic butter
directions: Preheat broiler to highest temperature.
In shallow baking dish or pan large enough to hold shrimp in one layer, melt butter over low heat; don't brown.
Stir in olive oil, lemon juice, shallots, garlic, salt and a few grindings of pepper.
Add shrimp and turn them in butter and oil to coat.
Broil them 3 to 4 inches from heat for 5 minutes, then turn and broil 5 minutes more or until lightly browned.
Transfer to dish with cooked linguini and toss with parsley.
Garnish with lemon quarters.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt and spices. Cream shortening and sugar. Add molasses and vanilla; beat well. Add flour mixture and water alternately, beating until well blended after each addition. Wrap dough in foil. Chill overnight.

title: asparagus and green pea casserole
directions: Pour the drained asparagus in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Pour the drained green peas on top of asparagus.
Add the grated eggs.
Dot with butter or grated cheese.
Heat the soup; pour over all.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake to bubble stage.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix well.
Add 1 cup of nuts or raisins or both.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hot chicken pasta
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; add cubed, cooked chicken.
Drain and rinse both kinds of beans and add to the mixture.
Cook and drain pasta; add pasta, sauce and seasoning.
Stir well and heat through before serving.

title: icebox butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and make into a large roll. Refrigerate overnight. Slice with a sharp knife into very thin slices and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken with apricot glaze
directions: Crush garlic into wine; marinate chicken pieces for 15 minutes.
In the meantime, place apricots in blender or food processor, turn into a paste.
Add dill and tarragon to paste.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350°.

title: applesauce bars
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add beaten eggs and applesauce. Sift flour, salt, soda and spices and add dates, nuts and vanilla. Bake in 11 x 16-inch pan for 25 minutes in 350° oven.
May be topped with powdered sugar icing.

title: dilled cucumbers
directions: Up to 1 week before serving, slice cucumbers very thinly.
In saucepan, combine vinegar, sugar, water and salt; bring to a boil. Layer cucumber and onion slices in jars or container with a cover.
Pour hot vinegar mixture over vegetables; add dill on top. Cover tightly and refrigerate.
Serve as a salad on greens or with hamburgers, etc., as a relish.
Makes 1 quart.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine apples, sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, salt and spice. Spread evenly in a fairly deep square baking pan or dish. Combine remaining ingredients and crumble over top of apples. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is browned.

title: quick cabbage soup
directions: Cook all ingredients together for 1 hour or until meat is tender.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed; drain and cool.
Add all ingredients, but tomatoes.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
Add chopped tomatoes prior to serving on top.

title: venous soup
directions: Cook meat and drain.
In 8 cups of water, add all ingredients, except macaroni.
Cook 25 minutes.
Add cooked macaroni.
Cook 5 minutes.

title: oat crust
directions: Mix all together well. Press into bottom and sides of pie pan. Add filling and bake. For an unbaked pie crust, bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Cool slightly; add filling. For cheesecake; press into bottom of spring form pan. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Cool, then add filling. This is a good crunchy pie crust or as a topping for fruit crisp. Makes 1 crust.

title: parmesan stuffed squash boats
directions: Place squash in boiling, salted water; simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until tender, but still firm.
Drain and cool slightly.
Cut squash in half lengthwise; remove and reserve pulp, leaving a firm shell.
Set aside.

title: transylvania eggplant-romanian(vinete)
directions: Broil eggplant on all sides until well cooked. Scrape off skin and mash with a wooden spoon. Add salt to taste. Mix grated onion with 1 tsp. of the oil and add to the eggplant. Add remaining oil to the eggplant slowly, stirring constantly. Add lemon juice and mix well. Serve on bread or crackers. Ethnic Romanian appetizer.

title: aunt edith's coca-cola cake
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together.
Mix oleo, cocoa and Coca-Cola in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over 1st set. Mix well.
Beat eggs.
Add baking soda and buttermilk.
Beat.
Add marshmallows.
Combine with 1st and 2nd set.
Beat well.
Bake in 9 x 13 greased pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pillow-shi-key
directions: Saute onions, then add the chip steak, salt and pepper.
Cook until meat loses all pink color.
(Do not overcook the steak or turnovers will be dry.)
Open up your dough and add some steak and cheese.
Fold other half over and pinch ends together to seal. Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes or until rolls are lightly browned.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour and baking soda together. Blend butter and sugars together; add eggs. Mix well. Add vanilla and milk. Add flour mixture. Mix well. Stir in oatmeal, chips and nuts. Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Can be used for bars. Press dough in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until light golden brown. Store in tight container.

title: k's shrimp scampi(serves 4)
directions: Using large iron skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add garlic, water or wine, shrimp and pepper.
Mix and simmer 3 minutes.
Add 1/2 pound thawed crab meat stuffing mix and drained crab meat.
Mix. Cover skillet and place in oven for 20 minutes. Do not let mixture dry out.
Serve sizzling hot with liquid.
Good with spinach salad and Zucchini Parmesan.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches into pan.
Mix margarine, sugar, flour and milk together.
Add vanilla.
Pour all ingredients into pan.
Bake until golden brown.

title: amy ouellette's cinnamon muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Place paper fillers in muffin tins; fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven.
Immediately remove the paper fillers. In a small bowl melt 1/4 cup margarine.
In a separate small bowl mix 1/2 cup sugar with 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Dip warm muffin into melted margarine, then into the sugar/cinnamon mixture.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Tear bread into pieces until you have 3 cups.
Place bread pieces in 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, stir in milk, sugar, eggs and cinnamon.
Stir well.
Pour evenly over bread pieces.
Place baking pan in pan of hot water (1-inch deep).
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold.

title: old time buttermilk pie
directions: Put in baking dish.
Bake in oven until crust forms and browns.

title: best cheesecake ever
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and oleo.
Press into a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Add eggs and lemon juice; mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 55 minutes or until center is set.
Cool and chill.
Top with pie filling and refrigerate.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine instant vanilla pudding mix and cold milk.
Beat until well blended.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add Eagle Brand milk.
Fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add celery and onion; cook until tender.
Mix with cooked rice and mushrooms.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pie filling, pineapple, oranges and grapes.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add apples and bananas just before serving.

title: can't goof homemade bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add 2 cups flour and remaining ingredients.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Add remaining flour, stirring with a spoon.
Cover and allow to rise in a warm place until double in size (25 to 30 minutes).

title: stuffed fig salad
directions: Toss together lettuce, watercress, green onions and walnuts. Divide among 4 salad plates; refrigerate.
Cut stems off figs. Using a small knife, carefully rotate tip of knife to make an opening in the stem of each fig.
Form a pocket in the opening with forefinger.
Stuff a small chunk of cheese into pocket of each fig.
Place cheese-stuffed figs in a baking dish.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes, or until cheese starts to melt.
Arrange hot figs on greens on salad plates, allowing 4 figs per serving.
Drizzle balsamic vinegar over salads.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Combine sugar, tapioca, salt and nutmeg.
Add rhubarb and fresh strawberries.
Mix to coat fruit.
Let stand 20 minutes.

title: cafe bavarian mint mocha
directions: Put sugar, coffee, creamer and peppermint candies in electric blender.
Cover and process at liquify until well blended.
Use 1 tablespoon of blended ingredients with 6 ounces of boiling water. Serves 14.

title: liver pate
directions: Cream the pate and cream cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and chill. Serves 12.

title: south-of-the-border squash
directions: Cut
squash
into 1/4-inch slices.
Combine the first 4 ingredients in
saucepan;
cook 6 to 8 minutes or until squash is tender.
Drain
well.
Add	chilies,
pimento
and cheese. Spoon into a lightly greased 1 3/4 quart casserole.
Place egg slices on top
and sprinkle corn chips over egg slices.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: 7 layer vegetable salad
directions: In a 3 to 4-quart shallow glass serving bowl, make a layer of shredded lettuce.
Top with a layer of each of onion, celery, water chestnuts and frozen peas.
Spread evenly with mayonnaise; sprinkle with sugar, cheese, salt and garlic powder.
Crumble bacon onto salad; sprinkle with chopped egg.
Arrange tomato wedges around salad.

title: steve's barbecue shrimp
directions: Combine all together.
Bake at 350° in a large baking pan for 45 minutes; stir after 20 minutes.
Serve with loaf of French bread.

title: southwestern dip
directions: Combine mayo, cheese, green chiles, 1/2 can of olives, Tabasco and garlic powder.
Mix well and place in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish or glass pie dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Garnish with a ring of olives, tomatoes and green onions.

title: lemon fluff salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water and 1 cup cold water. Set in refrigerator until thickened (like honey).
When Jell-O is thickened, whip until foamy.
Fold in whipped cream, one cup of cheese and pineapple.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain, rinse with cold water and drain again.
Mix with real mayonnaise and onion.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: sandi's cream of anything soup
directions: Saute mushrooms and
scallions	in butter.
Thaw frozen vegetables in large pan
over medium heat.	Add soups and milk or water.
Continue simmering	until soup is well mixed and of uniform consistency.
Add mushrooms and scallions.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 400°.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain oranges and add water to juice to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Bring to a boil and add to Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved. Add sherbet and stir until melted.
Chill to consistency of egg whites.
Fold in oranges and pineapple with juice.
Chill until set.
Garnish with cherries or strawberries.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add Milnot; add any flavor instant pudding.
I've use French vanilla and pistachio.
Add milk to fill ice cream maker to line indicated.

title: temptation pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add ice cream and mix until dissolved.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened (approximately 30 minutes).
Fold in remaining ingredients (except kiwi fruit). Pour into pie shell.
Garnish with sliced kiwi fruit.
Refrigerate 3 hours before serving.

title: low-fat barbecued chicken
directions: In a saucepan, combine Worcestershire sauce, water, catsup, pineapple juice, brown sugar substitute and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Combine sauce and margarine in a shallow baking dish.
Marinate chicken for 15 minutes, turning occasionally to coat all sides.
Grill or broil about 3 minutes on each side or bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cucumber-salmon watercress sandwiches
directions: Process cream cheese in food processor. Add finely chopped cucumber, salmon, lemon juice, and 1 tsp. watercress. Mix until well blended. Cut 2 rounds of each bread slice. Spread cheese mixture evenly on one side of bread rounds. Spread edges of sandwiches with butter. Dip edges in 1/2 c. minced watercress. Cover and chill for 2 hours.

title: fiesta corn relish
directions: Peel husks and silks from corn.
Place ears in a kettle; pour in boiling water to cover.
Heat to boiling again; cook 5 minutes; drain.
Cool until easy to handle, then cut corn from cobs. (There should be 8 cups.)
Combine corn with remaining ingredients in kettle; heat, stirring several times, to boiling.
Cook, uncovered for 20 minutes.
Ladle into hot sterilized jars; seal following manufacturer's directions.
Cool jars, label and date.

title: white trash
directions: In large pan melt butter, chocolate chips and peanut butter on low heat.
Mix well.
Mix cereal and peanuts together, then pour into melted mixture and coat thoroughly.
Put powdered sugar in brown paper trash bag.
Pour cereal mixture in bag and shake until well coated.
Everyone loves this!

title: charcoal lamb chops
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper.
Then marinate in a mixture of the other ingredients for 4 hours or overnight.
Grill the drained chops for 6 to 8 minutes on each side for a medium rare (pink center).

title: tomato basil soup
directions: This works great in a crock-pot. Either way, add all ingredients, except cream. Simmer and stir occasionally for about 1 hour. Add cream and serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain vegetables and put in a large flat dish.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, soup, onion and cheese.
Mix well.
Put on top of vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Crush crackers and spread on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lime chicken
directions: Brown chicken in olive oil. Add salt and pepper to taste. Remove chicken from pan and deglaze with the juice of one lime. Add butter and stir until mixed. Add dill and chives. Pour over chicken and serve immediately. Serves 3 to 4.

title: peanut patty candy
directions: Put all ingredients in a large pan.
Cook slowly until it forms a soft ball in water or measures soft ball stage on a candy thermometer.
Take off stove and add 4 teaspoons butter, 2 or 3 drops red food coloring (optional) and 1 cup powdered sugar.
Stir until it begins to thicken real good (which it does quickly). Drop on waxed paper or into buttered muffin pans to cool.

title: greek salad
directions: Layer lettuce, cauliflower, onion and bacon in large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese and sugar and spread over salad, sealing edges.
Make a day ahead.
Mix when ready to serve.
Very large recipe.

title: quick hamburger skillet
directions: Brown the hamburger. Add onions and celery and cook until soft.
Add kidney beans and ketchup and simmer until heated through and flavors blended.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Sift and measure flour.
Add spices and soda; sift again. Cream the shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Add egg and molasses. Beat well.
Add raisins.
Add milk and dry ingredients alternately.
Drop by teaspoon, 2 inches apart, on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a moderate oven, 350°, for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ostakaka
directions: Heat milk to lukewarm.
Mix 1/2 cup flour in a little warm milk, enough to make a paste.
Add the eggs and beat well.
Add to warm milk.
Add rennet tablet which has been dissolved in the warm water to milk mixture immediately, stirring slowly until it curdles.
Let stand for 2 1/2 to 3 hours in a warm place.
Then drain off whey.
Put in a baking dish.
Cut in the sugar and cream and bake at 350° until done.
Serve with lingonberries or strawberries.

title: baked macaroni
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until bubbly and gold on top.

title: four-fruit punch
directions: Combine undiluted frozen juice concentrates with water and sherry.
Chill.
Just before serving, add sparkling water or ginger ale.
Garnish with twists of fresh lemon, lime and orange peel, if desired.

title: challah
directions: Dissolve yeast in hot water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir and then knead together.
Let rise in extra greased bowl about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Also grease top of dough.
Punch down, divide into 3 rolls (like clay snakes) and braid onto greased pan.
Let rise again for 3/4 hour.
Brush top with egg yolk.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored, then add sugar gradually, beating constantly with electric mixer.
Add vinegar and vanilla. Stop beating with mixer and stir in melted butter.
Pour into a pastry and bake at 350° about 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: megan's famous sherbet punch
directions: Spoon sherbet into a large punch bowl. Pour ginger ale over sherbet. Stir gently with ladle. Ladle into cups. Yum!

title: banana cream pie ala microwave
directions: Place sliced bananas in cooled crust.
In a 2-quart glass bowl, mix together sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir milk in gradually and cook on High for 9 minutes. Stir frequently.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: In an ungreased 13 x 9-inch casserole, mix dry rice, mushroom soup, parsley, milk and undrained mushrooms.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburg, onions and green pepper.
Add taco seasoning, chili powder, tomato soup and tomato sauce; mix well.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Add red pepper flakes to taste.
Place in crock-pot; simmer for about an hour.

title: mississippi plantation banana cake(3 layers)
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add all other ingredients and mix well.
Then add mashed bananas.
Bake in 3 layers at 350°.

title: file gumbo
directions: In a large pot, combine water, crabmeat and garlic.
Bring to a boil.
Fry shrimp in oil until firm.
Remove shrimp and put in the pot.
Saute onions in oil and add to pot.
Pour leftover oil into a cup and add oil to bring level back up to 1/4 cup.
Make a roux with the flour and oil*.
Slowly add roux to pot.
Stir and add salt, pepper and parsley.
Simmer for about an hour.
Add oysters and cook another 10 minutes.
Skim off fat.
Serve over rice. Sprinkle file over each individual serving.
Do not cook the gumbo after file has been added, for this will make it stringy.
Serves 8.

title: goody bars
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 1 egg; press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: butterscotch icebox cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar with butter.
Add beaten egg and mix well. Sift flour with soda; add to first mixture.
Add nuts, if you wish.
Form dough into rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper or foil and chill several hours in refrigerator.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350°.
The rolls of dough can be frozen and then thawed before slicing for cookies.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, melted margarine and vinegar. Add coconut, pecans and dates and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in 350° oven for about 40 minutes. Makes 1 pie.

title: sweet potato surprises
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In saucepan, place sweet potatoes, milk and butter; heat until butter is melted.
Mash potatoes.
Add salt, pepper and orange rind.
Form into 4 balls with marshmallow in center of each.
Be sure marshmallows are completely covered. Roll balls in egg, then in cereal.
Bake in pie pan for 20 to 25 minutes, or until crusty.
Makes 4 servings.

title: make butter better
directions: As a compliment to potatoes, fish, chicken or just plain rolls, add any of the above to margarine or butter.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli, cauliflower and onion in small pieces. Mix salad dressing and sugar; toss salad ingredients together. Add crumbled bacon, cheese and sliced or chopped eggs. Mix good. Chill for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: blueberry cream cheese muffins
directions: Toss blueberries with 2 tablespoons flour.
Set aside. Combine remaining flour with dry ingredients and set aside. Combine cream cheese, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat until smooth. Add butter and milk; stir just until moistened.
Fill paper-lined muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes. Remove from pans immediately.

title: cream cheese deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs; peel, split in half and remove yolks.
Mix yolks with other ingredients and put back in egg whites.

title: wassail(warm spicy citrus drink)
directions: Place nutmeg, allspice, cloves and cinnamon sticks in a spice bag. Then place the spice bag and all remaining ingredients in a pot. Heat ingredients and allow to simmer for 15 minutes. Serve hot.

title: ozark hoecake
directions: Combine corn meal, salt and baking powder.
Add fat and stir in water to make soft dough.
Make small cakes 1/2-inch thick. Bake.
Brown on both sides on hot greased griddle.

title: tuna and pasta cheddar melt
directions: Cook pasta in broth and water in skillet until just tender. Do not drain. Add soup, milk and tuna. Top with cheese. Mix bread crumbs and butter. Sprinkle on top. Heat through. Serves 4.

title: pizza chicken italiano
directions: Place chicken in 2-quart baking dish.
Combine tomato sauce, oregano, chopped parsley, garlic salt, onion powder and sugar. Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Top with olives and Mozzarella cheese and continue to bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: zesty barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Great with country ribs or chicken.

title: vegetable spaghetti sauce(serves 6 to 10)
directions: Chop onion and garlic; heat in oil in big pot.
Include bay leaves at this point.
Add vegetables in order listed, all chopped. Saute over medium heat until limp and mushrooms have given up their juice.
Add can of tomatoes, paste, wine and sugar.
Cook on simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add spices at the end to maintain their flavor. Serve with any shape of pasta.

title: pineapple easy cake
directions: Layer ingredients in greased 13 x 9 inch pan in order given.

title: chocolate shortbread logs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl combine first 4 ingredients.
Thoroughly blend.
Using 1 teaspoon of dough for each cookie, shape with hands into 2-inch logs.
Place 1/2-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 13 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.

title: oven fried fish fillets
directions: Spray a baking pan with Pam.
Put crumbs in shallow bowl. Spread each fillet thinly on both sides with mayonnaise, then press lightly in crumbs, coating evenly.
Add more crumbs, if needed.
Arrange in a single layer in pan.
Bake in a very hot oven (400° to 425°) for 8 to 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients except broccoli in blender.
Stir into drained broccoli and mix.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Garnish with paprika.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Melt the margarine in saucepan.
Add the milk and sugar; bring to boil.
Remove from stove.
Add the chocolate chips and marshmallows.
Blend well; frost cake.

title: creme de menthe
directions: Mix sugar and water; bring to a boil.
Boil 8 to 10 minutes. Let cool.
Pour into a jug and mix by shaking.
Serve anytime.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer the first 4 ingredients.
Tear lettuce and cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Crumble bacon and chop onion.
Mix next 3 ingredients for sauce and spread over top of salad.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Toss just before serving.

title: low-fat mini eclairs
directions: Prepare pudding mixes in a separate container, using skim milk instead of water.
Split ladyfingers in half crosswise; spread each bottom half with 1 tablespoons vanilla pudding.
Cover with top half of ladyfinger to make an eclair.
Spread 1 tablespoon chocolate pudding on top of each "eclair".
Drop 1 teaspoon Cool Whip lite in center of eclair.
Chill.
Serves 4 (2 per person).

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Put melted margarine in 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Combine the remaining ingredients with some of the melted margarine.
Mix well.
Pour into baking pan and cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Sift together the flour and sugar.
Cut flour mix into margarine like making pie crust.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in glass dish in a 350° oven or metal pan at 375° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: laurie's chili
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer until thick, about 2 hours.

title: grandma's favorite oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk and cocoa, cooking over medium heat until soft ball; then cook 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat and add butter until melted.
Add peanut butter, mixing quickly; then add oats, mixing quickly.
Spoon on wax paper and cool.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix together and store.
Makes lots of powder.
Use as much in a cup as desired.

title: southwest chicken salad
directions: In large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Pour half over chicken; cover and marinate 1 hour.
For pasta salad, combine tomato, green onions, peppers, black beans, corn and pasta with marinade in bowl; toss to coat.
Cover; chill.
Spray grill or broiler rack with nonstick cooking spray before ignition.
Grill or broil chicken, turning and basting with marinade, 10 minutes or until done.
Thinly slice and serve with pasta salad on lettuce lined platter.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken pieces in greased casserole.
Mix soup, melted margarine and broth.
Pour over chicken.
Place stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream substitute
directions: Mix in blender until smooth and creamy.
Scrape sides occasionally.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute
onion
in margarine; add cooked broccoli, cheese and mushroom
soup.
Stir
until cheese is melted.
Add rice, salt and pepper.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbling, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: microwave play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large microwave bowl.
In smaller bowl mix water, oil and food coloring of your choice.
Mix in with dry ingredients.
Place in microwave.
Cook uncovered for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring after every minute.
Let cool slightly (until able to work with your hands), store in airtight container.

title: picante chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt.
Set aside.
In a 10-inch skillet, cook onion and garlic in oil for 2 minutes.
Add chicken broth and salsa.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Arrange chicken breasts over rice.

title: holiday cheesecakes
directions: Combine 1/3 cup sugar with crumbs and butter; blend well. Press into 10 (5 oz.) custard cups to within 1/4-inch of top, using the back of a spoon.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in 2/3 cup sugar.
Add 1/3 cup heavy cream, flour and seasonings.
Beat until blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Spoon filling into graham shells; place on baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool completely.
Loosen edges with spatula.
Chill until serving time. Remove from custard cups.
Garnish with whipped cream and cherries.
Makes 10 servings.

title: egg rolls
directions: Combine pork, shrimp and onions.
Cook in 1 tablespoon oil for 3 minutes.
Add bean sprouts, water chestnuts, ginger, soy sauce, egg yolk, cornstarch, pepper and salt.
Mix together and place desired amount of filling on skin and roll.
Paste roll together with raw egg white.
Heat oil in fryer to 360°.
Fry until skins are brown.
Makes 36.

title: cheeseburger pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 450 degrees. Let pie crust pouch stand at room temperature for 15-20 minutes.

title: low-sodium barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and mix well.
Simmer, uncovered, over low heat for 20 minutes.
Will keep refrigerated for 1 month.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: special k bars
directions: Mix Special K and coconut.
Mix Karo syrup and sugar and bring to a boil.
Add peanut butter. Pour this over Special K.
Spread on cookie sheet. Do not grease pan. Melt butterscotch chips and chocolate chips. Spread over top.
They freeze nicely.

title: shaving cream bath paint
directions: For a special bath time treat, mix up some shaving cream bath paints.
The kids will love creating silly pictures on the tube and tiles during bath time.
The clean up is simple, just wipe off the water and send paint down the drain.
Squirt shaving cream dollops into each section of a muffin tin.
Add a couple of drops of food coloring to each section and mix together with a spoon.
Place the tin where kids can reach it while in the bathtub.
Let them dip their fingers, hands or sponges into the paints and create pictures on the wall and tub.
When bathtime is over, be sure to rinse away the paint.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Heat 7-Up.
Add jello and cream cheese; mix well.
Add other ingredients.
Chill well.

title: giant gingers
directions: Combine
first	4
ingredients;
set aside. Beat margarine, Karo
syrup, Crisco shortening, 1 cup of the granulated sugar and the egg
until
fluffy.
Add the dry ingredients and the
ginger. Mix well.
Roll
into
balls
and
roll
in
the remaining 1/4 cup of sugar
and the cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or lightly browned.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Add salt, pepper and flour to cutlets.
Brown in butter and remove from pan.
Add mushrooms, broth and wine.
Heat to boiling and boil 1 or 2 minutes.
Return chicken to skillet.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Thicken sauce with flour to desired consistency.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: lobster chowder
directions: Saute lobster meat in butter for 7 to 8 minutes.
In saucepan, combine potatoes, onion and water.
Boil until tender.
Add heated milk and lobster meat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve hot. Serves 2.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Melt margarine in an oblong cake pan.
Add flour and nuts, then press into crust (use more flour, if needed).
Bake crust for 15 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Combine ingredients, except cheese and chips.
Pile lightly in pan and sprinkle with cheese and chips. Bake until heated through, about 10 minutes.
Nice for ladies luncheon.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Cream sugars and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Fold in vanilla.
Blend in flour, salt and baking powder. Fold in coconut, raisins, nuts and zucchini.
Pour batter in lightly greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done.
May be frosted with cream cheese frosting or served plain.

title: lori taylor's chocolate chippers(makes about 4 dozen)
directions: In a large bowl of an electric mixer, cream the butter and brown sugar until smooth.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Stir in the dates and let the mixture stand 5 minutes to soften dates. Then beat at a high speed for 3 minutes or until very light brown and creamy.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cut up chicken.
Wash and pat dry.
In a bowl, add lemon juice, cinnamon, salt and pepper to taste.
Add chicken and coat well with mixture.
In a large frying pan, heat butter and oil together and brown chicken.
Remove chicken pieces to a platter. Keep warm.
Peel and chop tomatoes.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and a cup of water to frying pan containing the butter and oil. Stir and cook tomatoes until very soft.
Return chicken to pan. Cover with sauce.
Cover and cook on low heat until chicken is ready to fall off the bone.
May be served with rice.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and butter.
Pour over Chex cereal and nuts.
Stir well.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Store in airtight container.

title: garden pea salad
directions: In a colander, drain peas very well. Place drained peas in a medium bowl. Add onions, crumbled eggs and mayonnaise, tossing to combine and coat peas. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Add pimento.

title: hickory country ribs
directions: Combine all ingredients except ribs; mix well.
Place ribs in a shallow dish.
Cover with marinade and refrigerate for 24 hours, turning meat occasionally.
Place several presoaked hickory chips on hot coals.
Remove ribs from marinade and place approximately 6 inches above coals.
Close hood of grill.
Cook over low heat, brushing occasionally with marinade.
Serves 6.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Drain one can of Veg-All and 1/2 of second can.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy pan.
Bring to full, rolling boil, stirring constantly, to prevent scorching. Boil 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat. Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Put butter, milk, sugar and salt in a pan over medium heat. Bring to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring continually. Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir to mix.
Beat with a spoon for 1 minute.
Marshmallows should be melted.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool and cut.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: lemon roasted chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pat chicken dry with paper towels. Place in roasting pan in oven.
Roast 40 minutes or until about 3/4 done.
Remove from oven.
Combine mustard, jam and lemon juice in small bowl.
Blend well.
Brush mustard mixture on both sides of chicken.
Bake, skin side up, about 10 to 15 minutes more or until golden brown.
Serve hot or cold.
Remaining sauce can be used for dipping.
Great for picnic!
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple slaw
directions: Cut apples into thin wedges.
Mix all ingredients gently together. Chill.

title: almond pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and flour alternately (1 egg and 1/2 cup flour), mixing well after each. Add flavoring.
Beat well 2 to 3 minutes on medium/high.
Pour into greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: pizzeria rice
directions: Cook rice following package directions, omitting butter.
Add Parmesan cheese, mix well.
Grease a 12-inch pizza pan or two 9-inch pie pans.
Firmly press hot rice mixture on the bottom and 1/2 inch up sides of the pan to form crust.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: peanut butter meltaway
directions: Mix well and form into eggs.
Set in refrigerator until set. Dip in melted chocolate.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Put barbecue sauce over the top before baking.

title: vegetable casserole cottage potatoes
directions: Dice potatoes; add bread cubes, onion, pepper and pimentos. Toss together and season to taste.
Add cheese.
Put in large greased baking pan.
Pour melted butter (or oleo) over top. Sprinkle corn flake crumbs over top.
Pour milk around sides of pan until halfway up.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: 24 hour salad (gladys)
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients in double boiler.
Cook until thickened.
Cool.
When mixture is cool, mix with Cool Whip.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Chill 24 hours.
Can use other canned fruits (chunked or fruit cocktail).

title: peanut brittle candy
directions: In a skillet, combine sugar, water, syrup and salt and stir occasionally.
Boil slow until candy thermometer reaches hard crack.
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla and peanuts. Stir well and continue cooking for about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in baking soda.
Stir well and pour on cookie sheet (slightly buttered).
Crack into pieces.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Place undrained pineapple, sugar and cornstarch in pan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Cool 10 minutes.
Mix dry jello and drained cherries.
Combine all ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Chill overnight.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Boil spinach according to package instructions.
Drain well. Break the cream cheese into drained spinach.
Add butter and mix. Grease a 9 x 9-inch dish.
Break up artichoke hearts to cover bottom of dish.
Pour in spinach mixture.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: chicken caesar salad
directions: Wash and dry lettuce.
Bread the chicken with egg and crumbs. Place in skillet and cook thoroughly.
Crush the cloves of garlic and mix with olive oil, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
When dressing is completely mixed, add the lettuce and toss with Parmesan cheese.
Top with sliced chicken and croutons.

title: peanut-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Don't grease pans.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes, then dry
well.
Cut
into finger width lengths and put in a
bowl.
Toss
potatoes
with rosemary and oil to coat well.
Lay	on
