foil on cookie sheets and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until browned and crispy.

title: sirloin chops
directions: First fry chops until browned.
Add soup, seasonings and water; simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.

title: baby wet wipes
directions: Boil water, add baby oil and baby bath, stir.
Cut paper towel in half.
Put half of paper towel into a large plastic container or a ziplock freezer bag, slowly pour water mixture over paper towel, remove cardboard tube and pull wipes from center of roll.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel and seed 2 large avocados.
In a bowl, mash avocados with 2 tablespoons lime juice, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/4 cup minced onion, 1 diced small tomato and 1 can (4 ounce) diced green chiles.
Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve as a dip with corn chips or as a salad on lettuce.

title: potato skins(from eater's choice)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Scrub potatoes well.
Cut them lengthwise into 6 wedges the size of dill pickle spears and dry them on a paper towel.

title: fried italian potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into cubes. Heat skillet with enough oil to coat bottom. Put potatoes in and sprinkle dressing on top. Stir until coated. Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mash the potato.
Mix egg yolks, sugar, butter, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and milk together well.
Add (fold in) beaten egg whites. Pour into raw unbaked shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook the macaroni until done. Drain water.
Add the soup and margarine or butter.
Mix well until butter melts.

title: deep dish sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: Combine ingredients in order given and pour into pie shell. Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 35 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Place strawberries in medium bowl. Sprinkle with sugar. Let berries thaw, then slice. Butter and flour two 9 x 5 loaf pans. Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt and baking soda in large bowl and mix well. Blend oil and eggs into strawberries. Add to flour mixture.
Stir in pecans. Put into dry ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: creamy potatoes puffs
directions: Combine softened cream cheese with potatoes.
Mix well until blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: no cook ahead lasagna
directions: In a large bowl, combine the Ricotta cheese, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, the egg, spinach and oregano.
In greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, layer 1/2 cup sauce, 1/3 noodles and 1/2 cheese mixture; repeat.
Top with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup remaining Mozzarella cheese over.
Pour water around edges.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
(There is no need to cook noodles ahead of time.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until bubbly.
Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.
Freezes well.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook over low heat about 4 hours or until thick.
May use slow cooker.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and mash them.
Beat egg; add other ingredients and mix together.
Brown 3 slices of bread.
Crumb over casserole. Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put pie filling in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
In bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon, flour, nutmeg, oats and salt.
Add margarine.
Mix up and spread on top of apple filling.
Bake at 375° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hot cakesdallas, texas
directions: In a bowl, put flour, salt, baking powder, soda and corn meal. Mix together and add egg, oil and enough buttermilk to blend into a pourable but thick batter.
Spoon onto a hot griddle that has oil or bacon drippings already hot.
Turn over when top surface is full of holes.

title: custard and bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and milk.
Pour into dish; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken and remove bone and skin. Mix together soup and next 5 ingredients and 1/2 cup of the cheese.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish and line bottom with 1/2 cup of crushed chips.
Mix chicken with soup mixture and pour on top of crushed chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Top with remaining chips and cheese.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Mix lemon juice with condensed milk.
Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix cheese with condensed milk to which lemon juice has been added.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Add Cool Whip.
Fold into mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Blueberry or cherry pie filling can be added on top of pie.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix
sugar, flour and beaten eggs; add all other ingredients. If	you
like meringue, save egg whites;
if not, top with Cool Whip when ready to serve.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir bacon and onion until bacon is crisp.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat until bubbly.
Pour into an ungreased 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 315°.

title: buttermilk pecan candy
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts and flavorings.
Use a large heavy kettle.
Stir only until sugar is dissolved.
Turn heat low and continue cooking until soft ball is formed in cold water or until it reaches 235° on candy thermometer.
The candy gradually browns.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts and flavorings. Beat until slightly thickened and pour into 8-inch square greased pan.

title: dream pie
directions: Mix all together and bake.

title: tuna canapes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix until well blended. Place tuna mixture on toast round; broil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen canapes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Form into a loaf.
Pour ketchup over, wrap in aluminum foil. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry-rhubarb crunch
directions: Combine flour, oats, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon; place half the crumb mixture in a 9-inch square pan.
Add rhubarb and strawberries.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla; cook until thick and clear.
Pour over rhubarb and strawberries.
Cover with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: beef marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate meat for 6 to 8 hours.

title: cousin dora zimmerman's icebox rolls
directions: Add yeast cake to warm milk and water; let stand until foamy. Make a soft dough by adding remainder of ingredients.
Work down and put in icebox until next day.
Make out a few rolls each day until all is used.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: vanilla pie
directions: Mix together and beat with mixer.
In unbaked pie shell, fill with half of the filling and half of the crumb mixture.

title: sunday night specials
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together, drain.
Add sour cream, chopped onion, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder.
Simmer on low heat for about 10 minutes.
Spoon mixture onto English muffin halves, sprinkle with cheddar cheese and broil until cheese melts.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add eggs, sugars and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Knead with hands.
Use small ice cream scoop to drop on sprayed pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Boil and debone 2 to 3 pound fryer.
Chop meat.
Set aside. Cook 1 box wild rice.
Set aside.
In skillet or Dutch oven, melt 1 cup margarine (may be reduced some).
Add 1/2 cup flour.
Add 3 cups broth (or milk) slowly with mushrooms, onions and chicken. Mix well.
Add rice.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: apple walnut supreme cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix together cheeses, pepper and salt. Spread one puff pastry sheet with butter.
Spread with cheese mixture. Place second pastry sheet on top.
Mash together ends of pastry.
With rolling pin, roll out to 1/4 inch thickness, about 15 by 15 inches.
Cut across in 1 inch wide ribbons.
Cut in half again.
Twist each piece (or not). Bake in
a preheated 425 degree oven for 3 to 5 minutes or until puffed and lightly browned.

title: pepperoni pie
directions: Mix all together and put in pie dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in an 8-inch square microwaveproof baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients and crumble over top of apples.
Cover with waxed paper and cook on High for 8 to 10 minutes in microwave.
Serve warm or cold.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Add 1/2 cup salt and let soak overnight. Drain and rinse.
Rinse and drain again.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix all ingredients; spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 to 35 minutes.
Cut into pieces, about 2 x 1-inch. Makes 4 dozen appetizers.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Bake potatoes and allow to fully cool. Remove skin and cut potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes. Set aside.

title: super casserole
directions: Place all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish and top with remaining onion rings.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes (peeled).
Cool and grate.
Mix melted butter with soup, sour cream, onion, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Layer potatoes, then cheese and sauce twice, ending with sauce on top.
Sprinkle with corn flake crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter and stir in stuffing.
Line casserole with half of stuffing mix.
Combine all other ingredients.
Spoon into casserole.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel icing
directions: Combine all except vanilla in heavy skillet.
Boil over low heat until thick and waxy.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and beat until thick enough to spread.

title: texas tarts
directions: Grate the 2 cheeses and mix, divide in half, beat eggs, add milk, flour, salt and pepper.
Grease 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 of cheese in pan.
Spread green chilies over the cheese.
Add remaining cheese.
Pour in the eggs, milk, flour mixture over all. Bake for about 1 hour at 325°.
Cut in squares to serve.
Great as a snack or for breakfast.

title: stuffed zucchini(zucanoes)
directions: Scoop out the insides of the zucchini to leave a 1/4 to 1/2-inch of rim. Chop innards into small bits and cook in margarine with onions, garlic, salt and pepper until onions are soft. Drain excess liquid. Combine with flour, cheeses, parsley and beaten eggs. Fry hamburger; drain and add to the vegetable and cheese filling. Fill zucchini and dust top with paprika. Place in a 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: no-name cake
directions: Put graham crackers on bottom.
Mix pudding and Cool Whip and layer with graham crackers, ending with graham crackers and ice it.

title: crab imperial
directions: Saute green pepper in butter 1 minute.
Mix all ingredients except crabmeat, then gently stir into crabmeat.
Put in individual shells or baking dish.
Spread 1 tablespoon of mayonnaise over each shell.
Sprinkle on paprika.
Bake at 350° until top browns and makes bubbles.

title: blueberry angel dessert
directions: In a large mixing bowl
beat the cream cheese and sugar; fold in whipped topping and cake cubes.
Spread evenly into an ungreased 13 X 9 X 2 inch dish.
Top with pie filling.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before cutting into squares. Yield: 13 - 15 servings.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with chips.

title: super potato salad
directions: Place potatoes and onion in enough water to cover potatoes. Add salt.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer until potatoes are just done.
Do not drain.
Add bouillon cubes and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add milk and cheese.
Continue to simmer until cheese is melted.
Add pepper and remove from heat.

title: cheezy spinach pinwheels
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Unroll dough into 2 long rectangles. Firmly press perforations to seal.
Spread rectangles with cream cheese to within 1/4-inch of edges; top with spinach leaves. Starting at shortest side, roll up each rectangle; press edges to seal.
Cut side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove immediately. Garnish as desired.
Serve warm.
Makes 16 appetizers.

title: dirt cake
directions: Plug hole in the bottom of (new) 8-inch clay flower pot with cookie.
Crush cookies in food processor.
Cream butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Set this aside.
Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Blend pudding mixture into cream cheese mixture.
Layer this mixture and cookies in the flower pot.
End with cookies. Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, plant silk flowers.
Can add gummy worms; kids love it.

title: beef soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes and onions.
Put in large pan.
I use a 6-quart pressure cooker.
Add water and tomato puree.
Start cooking while you lightly brown meat.
Drain meat on paper towel. Add all ingredients in pan.
If pressuring, cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
If open pan, cook until vegetables are tender.
May have to add a little more water while cooking.
I serve with cornbread.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until a firm ball forms in cold water.
Add 1/2 of the syrup to the stiffly beaten egg whites, pouring slowly and beating constantly.
Cook remains of syrup until mixture forms a hard ball in cold water.
Add slowly to the first mixture beating constantly.
Beat until mixture begins to hold its shape.
Add vanilla and walnuts.
Turn into greased pan. When cool, cut into squares.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Halve chicken breasts and wrap each half in bacon.
Cover the bottom of a greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish with chipped beef. Arrange chicken on top of this.
Blend soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
If preparing ahead, refrigerate at this point.
Bake uncovered at 275° for 3 hours.

title: date-raisin-nut cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in oleo until size of peas.
Stir in nuts, coconut, dates and raisins, egg and brandy. Mix with wooden spoon or hand until dough forms.
Chill 1 hour. Shape in 1-inch balls; place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 48.

title: onion casserole
directions: Melt 6 Tbsp. butter and pour over crushed crackers.
Slice onions thin and saute in remaining butter.
Pour 1/2 the onions into a buttered 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Cover with 1/2 of the cheese, then 1/2 of the buttered cracker crumbs.
Repeat layers with remaining onions, cheese and crackers.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: peach jam
directions: Prepare jars and lids. Chop peaches and add lemon juice. Put into a 6 to 8-quart saucepan. Stir in pectin and bring mixture to a full boil over high heat, stirring constantly. Add entire amount of sugar, stirring to dissolve. Return to a rolling boil and boil hard 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and remove foam. Ladle jelly into hot jars. Process 10 minutes. Allow to cool 12 to 24 hours. Check center of lid by pressing down for seal.

title: grandma's soup
directions: In a large kettle, put potatoes, celery, onion, parsley, 1 teaspoon of salt and enough water to cover them, plus some to make the soup as thin or thick as desired.
Pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil and simmer until potatoes are done.
Add ham or sausage.

title: mom's chili
directions: Heat oil.
Add onion, green pepper, garlic, bacon and ground beef.
Brown and drain fat.
Add tomatoes, sugar, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Cook (simmer) 1 hour.
Add beans in the last 15 minutes. May add celery.

title: caribbean pineapple ice cream
directions: Beat the eggs and mix them with the milk and sugar.
Heat until the mixture starts to thicken.
Beat with a whisk and cool. Whip the cream until it thickens.
Fold the cream and crushed pineapple into the custard.
Pour the custard into a plastic container.
Cover it and put in the freezer until firm.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Add all ingredients except cabbage, green beans and macaroni. Bring it all to a boil, lower heat and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes. Add cabbage, green beans and macaroni.
Cook until tender. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken romanesque
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Place cooked spaghetti in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover noodles lightly with butter to prevent clumping.
Season chicken breasts with salt and pepper; cook in large skillet with hot oil until brown, about 3 to 5 minutes to a side.
Arrange on top of noodles.
Add onion, pepper and garlic to skillet.
Cook about 3 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce and oregano.
Cook 1 minute.
Pour over breasts and noodles.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes, until chicken is tender.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach as on package; drain and press out all the water. Add remaining ingredients and mix together.
Let stand 20 to 30 minutes.
Roll into balls with wet hands.
Place on cookie sheets and freeze until hard, then store in bags.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Combine onion, celery, green pepper, cheese, corn and green beans in a large bowl.
Add soup and sour cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with mixture of margarine and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: sponge cake
directions: Last add boiling water.
Mix and bake at 350°.

title: gourmet chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts for 20 minutes in water which 1 teaspoon poultry seasoning and 1/2 teaspoon garlic salt have been added. Cube chicken.
Mix soup, water and sour cream.
Make Stove Top dressing by directions on package.
Layer dressing, cubed chicken, soup mix.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Enjoy!

title: toad-in-the-hole
directions: Make the batter in a blender, combining flour, eggs, milk, salt and a dash of pepper, 2 to 3 seconds on high.
Turn off. Scrape sides of blender and blend another 40 seconds. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Soften bread in milk.
Add meat, seasonings, eggs and onion. Blend thoroughly.
Form into an oblong loaf.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni according to package directions.
Cool completely.
Add all the rest of the ingredients.
Serves 10.

title: summertime cookies
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, oleo and milk.
Boil hard one minute. Remove from fire.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal, vanilla, cherries and coconut.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: taco rice skillet
directions: Brown hamburger with onion in 10-inch skillet with lid.
Drain fat off.
Drain tomatoes into a 2 cup measuring cup, reserving juice.
Chop up tomatoes and place them in a separate dish.
Add water to juice to make 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Add liquid, rice and taco seasoning to hamburger; stir.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until liquid is absorbed, about 25 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Place chips on plate.
Add hamburger mixture and top with cheese, lettuce, avocados, tomatoes and sour cream.

title: cracker candy
directions: Boil brown sugar and butter for 5 minutes. Line pan with foil and cover with soda crackers. Pour the mixture over crackers and bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Cover with nuts and chocolate chips.

title: cauliflower quiche
directions: Cook cauliflower.
Drain well and coarsely chop.
Place on paper towel and squeeze until barely moist.
Coat a 9-inch pie plate with Pam.
Layer cauliflower, green peppers, onion and cheese in pie plate.
Combine remaining ingredients in electric blender. Process 15 seconds or until well blended.
Pour into pie plate. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve and enjoy.

title: lisa's spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook pasta as directed.
Brown hamburger.
Drain off excess fat.
Lay cooked pasta in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Layer hamburger with bell pepper, onions and mushrooms on top of spaghetti.
Top with the mixture of Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate with oleo; gradually blend in milk.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt thoroughly.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Gradually blend in the chocolate mixture.
Pour into thawed pie shells.
Combine coconut and nuts; sprinkle over filling.
Bake at 375°
for 45 minutes.
Filling will be soft, but will set while cooling.
Cool at least 4 hours before serving.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Place milk, sugar, potatoes, butter and salt in a large saucepan.
Heat slowly to boiling point.
Let stand until lukewarm. Add yeast, dissolved in a little of this lukewarm mixture, then add to first mixture.
Mix soda and baking powder with flour.
Stir in to make a stiff dough.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Knead to a stiff dough, adding more flour, if necessary.

title: groovy butter bars
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 egg and butter.
Spread batter in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add remaining 2 eggs and vanilla.
Beat in the powdered sugar.

title: sausage and cheese snacks
directions: Cook sausage until well done and crumbled; drain.
Mix cheese and sausage in top of double boiler.
Spread topping on small slices of rye bread and freeze.
When ready to use, warm in 350° oven and serve.

title: dip
directions: Mix together.
Drain 1 package spinach or 1 package chopped broccoli (frozen).
Serve with crackers or vegetable sticks.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water and season with salt.
Mix cream cheese, milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Put cooked noodles in casserole dish and add cream cheese mixture.
Brown onion and green pepper in butter; add meat and brown on low heat.
Then add tomato sauce.
Skim off grease and cook thick.
Pour over noodles and cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° until casserole bubbles, about 10 minutes.

title: egg casserole
directions: Combine bread and cheese. Beat eggs and add to milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Bake in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole for 1 1/4 hours in a 325° oven. Tastes best when made in advance and placed in oven 1 1/4 hours before serving.

title: party favorite(graham cracker cookie)
directions: Line pan with one layer of crackers.
Mix the next five ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, cooking until slightly thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, add coconut, nuts and cracker crumbs.
Pour this mixture over the cracker layer.
Add another layer of the whole crackers and then frost.

title: swiss steak
directions: Remove all fat from meat and cut in steaks.
Tenderize meat with meat mallet.
Mix flour, onion salt, celery salt, pepper and garlic salt in small bowl.
Cover each piece of meat with flour mixture and brown in frying pan.
After browned, place beef cubes and water in pan (enough water to cover meat).
Cover, reduce heat to simmer and cook 45 minutes.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Put 1/2 stuffing mix in casserole dish; add chicken, then sprinkle onions on.
Melt margarine and add water to it.
Pour over chicken.
Beat eggs in milk.
Pour over mixture.
Top with can of soup and other half of stuffing mix.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: crunchy salad
directions: Combine apples, celery, walnuts, raisins and honey in a serving bowl.
Mix well and serve chilled.

title: moon cake(this is like a huge chocolate eclair!)
directions: Mix water and margarine or butter.
Bring to a boil.
Add flour all at once and stir rapidly until mixture forms a ball. Remove from heat and cool a little while.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well with spoon or mixer.
Spread on ungreased cookie sheet, 11 x 15-inch.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cool. (It will look like the moon's surface; that's why it's called Moon Cake.)
Don't prick.
Leave cake as is.
Mix pudding according to package directions.
Beat in cream cheese.
Blend well.
Spread on crust; refrigerate 20 minutes.
Top with whipped cream or whipped topping generously.
Drizzle with chocolate sauce and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: dilly dip(heart healthy)
directions: Put sour cream in bowl; mix well with all other ingredients. Chill.
Serve with crackers, chips, etc.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook 1/2 of berries, sugar, cornstarch and lemon juice.
Cook on low heat until thick and transparent.
Place whole berries in pie shell and pour cooked mixture over plain berries.
Chill.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Roll graham crackers and put 1/2 on bottom of pan.
Next layer: cream together butter, sugar, eggs yolks and nuts and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Cover graham crackers in pan.
Next layer:
raspberries.
Next layer: whipped cream or Cool Whip. Next layer:
crackers again.
Chill.

title: joe's oriental brisket
directions: Mix teriyaki sauce, water and brown sugar.
Sprinkle in garlic powder and pepper; stir.
Marinate a 3 to 7 pound brisket in teriyaki sauce for 24 hours.
Place brisket on gas or charcoal grill for 1 hour.
Remove and place in pan with teriyaki sauce and bake in oven for 3 1/2 hours.
Turn the brisket 1 time midway through cooking.
Remove meat from oven and let it cool for 15 minutes.
Place on platter, pour teriyaki over meat.
Cut into 3/4-inch strips and serve.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Drain part of juice off peaches.
Pour into oblong pan.
Cut crust off bread slices and then cut in half.
Cover peaches with bread touching one slice to the other.

title: surprise cookies
directions: Mix sugars, add oleo, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour, soda, cream of tartar; mix.
Add coconut, oatmeal and Rice Krispies and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheets, press lightly.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: carrots that even kids will eat
directions: Melt margarine and Velveeta cheese.
Steam carrots and drain. Fold into cheese mixture.
Pour into greased casserole dish; top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Remove all cartilage from crab meat.
In bowl, mix bread crumbs, egg, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Add crab meat; mix gently but thoroughly.
Shape into 6 cakes.
Cook in frying pan in just enough fat to prevent sticking, until brown.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and add sweet milk for batter to be thick. Drop by teaspoonful into hot oil.
Dip spoon into glass of water each time so batter will turn loose of spoon.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Italian seasoning may be substituted for marjoram and oregano.

title: grandma's oatmeal hot cakes
directions: Mix together the night before in a large bowl and let stand covered in refrigerator:
buttermilk and oats.
In the morning, stir in sugar, melted shortening and eggs.
Sift remaining ingredients, except corn, together and stir in just enough to mix (do not try to remove all the lumps).
Add the corn last.

title: chex party mix
directions: Melt margarine; add salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over Chex Mix that is spread in sheet cake pan.
Bake in oven at 250° for 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add all other ingredients. Pour into unbaked "deep dish" pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce temperature to 300° and bake for 35 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in 9 or 10-inch cake pan or cast-iron skillet.
Add sugar and stir until saturated by butter.
Pat evenly on bottom of pan.
Arrange pineapple slices in concentric circles, with a maraschino cherry in alternate "crescents" if desired.

title: paprika potatoes
directions: In a large skillet, slowly saute potatoes in butter until golden brown, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika. Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in order listed; stir gently.
Place in a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package; drain well. Combine soup, grated onion, beaten eggs, lemon rind, lemon juice and mayonnaise; beat until well blended.
Put layer of drained, cooked broccoli in bottom of buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole. Spoon a layer of soup mixture over broccoli, then sprinkle a layer of cheese.
Repeat the broccoli, soup mixture and cheese until all, except for 1/2 cup of cheese and bread crumbs, is used.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Combine the remaining cheese with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over top of casserole; return to oven for 10 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: ramen quickie(two servings)
directions: Fry hamburg and onion together in the frypan until bottom of pan is a bit brown.
Add mushrooms and water.
If you don't use mushrooms, add 1/4 cup more water. Simmer 5 minutes.
Add Ramen noodles and 1/2 package flavoring.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: lemon garlic chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients for marinade. Marinate chicken about 8 hours. Cook chicken on grill, basting with marinade, or broil or bake in oven. Bake at 400 for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: laverne's icebox fruit cake
directions: Work up all ingredients by hand.
When thoroughly mixed, place in container and refrigerate.
Will keep a long time.

title: iced tea syrup
directions: Add tea to boiling water; turn off fire.
Let steep for 5 minutes.
Strain and add sugar.
Use as needed, 2 to 3 teaspoons to a glass of water.

title: garlic string beans f.d.
directions: Cut ends off the string beans and rinse with cold water.
Fill a large pot 1/2 way with water until boiling.
Add string beans and parboil 10 to 12 minutes until cooked, but not real soft. Remove and drain.
In large frying pan, cover bottom about 1/4-inch with olive oil and heat.
Add garlic and string beans and fry on medium heat, mixing all ingredients together.
When almost done, add bread crumbs and mix briefly and serve.
Serve with Denny's chicken and your favorite macaroni, meat loaf, etc.

title: salsa
directions: Scald and peel tomatoes.
Cut into small pieces.
Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
To thicken salsa, add 4 tablespoons cornstarch or up to 1/2 cup if thicker sauce is desired.
Process in hot water bath 30 minutes.

title: t. v. snack
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in a large roaster.
Melt butter.
Pour butter over the mixed ingredients and mix together. Bake in a slow oven at 250° for 2 hours.

title: easy tortilla bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Line pan with tortillas, bringing edges up even to top of pan.
Cook ground beef and onions in skillet.
Drain.
Stir in seasoning and tomato sauce.
Spoon mixture onto tortillas.
Beat milk, eggs and baking mix in blender on high speed for about 15 seconds.
Pour over beef mixture.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool 10 minutes before cutting.
Serve with onions, shredded lettuce and sour cream.
Yields 8 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell. Bake 15 minutes, then reduce to 350° and bake 35 to 45 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on wire rack.

title: cool whip delight
directions: Add if desired, sliced apples, bananas and nuts.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimiento and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into 1-quart casserole. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer. This recipe can also be doubled. Baking time is a little longer.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream margarine; add flour, salt, Tabasco, cheese and cereal. Roll into small balls and place onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: coconut macaroon cupcakes
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together sugar, butter or margarine and salt until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add almond extract.
Fold flour into creamed mixture.
Stir in coconut.
Fill 24 muffin pans lined with paper bake cups 2/3 full with batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Cool on wire rack.
Sift powdered sugar over top if desired.
Makes 24 cupcakes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms thoroughly and pat dry.
Remove stems.
Chop stems fine.
Melt 1/4 cup of the butter in a skillet.
Saute mushroom caps briefly on both sides until they begin to turn beige.
Remove caps from pan.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients in 9 X 13 cake pan and spread evenly.
Place chicken thighs on rice mixture.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper, garlic salt and Mrs. Dash seasoning.
Cook approximately 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt Velveeta in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish in the microwave and mix in the mayo.
Hit frozen hash browns on counter until separated and add to cheese mixture and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
While this is baking, fry the bacon; drain and break into pieces.
Add bacon to top of first mixture and continue to bake for 15 more minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place the chicken in water with rice, onions, celery and dash of salt.
Bring to boil, cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Remove chicken and let cool.
Strain the broth; remove the chicken from the bone.
Mix chicken, broth and remaining ingredients together. Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald milk and pour over bread crumbs.
Cool and add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Place casserole dish in pan of hot water (1 inch deep).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until a silver knife inserted into pudding comes out clean.

title: christmas potato candy
directions: Mix potatoes and sugar.
Stir in rest of ingredients, except chocolate.
Blend well.
Press into a large pan to 1/2 inch thickness.
Melt chocolate and pour over candy.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: italian meat balls
directions: Soak toast in cold water about 7 minutes, then press dry. Combine all ingredients in a bowl and thoroughly blend.
Form into 12 medium balls and fry slowly in about 2 tablespoons hot shortening until golden brown.
(Do not turn these until absolutely brown.)
Add meat balls and drippings to sauce.
(Add several tablespoons of water to frying pan and scrape drippings and add to sauce.)
Simmer in sauce slowly so meat balls do not fall apart.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pan and cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie crust. Top with meringue.
Bake until meringue is lightly browned.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
May be frozen.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Brown chicken on both sides in oil. Remove chicken and saute onion and celery until soft and golden. Add mushrooms and tomatoes.
Bring to boil.
Add seasoning and chicken.
Simmer approximately 30 minutes.
Cook spaghetti according to directions. Drain.
Pour chicken and sauce over spaghetti.
Yields 4 servings.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add shortening.
Blend until mixture is coarse and mealy.
Add remaining ingredients, except peppers.
Mix well.
Fill greased muffin tin with mixture.
Place peppers on top. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 450°.

title: orange cheese cake
directions: Reserve 1 cup of dry cake mix.
Combine remaining mix, 1 egg and oil.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Press into bottom and sides of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Into bowl, blend the cream cheese, sugar, 3 eggs and reserved cake mix.
Beat 1 minute.
Slowly add milk and lemon juice.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes, until center is firm.
When cool, spread with topping. Chill before serving.
Refrigerate.
